`sage_module_sketchmig.md` · SAGE 2.0 Documentation Library

---

## 1. Introduction

SketchMig is SAGE''s smart entity-to-sketch migration tool, designed to promote generated frames from any production entity type (characters, animas, locations, backgrounds, etc.) into the `sketches` pipeline for further AI refinement. It solves a key workflow problem: once a generation map run produces promising frames for a given entity, those frames and their associated prompt/seed data need to be cloned into the Sketches entity system before they can be re-processed, rated, or used as img2img sources. SketchMig handles this promotion atomically — creating or reusing sketch records, cloning frames with full metadata, writing `frames_2_sketches` mapping entries, and logging migration provenance — all within a single database transaction. It sits between the generation layer (Taggeranger, Showrunner, map run system) and the downstream sketch curation and image refinement pipeline.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

SketchMig bridges SAGE''s entity-based generation system and the `sketches` entity type. Its core function is to take one or more frames from an existing map run (belonging to characters, animas, locations, or any other supported entity type) and clone them into the sketches system with proper relational integrity.

- **Input:** A selected `map_run` belonging to any non-sketch entity type, with one or more frames chosen for migration
- **Output:** New or updated `sketches` records; cloned `frames` records pointing to those sketches; `frames_2_sketches` join entries; `sketch_migration_entities` mapping for idempotent re-migration; `sketch_migration_frames` provenance log; a new `map_run` of type `''sketches''` grouping the migrated frames

---

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Entity type selector** | Dropdown in the header lets the user switch between any non-sketch, non-system entity type. Uses `$entityIcons` for display labels. |
| **Map run browser** | Paginated (20/page), searchable list of map runs for the selected entity type. Shows frame count and creation date per run. |
| **Frame grid** | Responsive photo grid of all frames in the selected run. Each card shows the entity name and a selection toggle. PhotoSwipe lightbox for full-size preview. |
| **Migration status overlay** | Cards already migrated show a `MIGRATED` watermark and are desaturated. A "Hide Migrated" toggle removes them from the grid entirely. |
| **Select All / None** | Toolbar shortcuts for bulk selection. |
| **Idempotent sketch resolution** | If a source entity has already been migrated, its existing sketch record is reused (with a timestamp bump) rather than creating a duplicate. |
| **Name collision guard** | If a new sketch name already exists, a date-stamped suffix (`Mig YYMMDD`) is appended. |
| **Atomic transaction** | The full migration — sketch creation/reuse, frame cloning, join table writes, provenance logging — runs inside a single `PDO` transaction with rollback on error. |
| **Toast feedback** | Success and error states surfaced via the shared `Toast` JS module. |

---

### Data Model

#### Tables Read

| Table | Usage |
|---|---|
| `map_runs` | Browsed and filtered by entity type; frame counts subqueried per run |
| `frames` | Source frames fetched per run; cloned into new frames records |
| `{entity_type}` (dynamic) | Joined to frames to pull `name`, `description`, `prompt_negative`, `seed` for sketch creation |
| `sketch_migration_frames` | Checked to determine whether a frame has already been migrated (`is_migrated` flag) |
| `sketch_migration_entities` | Checked for existing entity→sketch mappings before creating new sketches |

#### Tables Written

| Table | Usage |
|---|---|
| `map_runs` | New record created with `entity_type = ''sketches''` to group migrated frames |
| `sketches` | New sketch created per unique source entity (if not already mapped) |
| `frames` | New frame records cloned from source, `entity_type = ''sketches''`, `entity_id = sketch_id` |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Join entry written for every new frame → its target sketch |
| `sketch_migration_entities` | `(source_type, source_id) → target_sketch_id` mapping persisted for idempotency |
| `sketch_migration_frames` | `(source_frame_id, target_frame_id)` provenance log with timestamp |

#### Key Schema Notes

- `frames.entity_id` is overloaded: in the cloned records it points to the `sketches.id`, with `entity_type = ''sketches''`
- `sketch_migration_frames` uses `source_frame_id` as primary key (`INSERT IGNORE` prevents duplicate provenance rows)
- `frames_2_sketches` has a `CASCADE DELETE` FK on `to_id → sketches.id`

---

### API / Backend Integration

SketchMig is fully self-contained in PHP with no PyAPI or external AI provider calls. All three API actions are handled via `?api_action=` GET/POST dispatch within `sketchmig.php` itself:

| `api_action` | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `get_map_runs` | GET | Returns paginated map runs for the selected entity type. Params: `limit`, `offset`, `search`, `entity_type` |
| `get_frames` | GET | Returns all frames for a given `map_run_id`, joined to the entity table and `sketch_migration_frames` for migration status. Params: `map_run_id`, `entity_type` |
| `submit_migration` | POST (JSON body) | Executes the full migration transaction. Body: `{ frame_ids: int[], entity_type: string }` |

No scheduler job is triggered on migration completion. The new sketch''s `active_map_run_id` is set to the newly created map run, and `regenerate_images` is set to `0`.

---

### UI & Interaction

The view uses a fixed full-viewport layout (`100dvh`) divided into four zones stacked vertically:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  HEADER — title + entity type select│
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  TOP PANEL — map run browser        │
│  (paginated list, max 30vh)         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  MID PANEL — toolbar (info, filters)│
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  GRID AREA — frames grid (flex:1)   │
│  (scrollable, PhotoSwipe lightbox)  │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  FOOTER — selection count + submit  │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Interaction flow:**

1. User selects entity type from header dropdown → map run list reloads
2. User taps a map run row → frames grid populates below
3. Frame cards are toggled by tapping the label bar (not the image — image tap opens lightbox)
4. "All" / "None" shortcuts available in the toolbar once a run is loaded
5. "Hide Migrated" checkbox filters already-migrated cards from the grid
6. Footer shows live selection count; "Migrate to Sketches" button is disabled until ≥1 frame is selected
7. On success, the grid refreshes in-place with updated migration status

**Mobile-first notes:**
- Layout uses `100dvh` and `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` for iOS/Android safe area compliance
- `overflow: hidden` on body prevents scroll; only the grid area and run list scroll independently
- Frame grid uses `auto-fill / minmax(130px, 1fr)` — adapts to narrow screens without breakpoints
- Images use `loading="lazy"` to avoid loading off-screen cards

**Style notes:**
- Uses a teal accent (`#2dd4bf`) rather than the standard SAGE amber — this is intentional visual differentiation for the migration utility context [VERIFY: whether this diverges intentionally from the Forge UI system or is a legacy holdover]
- Fonts: `DM Mono` / `Fira Mono` (monospace stack) — no Syne/Space Mono from the standard Forge UI [VERIFY]

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Module / System | Relationship |
|---|---|
| `entity_icons.php` | Provides `$entityIcons` array used to populate the source entity dropdown |
| `map_runs` table | Shared with the broader generation pipeline (Taggeranger, generator modules) |
| `frames` table | Central shared asset table across all generation entity types |
| `sketches` entity system | Target of all migrations; downstream module where sketch-based generation and curation occurs |
| Taggeranger / Generator Forge | Upstream producers of the map runs and frames that SketchMig consumes |
| PhotoSwipe v5 (CDN) | Lightbox library for full-size frame preview within the grid |
| `toast.js` / `toast.css` | Shared SAGE toast notification system |
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Standard SAGE bootstrap chain for DB connections and environment |
| `templates/curation.php` | Layout template used for render wrapping (shared with other curation-class views) |

---

### Known State / Notes

- **`sketch_migration_entities` table** is referenced in the migration logic (`stmtCheckMap`, `stmtInsertMap`) but is **not included in the provided schema dump** — its DDL should be verified and added to the module''s schema documentation. [VERIFY]
- The `applyGridFilters()` function is referenced in the "Hide Migrated" checkbox `onchange` handler but is **not defined** in the provided JS — the actual filtering is done by toggling the `hidden-in-grid` CSS class during `renderGrid()`. The function name in the HTML may be a stale reference or a thin wrapper. [VERIFY]
- `toggleAll(true)` selects all cards including already-migrated ones — there is no guard to exclude `is-migrated` cards from bulk selection. This may be intentional (re-migration is idempotent) but could cause confusion. [VERIFY]
- The `lightbox` instance is initialized once on `DOMContentLoaded` and is not re-initialized after `renderGrid()` rebuilds the DOM — PhotoSwipe''s gallery selector (`#framesGrid`) should still pick up new children if the gallery element itself persists, but behaviour after grid re-render post-migration should be tested. [VERIFY]
- The teal accent color and monospace font stack diverge from the standard Forge UI amber/Space Mono design system. Whether this is deliberate visual scoping for migration utilities or an artifact of independent development is not documented. [VERIFY]
