**File:** `sage_module_entity_viewer.md`  
**Source files:** `entity_viewer.php`, `entity_viewer_api.php`, `entity_icons.php`

---

## 1. Introduction

The Entity Viewer is SAGE''s universal asset gallery and inspection interface, providing a paginated, multi-mode browser for all major production entity types — characters, locations, animas, vehicles, artifacts, sketches, composites, generatives, and more. It solves the problem of needing a single, fast visual surface to browse and cross-reference the image and video output attached to any entity class in the production database, without navigating into individual entity edit screens. The viewer operates in two modes — Entity Mode, which groups frames by the entity they were generated for, and Map Run Mode, which groups frames by the generation batch (map run) that produced them. Each frame card surfaces rich metadata including prompt text, ingredient composition (the sketch recipe that drove generation), and AI analysis/curation scores where available, making it a lightweight quality-review station as well as a browser.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Entity Viewer provides a read-oriented, paginated gallery over SAGE''s visual asset corpus. It does not perform generation or editing directly, but acts as a cross-cutting inspection layer: any entity type with an associated `frames_2_{type}` link table (or `map_runs` association) can be browsed here. It sits downstream of all generation pipelines and upstream of any curation or selection workflow.

**Inputs:** Entity type selection, optional ID range filter, mode toggle, page number.  
**Outputs:** Rendered gallery of frame cards (image + metadata) or video playlists, with modal popups for ingredient detail and AI analysis data.

---

### Key Features

#### Entity Mode
Paginates over rows in a named entity table (e.g. `characters`, `locations`), then for each entity fetches all associated frames via the `frames_2_{type}` join table. Each entity appears as a horizontal Swiper carousel of frame cards.

#### Map Run Mode
Paginates over `map_runs` filtered by `entity_type`, grouping frames by the generation batch rather than the entity. Supports video map runs: if a `map_run_id` has associated rows in `videos`, the item renders as a VideoJS playlist player instead of a frame carousel.

#### ID Range Filter
`From ID` / `To ID` inputs allow scoping the paginated results to a specific numeric ID range within the selected entity or map run set. State is preserved in the URL query string.

#### Frame Cards with Swiper Carousel
Each entity''s frames render as Swiper.js slides with `freeMode` horizontal scroll, navigation arrows, and a scrollbar. Frame cards show:
- Thumbnail image (PhotoSwipe lightbox on click)
- Frame ID
- Truncated prompt text (click to open full description modal)
- **Meta badge** — if the source sketch has ingredient records in `sketch_ingredients`, opens an ingredient composition modal
- **Analysis badge** — if the source sketch has a row in `sketch_analysis`, opens a curation modal showing overall quality score, narrative function, emotional tone, themes, and characters

#### Video Playlist Mode
When a map run has associated video records, a two-panel layout renders: a VideoJS player on the left and a horizontal strip of thumbnail cards on the right. Clicking a thumbnail switches the active video source.

#### Gear Menu Integration
Each frame card carries `data-gear-menu` attributes (`data-entity`, `data-entity-id`, `data-frame-id`, `data-img-url`), enabling the global `GearMenu` component to attach standard entity actions (edit, delete, re-generate, etc.) via the shared `gear_menu_globals.js` system.

#### URL State Persistence
Entity type, mode, page number, and ID filters are written to `window.history.replaceState` on every load, allowing deep-linking and browser back/forward navigation.

#### Theme Toggle
Inline light/dark toggle writes to `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and sets the `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`, consistent with the Forge UI system.

---

### Data Model

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `{entity_type}` (e.g. `characters`) | Source entity rows; fetches `id`, `name`, `created_at` |
| `frames_2_{entity_type}` | Join table linking `frames.id` → entity `id` via `from_id` / `to_id` columns |
| `frames` | Core asset records; `filename`, `prompt`, `entity_type`, `entity_id` |
| `sketches` | Source sketch record for a frame; supplies `description` |
| `sketch_ingredients` | Per-sketch ingredient rows; drives the Meta modal content |
| `generator_config` | Generator configuration records; titles resolved for ingredient labels |
| `meta_sketches` | Links sketch → generator config, template, interaction |
| `sketch_templates` | Template name, `core_idea`, `shot_type`, `camera_angle`, `perspective` |
| `interactions` | Interaction name for legacy meta display |
| `sketch_analysis` | AI curation output: `overall_quality`, `classification`, `scoring`, `entities`, `thematics`, `recommendations` (JSON columns) |
| `generatives` | Generative entity name (joined when `f.entity_type = ''generatives''`) |
| `image_edits` | Edit tool and note for derived frames |
| `map_runs` | Generation batch records; `entity_type`, `note`, `created_at` |
| `videos` | Video records linked to map runs via `map_run_id` |

#### Entity Icon Registry (`entity_icons.php`)

The `$entityIcons` array maps entity type slugs to emoji display characters used in the dropdown and elsewhere. The `$entitySchedulerIds` array maps entity types to their scheduler job IDs (used by other modules referencing this file, not directly by the viewer UI).

---

### API / Backend Integration

All data fetching goes through `entity_viewer_api.php` via `$.post(''entity_viewer_api.php?action=fetch_content'', ...)`.

**Action: `fetch_content`**

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `entity_type` | string | Entity table slug (e.g. `characters`) |
| `mode` | string | `entity` or `map_run` |
| `page` | int | Page number (1-indexed) |
| `from_id` | int\|null | Minimum entity/map_run ID filter |
| `to_id` | int\|null | Maximum entity/map_run ID filter |

**Response:**
```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "items": [...],
  "total_pages": 12,
  "current_page": 3
}
```

Each item in `items` carries:
- `id`, `title`, `meta` — display identity
- `frames` — array of hydrated frame objects (with `normalized_ingredients` and `curation` appended)
- `videos` — array of video records (populated only in video map run mode)
- `type` — `"image"` or `"video"`
- `item_type` — the entity slug or `"map_run"`

No external AI provider calls are made from this module. No scheduler jobs are triggered.

The `KitchenChef` class (`App\SceneKitchen\KitchenChef`) is instantiated in the API but its methods are not called directly in the current `fetch_content` path; it is available for potential future use. `[VERIFY]`

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout
- **Sticky header bar** — entity type dropdown, From/To ID inputs, Entity/Map mode toggle, theme toggle. On mobile (`< 768px`), the "Entity Viewer" title hides and ID inputs compress.
- **Content area** — `#viewer-content`, max-width 1600px centred. Each entity renders as a `.gallery-container` block with a title/meta row and a Swiper carousel or video player below.
- **Pagination bar** — previous/next buttons flanking a direct page number input.

#### Modals
Three overlay modals are used:

| Modal ID | Trigger | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `#meta-modal` | Click `.badge-meta` ("Meta" badge) | List of sketch ingredients with type icon, label, prompt fragment detail |
| `#analysis-modal` | Click `.badge-curator` ("Analysis (N)" badge) | Quality score, narrative function, tone, theme pills, character pills |
| `#desc-modal` | Click `.chain-card-prompt` (truncated prompt) | Full prompt/sketch description in monospace pre-wrap |

Modal overlays close on click of the backdrop or the `×` button.

#### Lightbox
PhotoSwipe 5 is initialised as `window.initLightbox()` after each content render, attaching to `.pswp-gallery` / `.pswp-gallery-item` elements. Natural image dimensions are written into `data-pswp-width` / `data-pswp-height` via the `onload` handler.

#### VideoJS
Video.js 8.5.2 is used for video playback. Players are initialised on each `initComponents()` call. The `changeVideo()` helper switches the active source on a pre-existing player instance using `videojs.getPlayer()`.

#### Mobile Behaviour
All views are mobile-first. The header uses `flex-wrap: nowrap` with `overflow-x: auto` for horizontal scroll on small screens. Swiper''s `freeMode` and `slidesPerView: ''auto''` handle touch-scroll carousels natively. Pagination uses a direct numeric input rather than a page-number list for compact vertical space.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Core | DB connections, session, access control |
| `entity_icons.php` | Shared config | Icon map and scheduler ID map |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | UI component | Included via `ob_start()` capture; provides frame detail modal markup |
| `GearMenu` module (`ModuleRegistry`) | UI component | Attaches standard entity actions to frame cards |
| `ImageEditor` module (`ModuleRegistry`) | UI component | Rendered on page; attachment to cards handled by `gear_menu_globals.js` |
| `forge_tool.php` | UI component | Forge tool footer (consistent across SAGE views) |
| `sage-home-button.js` | UI component | Back-to-dashboard button |
| `App\SceneKitchen\KitchenChef` | PHP class | Instantiated in API; not actively called in current code path `[VERIFY]` |
| Swiper.js 11 | JS library | CDN; horizontal frame carousels |
| PhotoSwipe 5 | JS library | CDN; image lightbox |
| Video.js 8.5.2 | JS library | CDN; video playback |

**Modules that link into Entity Viewer:**  
The dashboard and any view that uses `$entitySchedulerIds` may reference `entity_icons.php` directly. The Taggeranger and map run review views share the `sketch_analysis` data surface shown in the Analysis modal.

---

### Known State / Notes

- The `$availableEntities` array in `entity_viewer.php` defines which entity types appear in the dropdown for browsing: `characters`, `locations`, `backgrounds`, `animas`, `vehicles`, `artifacts`, `sketches`, `generatives`, `composites`. This is a subset of all types defined in `$entityIcons` — types like `frames`, `scene_parts`, `controlnet_maps`, `spawns`, `prompt_matrix_blueprints`, and `composites` are listed in `$entities_with_menu` for gear menu support but several are not exposed in the viewer dropdown. `[VERIFY]` intended scope.
- Legacy meta hydration path (using `meta_id`, `gen_config_title`, `template_name`, `interaction_name` from the SQL join) runs as a fallback when `normalized_ingredients` resolves empty. This covers older frames created before `sketch_ingredients` was introduced.
- The `frames` table is fetched with `ORDER BY f.id ASC` within each entity, meaning oldest frames appear first in the carousel.
- Pagination is set to `$LIMIT = 10` items per page in the API.
- `KitchenChef` is instantiated at the top of the API file and passed into `getRichContentForItem()` but none of its methods appear to be called in the current implementation. `[VERIFY]` whether it is a legacy holdover or reserved for a planned feature.
- The `scroll-magic-link` CSS class and its hover style are defined in the stylesheet but no element using this class is rendered by the current PHP/JS — likely a remnant of an earlier navigation feature. `[VERIFY]`
- VideoJS player instances are initialised with a guard (`if(!el.player)`) but VideoJS''s own API uses `videojs.getPlayer()` for retrieval — the guard condition may not behave as expected if VideoJS stores the player reference differently. `[VERIFY]`
