**File:** `sage_module_wordnet_admin.md`
**Source:** `public/view_wordnet_admin.php`, `public/wordnet_api.php`, `public/wordnet_proxy.php`, `src/Service/WordnetApi.php`

---

## Introduction

The WordNet Admin module is SAGE''s lexical database browser, providing access to Princeton WordNet''s structured vocabulary data directly from within the platform. It allows writers and narrative designers to explore word meanings, synonym sets (synsets), sense definitions, and semantic relationships such as hypernyms — supporting richer, more precise language in scripts, lore documents, and AI prompt construction. The module sits downstream of the Lore and Narrative layers, functioning as a reference utility rather than a production-pipeline actor. It communicates with a locally hosted Python FastAPI microservice (`wordnet_pyapi`, default port `8009`) that queries a MariaDB database populated from the WordNet SQL dump.

---

## Purpose & Scope

WordNet Admin gives SAGE users a search interface into the WordNet lexical database. Its purpose is vocabulary research: given a word (lemma), a user can retrieve all its senses (synsets), read definitions and usage examples, and traverse semantic relationships upward through the hypernym tree.

- **Inputs:** A lemma string entered by the user (or passed via URL query parameter `?q=`)
- **Outputs:** Lists of matching lemmas, sense records per lemma, synset detail cards, hypernym chains
- **Pipeline position:** Reference/research utility — not a write-path module; no content is persisted to the main SAGE database

---

## Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Lemma search | Full-text prefix/match search against the `words` table via the PyAPI `/wordnet/search` endpoint |
| Sense viewer | Lists all synsets associated with a lemma, showing synset ID, POS tag, definition, and usage samples |
| Synset detail modal | Opens a detail view for any synset: full definition, synonym list, and a button to load hypernyms |
| Hypernym expansion | Traverses the `semlinks` table (hypernym link type) and returns parent synsets inline in the modal |
| Raw JSON view | A debug utility that dumps the raw synset data object into a formatted `<pre>` block inside the modal |
| DB not-initialized guard | If the WordNet tables do not exist, the search result area displays an amber setup prompt with a link to `view_wordnet_initial_import.php` rather than a raw error |
| URL pre-population | If `?q=` is present in the page URL on load, the search field is auto-populated and the search fires immediately |

---

## Data Model

The WordNet module operates on a **separate MariaDB database** (`wordnet`) populated from the standard Princeton WordNet SQL schema. It does **not** read from or write to the main SAGE application database.

### Core Tables

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `words` | Canonical lemma strings with integer `wordid` keys |
| `synsets` | Synonym sets: POS tag, lexical domain, and definition text |
| `senses` | Junction table linking words to synsets; stores sense number, tag count, and sense key |
| `samples` | Usage example sentences keyed to `synsetid` |
| `semlinks` | Semantic relations between synsets (hypernym, hyponym, etc.) keyed by `linkid` |
| `lexlinks` | Lexical relations between word-sense pairs |
| `morphs` / `morphmaps` | Morphological variants mapped to base lemmas |
| `linktypes` | Reference table for semantic/lexical relation type names |
| `lexdomains` | Lexical domain names (e.g. `noun.cognition`, `verb.motion`) |

### Views (pre-built joins)

| View | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `dict` | Full dictionary view joining words, senses, synsets, cased forms, and sample sets |
| `wordsXsensesXsynsets` | Flattened word → sense → synset join |
| `sensesXsemlinksXsenses` | Sense-level semantic relation traversal |
| `synsetsXsemlinksXsynsets` | Synset-to-synset semantic link view |
| `morphology` | Word forms with POS and base lemma |
| `samplesets` | Aggregated usage examples per synset (pipe-delimited) |
| `verbswithframes` | Verbs extended with verbal frame data |
| `adjectiveswithpositions` | Adjectives with attributive/predicative position data |

---

## API / Backend Integration

### PHP → PyAPI (`src/Service/WordnetApi.php`)

All database queries are proxied through a FastAPI microservice. The `WordnetApi` service class makes direct HTTP calls via cURL to `http://127.0.0.1:8009` (configurable via `WORDNET_PYAPI_URL` env variable or `$GLOBALS`).

| Method | HTTP | PyAPI Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `search()` | GET | `/wordnet/search?q={q}&limit={n}` | Lemma prefix/match search |
| `lemma()` | GET | `/wordnet/lemma/{lemma}` | All senses for a lemma |
| `synset()` | GET | `/wordnet/synset/{id}` | Full synset detail |
| `hypernyms()` | GET | `/wordnet/hypernyms/{id}` | Hypernym chain for a synset |
| `morph()` | GET | `/wordnet/morph/{m}` | Morphological lookup [VERIFY: not exposed in UI] |

### PHP Router (`wordnet_api.php`)

A thin PHP JSON router that validates the `action` parameter and delegates to `WordnetApi`. Accepts both GET params and JSON POST body. Returns `{"status":"ok","data":...}` or `{"status":"error","message":...}`.

Supported actions: `search`, `lemma`, `synset`, `hypernyms`, `morph`

### Proxy (`wordnet_proxy.php`)

A secondary proxy entrypoint using a `WordnetBridge` class [VERIFY: `App\Wordnet\WordnetBridge` — separate class not included in dump]. Exposes a subset of actions: `lemma`, `synset`, `search`, `hypernyms`, `debug`. Uses a file logger from `$spw->getFileLogger()`. The relationship between this proxy and `wordnet_api.php` — whether they are parallel paths or one supersedes the other — is unclear from the source provided. `[VERIFY]`

---

## UI & Interaction

The view (`view_wordnet_admin.php`) renders within the standard SAGE layout via `$spw->renderLayout()` and uses `css/base.css` + `css/toast.css`.

### Layout

- **Header bar:** Page title ("WordNet") + Refresh button
- **Search card:** Text input (320px wide), Search button, Clear button, result-count limiter (number input, default 50)
- **Result list:** Rendered inline below the search bar; each matching lemma shows a "View Senses" and "Synsets" button
- **Modal:** A full-screen overlay (`position:fixed`) showing synset/sense detail. Scrollable, max 900px wide, max 90vh tall.

### Interaction Flow

1. User enters a lemma → `doSearch()` calls `wordnet_api.php?action=search`
2. Results render as lemma rows with two action buttons
3. "View Senses" → `loadLemma()` → calls `action=lemma` (POST) → renders sense cards in modal
4. "Open synset" from a sense card → `openSynset()` → calls `action=synset` → renders synset detail
5. "Show Hypernyms" → `loadHypernyms()` → calls `action=hypernyms` → appends hypernym list inline
6. "Raw" button → appends a formatted JSON `<pre>` block to the modal body

### Mobile / Responsive

- Search bar uses `display:flex` with `gap` — wraps naturally on narrow screens
- Modal uses `width:100%; max-width:900px` — suitable for mobile
- No explicit breakpoints defined; layout relies on flex wrapping. Mobile usability on narrow screens for the 320px input may need review `[VERIFY]`

### Error / State Handling

- DB not-initialized state: detected by checking for `"Table ... doesn''t exist"` in the `data.detail` field of the API response, even when HTTP status is 200. Renders an amber setup prompt.
- General errors: displayed inline in the results div in red text
- Toast notifications via `Toast.show()` if the Toast utility is available

---

## Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `wordnet_pyapi` (FastAPI, port 8009) | Runtime service | Must be running; all queries proxy through it |
| `wordnet` MariaDB database | Data store | Separate from main SAGE DB; must be populated via initial import |
| `view_wordnet_initial_import.php` | Related view | First-run import wizard; linked from setup prompt |
| `css/base.css`, `css/toast.css` | UI | Standard Forge UI stylesheets |
| `SpwBase` / `$spw->renderLayout()` | Core | Standard SAGE layout renderer |
| `src/Service/WordnetApi.php` | Service | PHP cURL wrapper for PyAPI |
| `App\Wordnet\WordnetBridge` | Service | Used by `wordnet_proxy.php` — source not included `[VERIFY]` |

---

## Known State / Notes

- **`morph` action** is implemented in `WordnetApi.php` and `wordnet_api.php` but has no corresponding UI control in `view_wordnet_admin.php`. It may be intended for programmatic use by other modules (e.g. Fuzz Forge or Scene Kitchen for lemmatisation). `[VERIFY]`
- **Dual proxy pattern** (`wordnet_api.php` vs `wordnet_proxy.php`) suggests the proxy was an earlier or parallel implementation. Whether both are actively used or one is deprecated is unclear. `[VERIFY]`
- **`WordnetBridge` class** (`App\Wordnet\WordnetBridge`) is referenced in `wordnet_proxy.php` but was not included in the source dump. Its implementation may differ from `WordnetApi.php`. `[VERIFY]`
- **Initial import flow** (`view_wordnet_initial_import.php`) is referenced but not included in this dump — presumably handles the one-time bulk load of the Princeton WordNet SQL data.
- **No ChromaDB / vector interaction** — this module is purely relational/lexical.
- **No write operations** to any database from the PHP/JS layer — read-only reference tool.
