*SAGE 2.0 Module Documentation*

---

## 1. Introduction

The Scheduler Log Viewer is a lightweight, real-time log monitoring tool within SAGE that streams the output of bash worker scripts directly to the browser. It scans the server-side `logs/` directory for `.log` files, presents them in a dropdown selector sorted by modification time, and polls the selected file every two seconds via a companion fetch endpoint. The viewer is intentionally minimal — monospace terminal aesthetic, no Forge UI dependency — making it a fast utility page for checking generation worker output, diagnosing failures, and confirming that scheduled cron jobs are running as expected.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

Provides live tail-style visibility into the output logs written by SAGE''s bash workers (e.g. `genworker_queue.sh`, `genvideo_queue.sh`) without requiring SSH access. Sits outside the main Forge UI design system; intended as a utility panel rather than a production interface.

**Inputs:** `.log` files in `{PROJECT_ROOT}/logs/`, served via `scheduler_log_fetch.php`.

**Outputs:** Read-only display. No writes to any database or filesystem.

---

### Key Features

#### File Selector
On page load, PHP scans the `logs/` directory for files matching `*.log` (case-insensitive), excluding any file with `err` in the name. Files are sorted by modification time descending so the most recently written log is pre-selected. The selector is a plain `<select>` that triggers an immediate fetch and scroll-reset on change, resuming auto-refresh if it was paused.

#### Auto-Polling
`fetchLog()` is called once on load and then on a 2-second `setInterval`. Each call fetches `scheduler_log_fetch.php?file={filename}` and sets `logDiv.textContent` to the response. The filename is URL-encoded to handle paths with spaces or special characters.

#### Smart Auto-Scroll
Before each content update, the viewer checks whether the user''s scroll position is within 5px of the bottom of the log div. If yes, the view auto-scrolls to the new bottom after the update. If the user has scrolled up to review earlier output, the position is preserved. Auto-scroll only applies when auto-refresh is active.

#### Pause / Resume Toggle
A `❚❚` / `▶` button toggles `autoRefresh`. When paused, `setInterval` continues to fire but the fetch still runs — content updates while paused, but auto-scroll is suppressed. [VERIFY — the pause button toggles the `autoRefresh` flag which gates auto-scroll, but `fetchLog()` itself does not check the flag before fetching, so polling continues regardless of pause state.]

---

### Data Model

No database interaction. Reads directly from the filesystem via PHP''s `scandir()` and `filemtime()`.

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `{PROJECT_ROOT}/logs/*.log` | Worker output log files. Excludes files containing `err` in the filename. |

The companion script `scheduler_log_fetch.php` (not included in this dump) is responsible for safely reading and returning the file contents. [VERIFY — confirm that `scheduler_log_fetch.php` applies path sanitisation to prevent directory traversal, e.g. validating that the resolved path stays within the `logs/` directory.]

---

### API / Backend Integration

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `scheduler_log_fetch.php?file={filename}` | GET | Returns raw log file content as plain text. Called by the frontend every 2 seconds. |

No calls to the PyAPI or any external services.

---

### UI & Interaction

Intentionally outside the Forge UI design system. Uses a hardcoded dark terminal aesthetic:

- Background `#111`, text `#0f0` (green-on-black terminal style)
- Fixed-height (`420px`) scrollable log div with `white-space: pre-wrap`
- Monospace font throughout
- No theming, no `localStorage` theme switching

The dashboard home link uses a plain emoji icon (`🗃`) rather than the standard Forge home button component.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Notes |
|------------|-------|
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Session bootstrap. No explicit auth redirect visible in this file — [VERIFY whether `bootstrap.php` handles the redirect or if this page is unguarded.] |
| `scheduler_log_fetch.php` | Companion file server for log content. Not included in source dump. |
| `genworker_queue.sh` / `genvideo_queue.sh` | Primary producers of the `.log` files displayed here. |
| `/dashboard.php` | Home navigation target. |

---

### Known State / Notes

- There is a commented-out alternative `fetchLog()` implementation preserved in the source. The active version fetches unconditionally (ignoring the `autoRefresh` flag); the commented version gated fetching on `autoRefresh`. The current behaviour means the log content always updates — only auto-scroll is suppressed when paused. [VERIFY — confirm this is intentional.]
- The `err` exclusion filter (`stripos($f, ''err'') === false`) hides error logs from the selector. These files exist in `logs/` but are not accessible via this UI. A separate viewer or direct file access would be needed to inspect them.
- No pagination or line-limit on the fetched log content. For very large or long-running log files, this could result in large payloads on every 2-second poll. [VERIFY — confirm `scheduler_log_fetch.php` applies a tail limit, e.g. last N lines or last N bytes.]
- The `position: absolute; right: 0` on the toggle button control div is not offset-aware and may overlap the file selector on narrow viewports.
