**File:** `public/todo.php`
**Convention:** `sage_module_todo.md`

---

## 1. Introduction Paragraph

The SAGE TODO Dashboard is an internal task management board purpose-built for tracking active development work across the SAGE platform itself. It provides a lightweight, priority-ordered ticketing surface for the sole developer — capturing everything from immediate production blockers to low-priority enhancement ideas — without depending on any external project management tooling. Tasks are stored in the SAGE database, sorted and filtered by a numeric priority order system, and can be reorganised in real time via drag-and-drop. An optional AI analysis layer, backed by a configurable LLM model selector, can suggest automated priority reordering, making the board self-reflective as the platform evolves.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The TODO Dashboard serves as SAGE''s internal developer backlog — a lightweight self-hosted issue tracker embedded directly in the platform. It is not part of the animated series production pipeline itself; rather, it tracks the ongoing development of SAGE as a product.

**Inputs:** Tasks are entered manually via the create/edit modal, or pre-existing records in `sage_todos` are loaded at page initialisation.

**Outputs:** Persisted `sage_todos` records with updated `order`, `status`, `name`, and `description` fields; drag-and-drop reorder commits via a batch SQL update.

---

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Task CRUD | Full create, read, update, delete via AJAX (no full-page reload) |
| Priority Order System | Numeric `order` field maps to four priority tiers: Immediate (1–10), High (11–25), Medium (26–50), Low (51+) |
| Drag-and-Drop Reorder | SortableJS-based reorder mode, toggled on/off; batch-saves new order values to DB |
| Priority & Area Filters | Filter buttons for priority tier; area filter (hidden by default in current build) |
| Search | Live client-side text search against task name and description |
| AI Analysis | Calls a separate `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php` endpoint to request LLM-powered priority suggestions; user can selectively apply or reject individual suggestions |
| Model Selector | Dropdown populated dynamically from `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php`; allows choosing which LLM model runs the analysis |
| Regen Indicator | Tasks with `regenerate_images > 0` display a `REGEN` badge |
| Stats Bar | Live count of tasks per priority tier, updated after every mutation |
| Toast Notifications | Slide-in toast for success and error feedback |
| Theme Toggle | Respects `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` via `theme-manager.js`; standard Forge UI dark/light pattern |
| URL Preload | If `?id=N` is passed in the query string, the edit modal opens automatically for that task on page load |

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Table: `sage_todos`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | INT (PK) | Auto-increment |
| `name` | VARCHAR | Task title (required) |
| `description` | TEXT | Optional extended detail |
| `order` | INT | Numeric sort order; drives priority tier classification |
| `status` | ENUM | `pending`, `in_progress`, `completed`, `cancelled` |
| `regenerate_images` | INT | Flag indicating image regeneration is pending; `> 0` shows REGEN badge |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | Set on insert |
| `updated_at` | DATETIME | Updated on every mutation |

**No ChromaDB / vector store interaction.** This module is purely relational.

---

### API / Backend Integration

The main `todo.php` handles all core CRUD actions itself via AJAX POST (same-file self-post). A secondary file, `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php`, handles the AI layer:

| Endpoint / Target | Action | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `todo.php` (self) | `create`, `update`, `delete`, `bulk_reorder`, `get_stats` | AJAX POST, `X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest` header gating |
| `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php` | `analyze_tasks`, `apply_suggestions`, `get_models` | Separate file; external LLM call details not visible in this source [VERIFY which AI provider is used] |

The `analyze_tasks` action returns an `analysis` string and an array of `suggestions` (each with `id`, `current_order`, `new_order`, `reason`). `apply_suggestions` accepts a JSON-encoded array of selected suggestions and commits them to the database.

---

### UI & Interaction

**Layout:**
- Single-column dashboard card
- Fixed header row with title, theme toggle, model selector, and action buttons (AI Analyse, New Task, Drag mode toggle, Save Order)
- Filter bar (priority tier buttons; area filter group is rendered but hidden via `display:none` in current build)
- Live search input
- Masonry/grid card list (`#taskGrid`) rendered by PHP on initial load, then mutated in-place by JavaScript
- Stats bar (5 stat cards: Immediate / High / Medium / Low / Total) at the bottom
- Timestamp display (`Last updated: …`)

**Task Cards:**
- Colour-coded by priority tier (CSS class on `.task-card`)
- Drag handle (`⋮⋮`) visible in sort mode
- Edit (✏️) and Delete (🗑️) action buttons
- Description truncated to 200 characters with ellipsis
- Badges: priority tier, auto-guessed area, order value

**Area Auto-Detection:**
The `guessArea()` function (mirrored in both PHP and JS) classifies tasks by keyword matching against name + description. Categories: `UI`, `Gallery`, `Generation`, `Models`, `Pose/Skeleton`, `DB`, `Scheduler`, `GearMenu`, `Workflow`, `Bugs`, `Assets`, `Integrations`, `General`.

**Modal:**
- Single shared modal (`#taskModal`) for both create and edit
- Fields: Task Name (required), Description, Priority Order (number), Status (select)
- Closes on backdrop click or Escape key

**Mobile / Responsive:**
- Uses base Forge UI stylesheet (`/css/base.css`, `/css/todo.css`)
- Mobile-first layout consistent with SAGE platform standards

**Real-time patterns:**
- All mutations (create, update, delete, reorder) are AJAX with no page reload
- New/updated cards are inserted in correct order position client-side (`insertTaskInOrder()`)
- `updateStats()` fires an additional AJAX call after each mutation to refresh the stats bar

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bootstrap.php` | PHP include | Core SAGE bootstrap (PDO, config) |
| `env_locals.php` | PHP include | Local environment variables |
| `SortableJS` | JS library | Drag-and-drop; loaded from CDN or `/vendor/sortable/` depending on `CDN_USAGE` flag |
| jQuery | JS library | AJAX and DOM utilities; loaded via `SpwBase::getJquery()` |
| `/css/base.css` | Stylesheet | Forge UI base styles |
| `/css/todo.css` | Stylesheet | Module-specific styles |
| `/js/theme-manager.js` | JS | Forge UI dark/light theme toggle |
| `/js/sage-home-button.js` | JS | Injects home button pointing to `/dashboard.php` |
| `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php` | PHP (sibling file) | Handles AI analysis and model listing [VERIFY — file not included in this dump] |

The TODO Dashboard is a standalone utility module; no other SAGE production modules feed into it or depend on it. It is accessed from the main SAGE dashboard.

---

### Known State / Notes

- The **area filter group** is rendered in the HTML but hidden (`display:none`). It is not actively exposed to the user in the current build. [VERIFY — intentional or pending re-enable]
- The `.ai-controls` div (containing a duplicate "Analyze All Tasks" button) is also hidden (`display:none`) — likely a legacy block superseded by the header-row AI button.
- A duplicate `id="analyzeBtn"` exists in the HTML (one in the header, one in the hidden `.ai-controls` div). The `showLoading()` / `hideLoading()` functions target `analyzeBtn` by ID — this should affect only the first match in the DOM. [VERIFY — confirm no functional side effects]
- `todo_prioritizer_ajax.php` is referenced by JS but not included in the source dump. Its internal logic, AI provider, and model list source are unverified from this file alone. [VERIFY]
- The `regenerate_images` column is read and displayed but not written or edited from within this UI — management of that flag presumably occurs elsewhere in the SAGE pipeline. [VERIFY]
