INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('544', 'mod_sketches', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: Sketches
`sage_module_sketches.md`

---

## 1. Introduction Paragraph

The Sketches module is SAGE''s primary interface for managing and reviewing AI-generated concept sketches — the raw visual ideation layer of *The Anima Chronicles* production pipeline. It exposes three tightly integrated views for every sketch entity: a CRUD manager for direct record editing and scheduler control, a modular paginated gallery for visual browsing with PhotoSwipe lightbox support, and a Map Runs explorer that groups generated frames by batch run for iterative review and curation. Together these views cover the full lifecycle from prompt authoring through image generation, metadata enrichment, and narrative analysis, making the Sketches module the canonical entry point for visual concept development in SAGE.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Sketches module manages entities in the `sketches` table — prompt-driven visual concepts that feed into SAGE''s AI image generation pipeline. Each sketch record carries a description/prompt, optional img2img and ControlNet map references, a regeneration flag, and links to active map runs (batches of generated frames). The module sits at the **ideation layer** of the pipeline: upstream from scene composition and downstream from lore/narrative planning.

The three views serve distinct roles:

| View File | Role |
|---|---|
| `sql_crud_sketches.php` | Create, edit, delete, copy, reorder sketch records; trigger scheduler |
| `gallery_sketches_nu.php` | Browse generated frames as a visual grid/slideshow gallery |
| `view_map_runs_sketches.php` | Inspect batch generation runs, frame chains, ingredient metadata, curation scores |

---

### Key Features

#### CRUD View (`sql_crud_sketches.php`)

- **Auto-discovered schema** — PHP introspects `SHOW COLUMNS FROM sketches` at runtime to determine which optional features are active (ordering, regeneration flag, img2img, ControlNet map references, active map run selector).
- **Paginated table via Swiper** — Records are loaded page-by-page into a Swiper carousel. Each page is fetched via `$.post` AJAX on slide change.
- **Inline editing** — `contenteditable` cells for `name`, `description`, `prompt_negative`; changes POST on `blur`.
- **Regeneration checkbox** — Sets `regenerate_images = 1` on the sketch record to flag it for the next scheduler pass.
- **Map run selector** — Per-row `<select>` dropdown loads recent map runs from `v_map_runs_sketches` and posts `setActiveMapRun` to set `active_map_run_id`.
- **Add / Copy / Delete** — Standard CRUD actions; copy duplicates all non-`id` columns with ` (Copy)` appended to name.
- **Drag-to-reorder** — jQuery UI Sortable on the `order` column; triggered via a toggle button.
- **Bulk reorder** — ASC/DESC bulk re-sort via `/order_recalc.php`.
- **Scheduler trigger** — 🌀 button POSTs `run_now` to `scheduler_view.php` using `$entitySchedulerIds[''sketches''] = 15`.
- **Prompt Matrix link** — ✺ button navigates to `view_prompt_matrix.php?entity_type=sketches&entity_id=…`.
- **Frame Details modal** — 🕸️ button calls `window.showEntityFormInModal(''sketches'', id)`.
- **Thumbnail gallery** — img2img and ControlNet map thumbnails render inline with PhotoSwipe lightbox; double-click removes the reference (`remove_image` action).
- **Icon routing** — For `sketches`, the entity icon links to `view_map_runs_sketches.php` rather than the standard gallery (special-cased in the template).
- **Mobile card view** — Responsive CSS collapses the table into card layout below 768 px; rows are collapsible with a toggle button.

#### Gallery View (`gallery_sketches_nu.php` + `SketchesNuGallery.php`)

Built on `AbstractNuGallery`, which provides:

- **Swiper-based pagination** — Pages load lazily via AJAX (`ajax_gallery=1`) as the user swipes.
- **PhotoSwipe lightbox** — Full-screen image viewer with optional gear menu (⚙️) and frame details button (🎯).
- **Grid / Pic toggle** — Switch between masonry-style grid and single-image view without a page reload.
- **Filter bar** — Absolute-positioned `<select>` dropdowns rendered from `filterOptions`; form submits on `change`.
- **GearMenu module** — Standard actions injected via `ModuleRegistry`; attaches to loaded slides.
- **ImageEditor module** — Mask, crop, transform, and filter tabs available per frame.
- **Frame Details modal** — `modal_frame_details.php` included for in-lightbox frame inspection.
- **Full-text caption modal** — 📖 button exposes full prompt text without truncation.

`SketchesNuGallery` specialisation:

- **Map Run filter** — Dropdown populated from `map_runs WHERE entity_type = ''sketches'' ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 50`. Display format: `{id}: {note truncated to 20 chars} (MM-DD HH:mm)`.
- **WHERE clause** — Extracts the integer run ID from the formatted string and filters `v_gallery_sketches` by `map_run_id`.
- **Caption fields** — Entity ID, Map Run, Frame ID, Name, Description, Style.
- **Order** — `frame_id DESC`.
- **Toggle button left offset** — 220 px (accommodates the wider map run dropdown).

#### Map Runs View (`view_map_runs_sketches.php`)

- **Run listing** — Paginates `map_runs WHERE entity_type = ''sketches''` at 5 runs per page.
- **Search** — Filters by run ID, note text, or frame prompt/name via a correlated subquery on `frames`.
- **Frame chain Swiper** — Each run renders its frames as a horizontally scrollable card carousel (`slidesPerView: ''auto''`, free-mode).
- **Chain cards** — Thumbnail, frame ID, entity type/ID badge, generation method badge (Original / Img2Img / Edit), ingredient pill, and curation analysis pill.
- **Ingredient modal** — Clicking the "Ingredients (n)" pill opens a modal listing all `sketch_ingredients` rows for that sketch, normalised across both the new flexible ingredient system and legacy `meta_sketches` data. Generator config titles are resolved via a secondary query.
- **Curation modal** — Clicking the "🕵️ Analysis (score)" pill opens a detailed breakdown from `sketch_analysis`: overall quality score, classification (narrative function, emotional tone), primary themes (rendered as pills), character/artifact entities, potential use recommendation, and a 4-axis score breakdown (narrative completeness, visual impact, production readiness, visual distinctiveness).
- **Note editing** — Inline `<input>` per run POSTs `update_note` on `change`; a ✔ save indicator fades in/out.
- **Regenerate run** — 🔄 button POSTs `regenerate_run`; finds all `entity_id` values from `frames WHERE map_run_id = … AND entity_type = ''sketches''` and sets `regenerate_images = 1` on each.
- **Scroll Magic link** — Each run header links to `view_scrollmagic_map_run.php?map_run_id=…` in a new tab.
- **Page input** — Direct numeric page jump input in the pagination bar.
- **GearMenu + ImageEditor** — Standard modules attached to the `.container` element.
- **PhotoSwipe** — Loaded as ES module from CDN; initialised over `.pswp-gallery` wrapping all runs.

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Tables

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `sketches` | Core entity — prompts, flags, img2img/cnmap references, active map run |
| `frames` | Generated images linked to sketches via `entity_type = ''sketches''` and `entity_id` |
| `map_runs` | Batch generation run records; `entity_type = ''sketches''` scopes them to this module |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Junction table linking frames to sketches (FK to `sketches.id` with cascade delete) |

#### Supporting Tables (Map Runs view)

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `sketch_ingredients` | Flexible prompt ingredient records per sketch; `ingredient_type`, `source_id`, `prompt_fragment`, `snapshot_data` |
| `meta_sketches` | Legacy metadata — links to `generator_config`, `sketch_templates`, `interactions` |
| `sketch_analysis` | Curation scores: `overall_quality`, `classification`, `scoring`, `entities`, `thematics`, `recommendations` (JSON columns) |
| `generator_config` | Generator configuration records; title resolved for ingredient display |
| `sketch_templates` | Template definitions: `core_idea`, `shot_type`, `camera_angle`, `perspective` |
| `interactions` | Named interaction records |
| `image_edits` | Edit history for derived frames |

#### Key `sketches` Columns

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | int PK | Auto-increment |
| `name` | varchar(100) | Unique |
| `order` | int | Display sort order |
| `description` | text | Prompt / raw scene text |
| `description_raw` | text | Pre-continuity original prompt |
| `prompt_negative` | text | Negative prompt |
| `regenerate_images` | tinyint | 1 = queue for regeneration |
| `active_map_run_id` | int | Currently active batch run |
| `img2img_frame_id` | int | Source frame for img2img |
| `cnmap_frame_id` | int | Source frame for ControlNet map |

#### Gallery View

Reads from `v_gallery_sketches` — a database view that joins `frames` with sketch metadata and exposes `map_run_id` for filtering. `[VERIFY: exact view definition not included in dump]`

#### Map Run View

Also reads from `v_map_runs_sketches` (used in the CRUD map run select fallback). `[VERIFY: exact view definition not included in dump]`

---

### API / Backend Integration

| Integration | Detail |
|---|---|
| Scheduler | `scheduler_view.php` — `run_now` action, scheduler ID `15` |
| Order recalc | `/order_recalc.php?ajax=1` — bulk ASC/DESC reorder |
| Prompt Matrix | `view_prompt_matrix.php?entity_type=sketches&entity_id=…` — navigation link |
| Scroll Magic | `view_scrollmagic_map_run.php?map_run_id=…` — external tab link |
| Frame Details | `modal_frame_details.php` — included PHP partial; `showFrameDetailsModal(frameId)` JS |
| Entity Form Modal | `window.showEntityFormInModal(''sketches'', id)` — global JS function |

No direct PyAPI (FastAPI) calls are made from these views. AI generation is triggered via the scheduler.

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Design System

All three views follow the Forge UI system:
- Theme via `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` → `data-theme` on `<html>`
- Base styles from `/css/base.css` (CSS custom properties: `--bg`, `--card`, `--accent`, `--border`, `--text`, `--text-muted`)
- Toast notifications via `/css/toast.css` + `/js/toast.js`
- Home button via `/js/sage-home-button.js` pointing to `/dashboard.php`
- `forge_tool.php` floatool included in all views

#### CRUD View

- Mobile-first card collapse below 768 px; `data-label` attrs drive `::before` pseudo-content labels
- Swiper `autoHeight` accommodates variable row counts per page
- PhotoSwipe for thumbnail lightbox; `appendToEl: document.body` to avoid z-index stacking issues
- `100% / max-width: 100%` on `html, body` prevents layout explosion when modals open
- PhotoSwipe patched to use `width: 100%` / `height: 100%` (not `vw/vh`) to avoid scrollbar-induced width miscalculation on tablets

#### Gallery View

- Mobile-first; toggle button position configured per entity subclass (220 px for sketches)
- Swiper horizontal swipe between pages; lazy AJAX load on `slideChange`
- Filter `<select>` elements absolutely positioned at configurable `left` offsets
- GearMenu attaches to each loaded slide after AJAX injection
- `forge_tool.php` floatool rendered via `showFloatool()` (returns `true` by default)

#### Map Runs View

- Viewport scale `0.7` set in meta tag for mobile density
- Bootstrap Icons CDN for run header action icons
- Per-run Swiper: `slidesPerView: ''auto''`, `freeMode: true`, scrollbar + nav arrows
- Three modal overlays: Ingredients, Curation Analysis, Full Description
- Save indicator (✔) per run note input using `opacity` transition
- Gear Menu attached to `.container` after DOM ready

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Module / File | Relationship |
|---|---|
| `AbstractNuGallery` | Base class for `SketchesNuGallery`; provides Swiper pagination, PhotoSwipe, AJAX loading, filter rendering |
| `GearMenuModule` | Injected into gallery and map runs views via `ModuleRegistry`; standard actions per entity |
| `ImageEditorModule` | Injected into gallery and map runs views; mask/crop/filter editing |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | Included in all three views; provides frame detail inspection overlay |
| `forge_tool.php` | Floatool included in all views |
| `view_scrollmagic_map_run.php` | Linked from map runs view header per run |
| `view_prompt_matrix.php` | Linked from CRUD view per row |
| `scheduler_view.php` | Scheduler trigger endpoint |
| `ajax_gallery.php` | Default AJAX endpoint for `AbstractNuGallery` page loads (can be overridden) |
| `Scene Kitchen` | Downstream consumer of sketches as scene composition ingredients `[VERIFY]` |
| `Enhanimaticism` | Likely consumes sketch frames for frame review `[VERIFY]` |
| `Fuzz Forge` | May ingest sketch descriptions for lore clustering `[VERIFY]` |

---

### Known State / Notes

- **Sketches icon routing** — `sql_crud_sketches.php` contains a special-case `if ($entity == "sketches")` block that points the entity icon to `view_map_runs_sketches.php` rather than the standard `gallery_*_nu.php`. This is the only entity in the shared CRUD template with this override.
- **`frames_2_sketches` junction table** — Present in the schema but not queried in any of the three view files included in this dump. Its role in the pipeline (possibly for multi-sketch frame association) is `[VERIFY]`.
- **`v_gallery_sketches` view** — Referenced in `SketchesNuGallery::getBaseQuery()` and `fetchDistinct()` but its definition was not included in the dump. It must expose at minimum: `filename`, `prompt`, `entity_id`, `frame_id`, `map_run_id`, `name`, `description`, `style`. `[VERIFY]`
- **`v_map_runs_sketches` view** — Referenced as a fallback in the CRUD `fetchMapRuns` action. Definition not in dump. `[VERIFY]`
- **Ingredient normalisation** — The `getFramesForRun()` helper in `view_map_runs_sketches.php` uses `array_values(array_unique(...))` with an explicit comment noting that `array_unique` preserves keys and must be re-indexed to avoid gaps in `array_fill` placeholder generation. This was a fixed bug.
- **PhotoSwipe tablet fix** — Both CRUD and gallery views explicitly override PhotoSwipe''s default `100vw/100vh` sizing to `100%/100%` to prevent scrollbar-induced layout expansion on Android/tablet viewports.
- **`sketch_analysis` curation data** — Populated by a separate analysis pipeline (not shown in this dump). The map runs view gracefully hides the curation pill when `classification` is empty.
- **Legacy meta vs. flexible ingredients** — `getFramesForRun()` supports both the old `meta_sketches` join path and the new `sketch_ingredients` flexible system, preferring the new system when records exist.
- **`view_map_runs_sketches.php` viewport scale** — Set to `0.7` via `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=0.7">`. This differs from the standard `1.0` used across other SAGE views and may be intentional for the dense card layout on mobile. `[VERIFY]`
- **Toast in map runs view** — `toast.css` and `toast.js` are included at the bottom of the file (after `forge_tool.php`) rather than in `<head>`. Functional but inconsistent with other views.
