INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('543', 'mod_sketches_viewer', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: Semantic Sketch Viewer & Sketch Match

**Files:** `public/sketches_viewer.php` · `public/sketches_viewer_api.php` · `public/sketch_match.php` · `src/Core/PyApiVectorService.php`

---

## 1. Introduction Paragraph

The Semantic Sketch Viewer and Sketch Match module is SAGE''s visual asset discovery and lore-bridging system, providing two complementary interfaces for exploring the `sketches` entity and its linked `frames`. The Sketch Viewer (`sketches_viewer.php`) delivers a browsable gallery of all sketch groups with their associated frame chains, and exposes both text-based semantic search (via MiniLM embeddings in ChromaDB) and image-upload-based visual similarity search (via CLIP Vision), allowing the production team to locate concept imagery by description or by example photograph. Sketch Match (`sketch_match.php`) extends this further by using a selected sketch''s semantic metadata as a live vector query against any registered ChromaDB lore collection, surfacing narrative documents, character profiles, or location entries that are thematically resonant with a given visual asset — effectively closing the loop between visual pre-production and the lore knowledge graph. Together, these views form the semantic retrieval layer of the SAGE image pipeline, sitting downstream of frame generation and upstream of scene composition and knowledge graph enrichment.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

| View | Primary Function |
|---|---|
| `sketches_viewer.php` | Browse, search, and inspect all sketches and their linked frames |
| `sketch_match.php` | Select a sketch and find semantically related lore/knowledge documents |

**Pipeline position:** Post-generation (frames exist) → Semantic review → Lore linkage → Scene Kitchen / Knowledge Graph enrichment.

**Inputs:**
- Text query string (natural language description)
- Uploaded image file (for CLIP visual similarity)
- Sketch selection (for Sketch Match lore query)

**Outputs:**
- Ranked list of matching sketch groups with frame carousels
- Lore match cards with similarity scores and document references

---

### Key Features

#### Sketches Viewer (`sketches_viewer.php`)

**Sticky Search Header**
- Text input with 500ms debounce triggers semantic vector search against the `sage_sketches_nu` ChromaDB collection using MiniLM embeddings.
- Image upload button (📷) accepts any image file; visual similarity search runs against the `sage_nu_images` collection using CLIP Vision. Uploaded image is previewed inline in the search bar with a clear button.
- Reset button clears both text and image query state simultaneously.

**Sketch Gallery Cards**
Each sketch renders as a `.gallery-container` block containing:
- Header with sketch name, ID, quality score badge (colour-coded: green ≥8, amber ≥5, red <5), narrative function pill, and thematic tag pills (up to 3).
- Description excerpt (150 chars) that opens a full-text modal on click.
- Swiper.js horizontal frame carousel — up to 10 frames per sketch, each as a tappable card with thumbnail, frame ID, and truncated prompt. Cards open full-size in a PhotoSwipe lightbox.
- Similarity distance score displayed on each frame card when in vector search mode (`Sim: 0.XX`).

**Gear Menu Integration**
Both `sketches` and `frames` entities are registered with `ModuleRegistry` gear menus, enabling standard entity actions (edit, delete, link) directly from sketch headers and frame cards.

**Pagination**
Load-more pattern: 10 items per page, appended on scroll via "Load More" button. Button label adapts (`Load More Matches` vs `Load More Sketches`) based on active mode.

---

#### Sketch Match (`sketch_match.php`)

**Sticky Sketch Carousel Header**
- Horizontal Swiper gallery of all sketches (paginated, 20 per page [VERIFY]), with thumbnail, name, and ID.
- Text filter input with 400ms debounce for filtering by sketch name or ID.
- Pagination control with direct page-number input field (Enter or `onchange` triggers `jumpToPage()`), previous/next buttons, and dynamic total-page label.

**Sketch Selection**
- Clicking a sketch card marks it `.selected` (pink/red highlight with scale transform) and stores the sketch data in `activeSketchData`.
- Active query display bar shows the selected sketch name and ID.
- "👁️ View Sketch" button appears after selection and opens the sketch''s `entity_form.php` in a full-screen iframe modal.

**Lore Search**
- Uses `activeSketchData.vector_text` (the sketch''s semantic metadata string [VERIFY: field name]) as the query text.
- Posts to `sketch_match_api.php` with `action: search_lore` against the selected ChromaDB text collection.
- Collection dropdown populated from `chroma_collections` table filtered to `type=''text''`.
- Results rendered as a responsive grid of `.hit-card` elements colour-coded by match type: character (blue), episode (purple), location (amber), overview (green).
- Each hit card shows: entity type, similarity percentage, entity name, source document title and category, and a text snippet.
- Clicking a hit opens `view_curated_docs.php` in a full-screen iframe modal with `focus_type` and `focus_entity` URL params for contextual highlighting.

**TTS (Text-to-Speech)**
- "🔊 Speak selection" button in the lore document modal reads selected text (or `.marked` elements) from the embedded iframe.
- Uses `postMessage` cross-frame communication to retrieve the iframe selection when direct `getSelection()` access is blocked.
- Calls `api_tts_inline.php` with model `en_US-libritts_r-medium`; streams audio via a hidden `<audio>` element.
- Status indicator shows "Generating audio…" / "Playing…" states. Stop button halts playback.

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Tables

| Table | Usage |
|---|---|
| `sketches` | Core entity — `id`, `name`, `description`, `created_at` |
| `sketch_analysis` | Quality and classification data — `overall_quality`, `classification` (JSON), `thematics` (JSON) |
| `frames` | Individual generated frames — `id`, `filename`, `prompt` |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Many-to-many join — `from_id` (frame), `to_id` (sketch) |
| `chroma_collections` | Registry of ChromaDB collections — `name`, `type`; used to populate the collection dropdown in Sketch Match |

#### `sketch_analysis` JSON Fields (parsed at runtime)

| JSON Key | Usage |
|---|---|
| `classification.narrative_function` | Displayed as purple pill on sketch card |
| `thematics.primary_themes` | Array of strings displayed as blue theme pills (max 3) |

#### `md_doc_analysis` (lore document metadata)

Referenced indirectly via `sketch_match_api.php` lore search results. Contains fields including `summary`, `entities`, `lore_points`, `production_assessment`, `thematics`, `narrative_utility`, `showrunner_analysis`, `series_bible`, `target_collection`, and `is_locked` (aggregator skip flag).

```sql
-- Aggregator skip flag
`is_locked` tinyint(1) DEFAULT 0 COMMENT ''If 1, the aggregator will skip this document to protect manual edits.''
```

#### ChromaDB Collections

| Collection | Modality | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `sage_sketches_nu` | Text (MiniLM) | Sketch metadata/descriptions — IDs formatted as `sketch_{id}_{type}_chunk_{n}` |
| `sage_nu_images` | Image (CLIP Vision) | Frame image embeddings — IDs formatted as `frame_{id}` |

---

### API / Backend Integration

#### `PyApiVectorService` (extends `PyApiProxy`)

Central PHP service class at `src/Core/PyApiVectorService.php`. Resolves the PyAPI base URL dynamically at runtime via `bash/pyapi_echo.sh`.

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `ping()` | `GET /ping` | Health check; expects `{"ok": true, "message": "pong"}` |
| `query()` | `POST /chroma/query` | Form-based multimodal query; routes to `queryJson()` if `$where` filter present |
| `queryJson()` | `POST /chroma/query_json` | JSON-body query; preferred for metadata-filtered (`$where`) text queries |
| `extractSketchIds()` | — | PHP-side: collapses chunked Chroma results to unique sketch IDs by reading `sketch_id` from returned metadata; falls back to ID string parsing |
| `cleanIds()` | — | Legacy ID normaliser; kept for non-chunked frame/image queries only |

**Chunking note:** Sketch text documents are stored in Chroma as multiple chunks (e.g. `sketch_2718_primary_chunk_0`). `extractSketchIds()` reads `sketch_id` from metadata rather than parsing the chunk ID, and collapses all chunks to a single entry keeping the best (lowest) distance. `cleanIds()` is unreliable for chunked data and should not be used for sketch queries.

#### `PyApiProxy` Base Class

`src/Core/PyApiProxy.php` provides cURL transport methods:

| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `executeApiRequest()` | Form POST, no file |
| `executeApiRequestWithImage()` | Attaches single file as `file` field via `CURLFile` |
| `executeApiRequestWithImages()` | Multiple file fields |
| `executeApiRequestWithImageJson()` | Image upload + JSON decode |
| `executeGetRequest()` | GET request for health/info endpoints |

Timeouts: `CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT 60`, `CURLOPT_TIMEOUT 300` (standard); `2s`/`3s` for ping health checks.

#### `sketches_viewer_api.php`

Internal AJAX endpoint consumed exclusively by `sketches_viewer.php`.

| POST param | Values | Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| `action` | `fetch` | Fetch page of sketches with frames |
| `page` | integer | Pagination offset (`limit = 10`) |
| `search_mode` | `true` / `false` | Activates vector search path |
| `query` | string | Text for MiniLM search against `sage_sketches_nu` |
| `image` | file upload | Image for CLIP search against `sage_nu_images` |

**Search routing:**
- Image upload → searches `sage_nu_images` → maps returned frame IDs back to sketch IDs via `frames_2_sketches` → fetches ordered sketches.
- Text query → searches `sage_sketches_nu` → extracts sketch IDs from Chroma result IDs via regex.
- No query → standard `ORDER BY s.id DESC` browse.

Result ordering in vector search mode uses MySQL `FIELD(s.id, ...)` to preserve Chroma''s relevance ranking. Distance scores are passed through to frame cards as `f.distance`.

#### `sketch_match_api.php`

Separate backend for Sketch Match [VERIFY: file not included in dump; behaviour inferred from frontend calls].

| `action` | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `fetch_sketches` | Returns paginated sketch list with `thumb`, `name`, `id`, `vector_text` |
| `search_lore` | Takes `query` + optional `collection`; returns ranked lore hits with `doc_id`, `match_type`, `match_entity`, `title`, `category`, `snippet`, `relevance` |

---

### UI & Interaction

**Themes:** Both views apply SAGE Forge UI dark/light theming via `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` / `data-theme` attribute. Theme is set before page render via inline script to prevent flash.

**Mobile-first:** `viewport` uses `initial-scale=0.8`. All grids use `auto-fill` / `minmax` responsive columns. Swiper''s `slidesPerView: ''auto''` handles narrow screens.

**Key interaction patterns:**

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Debounced search | `setTimeout` 500ms (Viewer) / 400ms (Match) |
| Lazy image loading | `loading="lazy"` on all thumbnails |
| PhotoSwipe lightbox | ESM module import; re-initialised after each render batch via `initLightbox()` |
| Swiper carousels | Re-instantiated per `.frame-chain-swiper`; destroyed before re-render in Sketch Match |
| Gear menus | `window.GearMenu.attach()` called 100ms after each render via `setTimeout` |
| Modals | jQuery `.show()`/`.hide()` with `display:flex`; ESC key closes all modals |
| Toast notifications | `/js/toast.js` + `/css/toast.css` for error/warn/info states |
| Cross-frame TTS | `postMessage` for selection retrieval from sandboxed iframes |

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `PyApiVectorService` | Internal service | Vector search; requires PyAPI running on port from `pyapi_echo.sh` |
| ChromaDB | External vector store | Collections `sage_sketches_nu`, `sage_nu_images` |
| `ModuleRegistry` / `GearMenu` | UI module | Standard entity actions for `sketches` and `frames` |
| `ImageEditor` | UI module | Registered in Viewer; render injected into page |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | Partial | Frame detail modal markup |
| `entity_form.php` | Linked view | Loaded in Sketch Match''s "View Sketch" modal iframe |
| `view_curated_docs.php` | Linked view | Lore document viewer; loaded in doc modal iframe |
| `api_tts_inline.php` | Internal API | TTS audio generation endpoint |
| `sketch_match_api.php` | Internal API | Sketch/lore data backend for Sketch Match |
| Scene Kitchen | Downstream | Sketch assets feed scene ingredient selection |
| Knowledge Graph | Downstream | Lore match results can inform KG enrichment |
| Swiper.js v11 | CDN | Horizontal frame carousels |
| PhotoSwipe v5 | CDN | Full-screen image lightbox (ESM) |
| jQuery 3.7.1 | CDN | AJAX and DOM manipulation |

---

### Known State / Notes

- **`cleanIds()` deprecation:** Method is preserved for backward compatibility for frame/image queries but explicitly marked unsafe for sketch queries due to chunked document IDs. `extractSketchIds()` is the correct replacement.
- **`debugApiRequest()` logging:** cURL debug logging is commented out in `PyApiProxy`; method body is a no-op in production.
- **Sketch gear menu (Viewer):** The per-sketch header gear menu button is commented out in `sketches_viewer.php` (`<!-- <div style="display:none;" class="gear-menu-btn"...> -->`). Sketch-level entity actions via gear menu are not currently active; frame-level gear menus are active. `[VERIFY: intentional or in-progress?]`
- **`sketch_match_api.php` not included in dump:** The backend for Sketch Match was not provided. `vector_text` field name on sketch objects and the exact lore search implementation are inferred from frontend JS and flagged `[VERIFY]`.
- **`meta.total_pages` from `sketch_match_api.php`:** Frontend guards against missing `meta` gracefully (`totalSketchPages = Math.max(1, totalSketchPages)`), suggesting the field may not always be returned. `[VERIFY]`
- **Theme toggle button (Viewer):** `#themeToggle` button is rendered with `display:none` and never shown; theme is managed globally. Likely a legacy element.
- **`$COLL_IMAGES` / `$COLL_SKETCHES` constants:** Hardcoded in `sketches_viewer_api.php` as `sage_nu_images` and `sage_sketches_nu`. Any collection rename requires a code change.
- **`where` filter support:** `PyApiVectorService::query()` accepts a `$where` array for metadata filtering, routing to `queryJson()` automatically. This capability is not currently used by either viewer frontend but is available for future use.
