### Known State / Notes

- The `$entityIcons` and `$entitySchedulerIds` arrays in `entity_icons.php` serve as the canonical entity registry for icon display and scheduler ID lookup. However, registering an entity here is only one small step — a new entity type requires authoring its own `sql_crud_{entity}.php`, `gallery_{entity}_nu.php`, `{Entity}NuGallery.php`, `view_map_runs_{entity}.php`, database table, and `v_gallery_{entity}` view. The convention is well-established enough that new entities can be built quickly by following existing entity files as templates, but there is no code generation or auto-registration.
