**File:** `public/view_storyboards_chains.php`  
**Companion:** `public/view_frame_chain.php`  
**Version:** SAGE 2.0

---

## 1. Introduction

The Storyboards Chain View is SAGE''s visual continuity browser for assembled storyboards, presenting each storyboard''s frames as a horizontally scrollable card chain rather than a flat grid. It sits at the intersection of the image generation pipeline and the narrative sequencing layer, giving Sebastian a rapid way to review how frames flow together, inspect the generative provenance of each image, and surface AI curation analysis without leaving the overview. For each storyboard, the module surfaces ingredient metadata, sketch analysis scores, creation method badges, and inline description editing, making it the primary QA surface for storyboard sequences before they proceed to the Scroll Magic presentation view or the frame-by-frame storyboard editor.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

This module provides a paginated, searchable index of all storyboards in the production database, with each storyboard rendered as a horizontally scrollable Swiper.js card sequence. Each card represents one `storyboard_frames` entry, showing the rendered image, creation method, prompt ingredients, and AI curation data.

The companion file `view_frame_chain.php` handles a narrower use case: tracing the full **generation lineage** of a single frame backwards through its parent chain (img2img ancestors and image editor steps), displayed as its own standalone Swiper sequence.

**Inputs:**
- `GET ?page`, `GET ?search` — pagination and search controls
- `GET ?start_frame_id` (frame chain view only)

**Outputs:**
- Rendered HTML storyboard chain UI
- AJAX JSON responses for description updates and sketch regeneration flags

---

### Key Features

#### Storyboard Chain Browser (`view_storyboards_chains.php`)

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Paginated storyboard list | 5 storyboards per page, ordered by ID descending |
| Full-text search | Searches storyboard name, description, frame prompts, and `storyboard_frames` name/description fields; also matches numeric IDs exactly |
| Swiper card chains | Each storyboard renders as a horizontal Swiper.js carousel; cards are 300px wide with arrow connectors (`→`) between slides |
| Inline description editing | Each storyboard header includes an editable text input; changes POST via AJAX and display a transient save indicator |
| Sketch regeneration trigger | Per-storyboard ↺ button flags all linked `sketches` records (`regenerate_images = 1`) via AJAX POST |
| Creation method badges | Each frame card shows `Original` / `Img2Img` / `Image Edit` as colour-coded badges (grey / blue / orange) |
| Ingredients modal | Frames linked to `sketch_ingredients` rows show an "Ingredients (N)" purple badge; clicking opens a modal listing each ingredient type with icon, label, and truncated detail |
| Legacy meta fallback | If no `sketch_ingredients` rows exist, the module falls back to `meta_sketches` joins to populate ingredient display |
| Curation/Analysis modal | Frames with a `sketch_analysis` record show a 🕵️ badge with the overall quality score; clicking opens a detailed modal with tone, themes, character entities, score breakdown, and AI suggestion |
| Full description modal | Clicking a truncated prompt opens a monospace full-text modal |
| PhotoSwipe lightbox | Frame thumbnail images are wrapped in PhotoSwipe gallery links for full-screen zoom |
| Scroll Magic link | Per-storyboard icon links to `view_scrollmagic_multi_prm.php` (presentation view) |
| Storyboard editor link | Per-storyboard icon links to `view_storyboard.php?id=N` (frame editor) |
| Gear Menu integration | `ModuleRegistry` gear menu attached to `.container`, providing standard entity actions for all major entity types |

#### Frame Generation Chain (`view_frame_chain.php`)

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Recursive lineage query | Uses a `WITH RECURSIVE` CTE to walk backwards up the frame parent chain up to 20 levels deep |
| Unified parent resolution | `COALESCE` checks `frames.img2img_frame_id` first, then falls back to the `frames_chains` table for image editor steps |
| Creation method detection | Same badge logic as chain view: edit_tool → orange `Image Edit`; img2img_frame_id → blue `Img2Img`; else grey `Original` |
| Generative name display | If the frame''s `entity_type` is `generatives`, the generative name is shown as a blue badge in the card footer |
| PhotoSwipe lightbox | Gallery wrapping identical to the storyboard chain view |
| Modal view flag | Accepts `?view=modal` GET param (`$is_modal_view` set but not yet consumed in current render) `[VERIFY]` |

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Tables

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `storyboards` | Top-level storyboard records; holds `name`, `description`, `created_at` |
| `storyboard_frames` | Join table linking storyboards to frames; holds `frame_id`, `name`, `description`, `filename`, `sort_order` |
| `frames` | Core image record; holds `filename`, `prompt`, `entity_type`, `entity_id`, `img2img_frame_id`, `cnmap`, `model`, `seed`, `rating` |
| `sketches` | Scene-level AI generation config; holds `description`, `regenerate_images` flag, `img2img`/`cnmap` fields |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Many-to-many join between frames and sketches (`from_id` → `frames.id`, `to_id` → `sketches.id`) |

#### Supporting Tables (joined in `getFramesForStoryboard`)

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `generatives` | Source entity for frames where `entity_type = ''generatives''` |
| `image_edits` | Records image editor operations; `derived_frame_id` links to the output frame; provides `tool` and `note` |
| `meta_sketches` | Legacy sketch metadata; joins via `sketch_id` |
| `generator_config` | Generator preset records; referenced from `meta_sketches.desc_gen_config_id` and `sketch_ingredients.source_id` |
| `sketch_templates` | Template presets; provides `name`, `core_idea`, `shot_type`, `camera_angle`, `perspective` |
| `interactions` | Interaction presets for legacy meta |
| `sketch_ingredients` | Flexible ingredient system; each row is a typed prompt fragment linked to a sketch via `sketch_id`; types include `generator_config_desc`, `generator_config_name`, character, location, style, template, interaction, anivoc, etc. |
| `sketch_analysis` | AI curation records; holds `overall_quality`, `classification`, `scoring`, `entities`, `thematics`, `recommendations` as JSON columns |
| `frames_chains` | Newer parent-tracking table for image editor lineage; `frame_id` → `parent_frame_id` |

#### `frames` Schema (abbreviated)

```sql
frames.id                   -- PK
frames.filename             -- Relative image path
frames.prompt               -- Generation prompt
frames.entity_type          -- ''sketches'' | ''generatives'' | etc.
frames.entity_id            -- FK to entity table
frames.img2img_frame_id     -- Legacy parent frame reference
frames.cnmap_frame_id       -- ControlNet map frame reference
frames.rating               -- Unsigned tinyint quality flag
```

#### `sketches` Schema (abbreviated)

```sql
sketches.regenerate_images  -- 1 = queued for regeneration
sketches.img2img            -- img2img mode flag
sketches.depth2img          -- depth2img mode flag
sketches.cnmap              -- ControlNet map mode flag
```

---

### API / Backend Integration

This module is **PHP-only with no PyAPI calls**. All data operations are direct MariaDB queries via PDO.

#### AJAX Endpoints (self-POSTing to the same file)

| `action` param | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `regenerate_storyboard` | POST | Finds all `sketches.id` values linked to frames in the given storyboard; sets `sketches.regenerate_images = 1` for all. Returns `{success, count}`. |
| `update_description` | POST | Updates `storyboards.description` for the given `storyboard_id`. Returns `{success}`. |

No external AI provider calls. No scheduler triggers. No ChromaDB interaction.

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout

- **Header bar:** Icon link back to `view_storyboards.php`, page title "Storyboards Chains"
- **Search bar:** GET form with text input (searches name, description, prompts, IDs) and Reset link
- **Storyboard sections:** One `.storyboard-section` per record, each containing:
  - Header row: storyboard title, Scroll Magic link (▶), editor link (✏️), regen button (↺), creation date, frame count, inline description input
  - Swiper carousel of frame cards
- **Frame cards:** Square thumbnail (PhotoSwipe-linked) + card body with title, method badge(s), truncated prompt, entity badge
- **Pagination:** Previous / Next buttons + direct page number input

#### Responsive Behaviour

The `<meta viewport>` is set to `initial-scale=0.6` (storyboard chains view) and `0.7` (frame chain view) — these are fixed zoom-out scales rather than fully fluid responsive layouts. This is intentional for the mobile-on-Chrome workflow, allowing wider card carousels to be visible without horizontal overflow clipping. `[VERIFY — confirm this is intentional vs. a placeholder]`

#### Modals

| Modal ID | Trigger | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `#meta-modal` | Click `.meta-pill-trigger` (Ingredients badge) | Lists all `sketch_ingredients` rows for the frame with type icons and truncated detail |
| `#curation-modal` | Click `.curation-pill-trigger` (Analysis badge) | Overall quality score, narrative function, emotional tone, themes (pills), characters (pills), artifacts, score breakdown grid (narrative / visual / production / distinctiveness), AI suggestion block |
| `#desc-modal` | Click `.full-desc-trigger` (prompt text) | Full prompt/description in monospace, pre-wrap |

All modals use `.modal-overlay` with click-outside-to-close and ✕ button.

#### Toast Notifications

Uses `/js/toast.js` + `/css/toast.css` for success/error feedback on regeneration and save operations.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Direction | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `view_storyboards.php` | Links to | Overview/grid view of all storyboards; icon link in header |
| `view_storyboard.php` | Links to | Per-storyboard frame editor; pencil icon per section |
| `view_scrollmagic_multi_prm.php` | Links to | Scroll Magic presentation view; play icon per section |
| `view_frame_chain.php` | Companion | Single-frame lineage viewer; shares data model and card design |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | Included | Frame detail modal (shared partial); included via output buffer |
| `ModuleRegistry` (GearMenu) | Embedded | Gear menu attached to container; standard entity actions for all major entity types |
| `ModuleRegistry` (ImageEditor) | Embedded | Image editor module rendered into page |
| `/js/gear_menu_globals.js` | Script dep | Global gear menu JS |
| `/js/sage-home-button.js` | Script dep | Dashboard home button (storyboard chains view only) |
| SwiperJS 11 | CDN | Horizontal card carousel |
| PhotoSwipe 5 | CDN | Full-screen image lightbox |
| Bootstrap Icons 1.10 | CDN | UI icons |
| jQuery 3.7.1 | CDN | AJAX and DOM helpers |

---

### Known State / Notes

- **`$is_modal_view` flag** in `view_frame_chain.php` is set from `?view=modal` but not used in the current render path — no conditional HTML output branches on it. `[VERIFY — likely in-progress feature for embedding the chain view inside a modal in another page]`
- **Viewport scale** uses fixed `initial-scale=0.6/0.7` rather than a fluid responsive breakpoint. This is consistent with the mobile-Chrome-on-Termux workflow but may clip on very small screens without scrolling.
