*SAGE 2.0 Module Documentation — Scheduler Forge / Map Run Queue Viewer*

---

## 1. Introduction

The Queue Viewer is SAGE''s real-time production job monitor and control panel for the AI asset generation pipeline. It surfaces every pending, processing, completed, failed, and cancelled task in the `map_run_queue` table through a live-updating table interface, giving the operator full visibility over both image frame generation (handled by `genworker_queue.sh`) and video/animatic generation (handled by `genvideo_queue.sh`). Beyond passive monitoring, the Queue Viewer is an active operations tool: individual jobs can be cancelled, reset, re-prioritised, or have their AI provider and model overridden on a per-job basis without touching the underlying entity. The module also hosts the Global & Manual Worker Defaults panel, where the scope-level provider configuration — endpoint, model, and output dimensions — can be saved to the database for both the cron worker and ad-hoc manual runs.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Queue Viewer sits at the execution layer of the SAGE pipeline, downstream of all entity-level generation triggers (sketch editors, animatic editors, enhancement tools, etc.) and upstream of the actual worker bash scripts. Its job is to make the asynchronous generation queue observable and operable from a mobile browser without SSH access.

**Inputs:** `map_run_queue` and `map_run_queue_archive` database tables; `worker_img_api_endpoint`, `worker_img_api_endpoint_param`, and `worker_img_provider_default` tables for provider configuration; the Pollinations AI public model list API.

**Outputs:** Written mutations to `map_run_queue` (status changes, priority toggles, per-job `api_provider_config` overrides); written mutations to `worker_img_provider_default` (scope-level defaults); read-only display of all queue state.

---

### Key Features

#### Live Queue Table
Paginated table (50 rows/page) showing all queue items with columns: ID, Map Run ID, Entity (type + ID, clickable to open the entity form modal), Status (badge), Asset (type + ID or "pending"), Model override chip, Attempts (with max), Priority indicator, and Created timestamp. The table refreshes on demand via the header refresh button.

#### Archive Toggle
A checkbox switches the view between the live `map_run_queue` table and the `map_run_queue_archive` table (completed items moved by the archive action). Archive mode shows different action buttons and only allows selecting cancelled items for restoration.

#### Pending Count & Breakdown
The header displays the live count of pending jobs. Clicking it opens a modal showing the breakdown of pending jobs grouped by `entity_type`, with a row total. This is the fastest way to gauge queue composition at a glance.

#### Batch Actions

| Button | Key | Behaviour |
|--------|-----|-----------|
| `arcomp` | Archive Completed | Moves all `completed` rows from `map_run_queue` to `map_run_queue_archive` |
| `del` | Cancel / Delete Selected | Pending items → `cancelled` (moved to archive); failed items → hard deleted |
| `rst` | Reset Selected | Resets `failed` items: clears `attempts`, sets status back to `pending` |
| `prio` | Toggle Priority | Toggles `priority` between 0 and 1 for selected pending/failed items |
| `undel` | Undelete Selected | Restores `cancelled` archive items back to `pending` in live queue |

Checkboxes are context-sensitive: in live mode, only `pending` and `failed` rows show checkboxes; in archive mode, only `cancelled` rows do.

#### Global & Manual Worker Defaults Panel (`ProviderPanel`)
A collapsible panel below the header that manages the `worker_img_provider_default` table. Two scopes are presented side-by-side:

- **Cron Worker (global):** Used by the scheduled `genworker_queue.sh` cron run.
- **Manual / Ad-hoc:** Used when the worker is triggered manually or from the queue UI.

Each scope exposes: Endpoint selector (from `worker_img_api_endpoint`), Model Override selector (populated from the live Pollinations model list API), and Width × Height overrides. Changes are saved independently per scope via the `save_provider_default` API action.

The panel summary line in the header shows the currently configured provider/model for each scope without needing to expand the panel.

#### Per-Job Model Override (`ModelOverride`)
Each `pending` or `failed` job row in the table shows a clickable **model chip** in the Model column. For jobs with no override it shows `—`; for jobs with an active override it shows the model name highlighted in blue. Clicking it opens a modal allowing the operator to set a specific endpoint, model, and dimensions for that individual job, stored as a JSON object under the `provider` key in `map_run_queue.api_provider_config`. The Clear button removes the override. This does not affect the scope-level defaults.

The model dropdown in both this modal and the Provider Panel is populated dynamically by calling `https://gen.pollinations.ai/image/models`, so it always reflects the provider''s current available models. A hardcoded fallback list (`flux`, `turbo`, `nanobanana`, `gptimage`) is used if the fetch fails.

#### Pagination
Previous/next chevron buttons plus a direct page number input. The total page count is shown. Page state is maintained in the `QueueViewer` IIFE.

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Tables

| Table | Role |
|-------|------|
| `map_run_queue` | Live job queue. One row per generation task. |
| `map_run_queue_archive` | Completed/cancelled jobs moved out of the live queue. Same schema minus auto-increment; adds `archived_at`. |
| `map_runs` | Groups queue items by batch run. Each row represents a generation session for an `entity_type`. |
| `frames` | Output table for image generation jobs. `asset_id` in the queue row is populated with `frames.id` on completion. |
| `frame_counter` | Single-row table with a `next_frame` bigint counter. Atomically incremented per frame to produce unique filenames (`frame0000001.jpg` etc.). |
| `frame_enhancements` | Enhancement-type entities. Queue items with `entity_type = ''frame_enhancements''` reference rows here. |
| `frame_enhancement_frames` | Join table linking an enhancement to one or more reference frames to be uploaded as additional image inputs. |
| `sketches` | Standard image entity. Queue items with `entity_type = ''sketches''` source prompts from the `v_prompts_sketches` view. |
| `animatics` | Video entity. Video queue items reference this table. |
| `videos` | Output table for video generation jobs. |
| `videos_2_animatics` | Maps generated `videos.id` back to the source `animatics.id`. |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Maps generated `frames.id` back to the source `sketches.id`. |

#### Provider Config Tables

| Table | Role |
|-------|------|
| `worker_img_api_endpoint` | Registered API endpoints (provider, base URL, path template, HTTP method). |
| `worker_img_api_endpoint_param` | Per-endpoint query parameter defaults (model, width, height, nologo, etc.) with sort order. |
| `worker_img_provider_default` | One row per scope (`global` / `manual`). Stores the active endpoint ID and any scope-level overrides for model, width, height. |

#### `map_run_queue` Column Notes

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `entity_type` | The semantic source type (e.g. `sketches`, `animatics`, `frame_enhancements`, `composites`). |
| `asset_type` | The physical output type (`frames` or `videos`). Routes to the correct worker. |
| `asset_id` | NULL until the worker successfully generates and inserts the output row. |
| `priority` | Integer; higher = earlier. The UI toggles between 0 and 1. |
| `api_provider_config` | JSON blob. Top-level keys `limit`, `offset`, `no_styles`, `add_to_prompt` control frame generation behaviour. The `provider` sub-object holds per-job endpoint/model/dimension overrides read by the worker. |
| `error_msg` | Dual-use: stores error text on failure; temporarily stores a worker claim token (`worker_$$_${RANDOM}`) during atomic batch claiming to prevent duplicate processing by concurrent worker instances. |

---

### API / Backend Integration

All frontend requests in `view_queue.php` go to `/api/scheduler_forge_api.php` via `POST` with a JSON body containing an `action` key. The `apiCall()` utility function handles all requests.

| Action | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `fetch_queue` | Returns paginated queue rows. Params: `page`, `limit`, `archive` (bool). Also returns `pending_count` and `pending_by_entity` breakdown. |
| `archive_completed_queue` | Moves all `completed` rows from live queue to archive. Returns `count`. |
| `cancel_queue_items` | Marks selected `pending` item IDs as `cancelled` (archive-compatible). |
| `delete_failed_queue_items` | Hard-deletes selected `failed` item IDs. |
| `reset_failed_queue_items` | Resets `failed` items to `pending` with `attempts = 0`. |
| `uncancel_queue_items` | Restores `cancelled` archive items to `pending` in the live queue. |
| `toggle_queue_priority` | Flips `priority` between 0 and 1 for selected IDs. |
| `fetch_provider_config` | Returns all `worker_img_api_endpoint` rows plus `worker_img_provider_default` rows for all scopes. |
| `save_provider_default` | Upserts a scope row in `worker_img_provider_default`. Params: `scope`, `endpoint_id`, `model_override`, `width_override`, `height_override`. |
| `set_queue_item_provider` | Updates `api_provider_config` on a single queue row. Params: `id`, `api_provider_config` (JSON or null). |

**External API call (client-side):** `https://gen.pollinations.ai/image/models` — fetched directly from the browser by `PollinationsAPI.getModels()` to populate model dropdowns. Result is cached in-memory for the page lifetime.

---

### Worker Scripts

The queue is consumed by two bash workers, both invoked either via cron or manually from the server.

#### `bash/genworker_queue.sh` — Frame Generation Worker

Usage: `./genworker_queue.sh [limit] [scope]`

- **Scope** (`global` or `manual`, default `global`) determines which `worker_img_provider_default` row is loaded for provider defaults.
- Uses **atomic claiming**: sets `status = ''processing''` and `error_msg = ''$WORKER_CLAIM_ID''` in a single `UPDATE ... LIMIT N` before fetching, preventing duplicate processing by concurrent instances. The claim token is a PID+random string (`worker_$$_${RANDOM}`). On completion, `error_msg` is overwritten with the actual error or set to NULL.
- **Provider resolution order** (highest priority wins):
  1. Per-job `api_provider_config.provider` sub-object (endpoint_id, model, width, height)
  2. Scope-level `worker_img_provider_default` overrides (model_override, width_override, height_override)
  3. `worker_img_api_endpoint_param` table defaults for the active endpoint
  4. Hardcoded fallback (flux / 1024×1024) if no DB config exists
- **Entity routing**: `entity_type = ''frame_enhancements''` is processed differently from standard types. Enhancements read from the `frame_enhancements` table and may attach multiple additional reference images via `frame_enhancement_frames`.
- **Prompt sourcing**: Standard entities read from `v_prompts_{entity_type}` views. Enhancements use their own `description` field plus the original entity''s description as the DB-saved prompt.
- **Image uploads**: Source images for img2img and depth2img workflows are uploaded to `freeimage.host` (with `litterbox.catbox.moe` as fallback) before generation, producing a URL passed as the `image` query param.
- **Output**: Writes to `frames` table and the appropriate `frames_2_{entity_type}` mapping table. Frame filenames are generated atomically from `frame_counter`.
- **Retry logic**: `max_attempts` retries per job. On failure below the limit, status returns to `pending` with incremented `attempts`. At limit, status becomes `failed`.

#### `bash/genvideos_queue.sh` — Video Enqueuer

Usage: `./genvideos_queue.sh entity_type [batch_limit]`

- Not a worker — a **queue filler**. Selects entities with `regenerate_videos = 1` (or `regenerate_images = 1` for composites), creates a `map_runs` row, and inserts `asset_type = ''videos''` queue items. Clears the regenerate flag immediately after queuing.

#### `bash/genvideo_queue.sh` — Video Generation Worker

Usage: `./genvideo_queue.sh [limit]`

- Consumes `asset_type = ''videos''` queue items. Does not use the DB provider config system (hardcoded to Pollinations `wan-fast` at 1024×1024). [VERIFY — may be updated in a future iteration]
- Handles two modes: `animatics` (text-to-video or image-to-video depending on `img2img` flag) and `composites` (interpolation between two frames).
- Writes to `videos` table and the `videos_2_{entity_type}` mapping table.
- Generates a thumbnail via `ffmpeg` from the first frame of the output video.

---

### UI & Interaction

The layout is a full-viewport flex column: fixed header → optional provider panel → scrollable table wrapper. `overflow: hidden` on `body` keeps the outer frame static while the table scrolls internally.

**Theme:** Forge UI dark/light with `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` applied before paint via an inline script to prevent FOUC.

**Entity link:** Clicking the Entity cell calls `showEntityFormInModal(entity_type, entity_id)` if that function is available in the window scope, implying this view is designed to be embedded in a parent frame (`?embed=1` viewport scale parameter present) that provides the entity form modal. When used standalone, the click does nothing harmful.

**Modals:**
- *Pending Breakdown* — simple table overlay, closed by clicking overlay or the × button.
- *Model Override* — endpoint + model + dimensions form. Overlay-click closes. Save triggers `set_queue_item_provider` API call then reloads the table.

**Toast notifications:** Bottom-right stack with auto-dismiss (3s) and click-to-dismiss. Colour-coded: green border for success, red text+border for error.

**Mobile-first:** Viewport set to `width=device-width, initial-scale=0.8`. Provider panel uses a 2-column CSS grid that collapses to 1 column below 600px. All controls are touch-target sized.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|------------|------|-------|
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | PHP | Session auth; redirect to `/login.php` if unauthenticated |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | PHP include | Provides the entity form modal used when clicking entity links |
| `/js/sage-home-button.js` | JS | Injects the standard SAGE home navigation button, pointing to `/dashboard.php` |
| `/api/scheduler_forge_api.php` | PHP API | Backend for all AJAX actions |
| `v_prompts_{entity_type}` | DB views | Read by `genworker_queue.sh` to resolve prompts for standard entity types |
| `v_styles_helper` | DB view | Read by `genworker_queue.sh` to enumerate styles for frame generation |
| Scheduler Forge (trigger UI) | SAGE module | The module that initiates generation runs and populates `map_run_queue` [VERIFY — exact module filename] |
| Sketch Editor / Animatic Editor | SAGE modules | Set `regenerate_images`/`regenerate_videos` flags that enqueuer scripts consume |

