**File:** `rapid_kg_api_processor.php`
**Codename:** *The Curator''s Studio (KG Edition)*
**Module Family:** Knowledge Graph / AI Generation Pipeline

---

## 1. Introduction

The KG Rapid API Processor is SAGE''s AI showcase generation workbench for Knowledge Graph entities. A direct sibling of the Lore API Processor, it operates against the live `kg_nodes` table rather than curated `md_doc_analysis` documents — making the full Knowledge Graph browseable and generatable without requiring prior document analysis. Given a selected KG node (character, location, concept, arc, episode, or any other typed node), the module assembles semantic context from the node''s identity fields and its `kg_node_items` relationship network, presents that context in an editable workspace, and routes it through a configurable AI generator to produce a structured visual prompt showcase in Markdown. The resulting prompts are published to the `rapid_showcase` table for downstream CLI image generation, or saved to the Scripts Library. Alongside the KG Rapid Processor, this recipe also documents `kg_api.php` — the central Knowledge Graph REST API — and `rapid_sketches_processor.php`, the sketch-native showcase generator that operates directly on the `sketches` table with beat brainstorming support.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The KG Rapid API Processor serves the same end goal as the Lore API Processor — generating batches of image prompt showcases — but sources its context from the Knowledge Graph directly. This removes the `md_doc_analysis` dependency entirely, allowing any KG node to become a generation target regardless of whether it originated from a curated lore document. It also supports category-tree filtering, so a showrunner can scope their browse to a specific civilisation, faction, or story arc within the KG hierarchy.

**Pipeline position:**
```
kg_nodes / kg_node_items → [KG Rapid Processor] → rapid_showcase → CLI Image Generator
```

**Inputs:**
- A selected `kg_nodes` record, optionally filtered by `kg_categories` tree
- A chosen Generator Config for showcase authoring
- A chosen Target Generator Config for CLI downstream step

**Outputs:**
- AI-generated Markdown with `### REF_CODE: Title` / context / fenced-prompt blocks
- Rows inserted into `rapid_showcase` (via Publish)
- Optionally, a document saved to `documentations` via the Scripts Library

---

### Key Features

#### KG Category Tree Browser
The sidebar header selector is populated from `kg_categories` with full parent/child hierarchy, rendered via a recursive `buildCatOptions()` PHP function with `&nbsp;` indentation by depth level. Selecting a category triggers `getKgCatFamily()`, which recursively collects all descendant category IDs (breadth-first traversal of the in-memory `childrenMap`), then filters `kg_nodes` to that family. Selecting the blank "All KG Nodes" option loads the entire active node set unfiltered.

#### Dynamic Node Type Grouping
Unlike the Lore API Processor (which groups by hardcoded type list), the KG variant uses `Object.keys(data).sort()` — all node types returned by the backend are rendered dynamically in alphabetical order. This means new `node_type` values in the KG are automatically surfaced in the sidebar without frontend changes.

#### `localStorage` Category State (Default Open)
Category collapse state is persisted under the `kg_cat_` key prefix. The default behaviour differs from the Lore variant: KG categories default to **open** unless explicitly closed (`localStorage !== ''closed''`), reflecting that KG browsing benefits from immediate visibility.

#### Semantic Context Assembly (Direct KG)
On entity selection, `fetch_context` reads `kg_nodes` for the identity block (name, type, description, keywords) and `kg_node_items` for the relationship network. Each item is formatted as:
```
item_label (item_type) - relationship: note
```
The assembled context string has three sections: `IDENTITY` (JSON), `RELATIONSHIPS` (line list), and `CONTENT` (node freetext). All three are editable in the Semantic Data Context textarea before generation.

#### Mini-Graph Deep Link (KG Only)
Because the context source is already a KG node, the mini-graph trigger is always available and always points to `mini_graph.php?graph=kg&node_id={id}`. Both direct link and iframe modal button are rendered unconditionally for every selected node (no AG node lookup is performed in this module — that cross-reference is left to `kg_api.php::fetch_visuals`).

#### Visual Sketch Gallery (Name-Based Cross-Reference)
Sketch history lookup in the KG variant is name-based rather than doc-scoped: `sketch_lore_history` is queried by `entity_name` match only (no `doc_id` constraint), making it cross-compatible with both lore-derived and KG-derived sketches for the same entity. The gallery renders in the same Swiper/PhotoSwipe carousel as the Lore variant, but is constrained to a fixed `320px × 320px` square rather than the free-scroll wide carousel.

#### AI Showcase Generation, Publish, Save to Scripts
Identical pipeline to the Lore variant: `AIProvider::sendPrompt()` at temperature 0.7, `### REF_CODE:` regex parse on publish, `api_md.php` save for the Scripts Library. The default publish category name is taken from the selected KG category selector label (trimmed of `&nbsp;` padding) rather than a document name.

---

### Data Model

#### Tables Read

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `kg_categories` | Category tree for sidebar filter; recursive family traversal |
| `kg_nodes` | Entity index — name, type, description, keywords, content |
| `kg_node_items` | Relationship network per node — item_type, item_id, item_label, relationship, note |
| `sketch_lore_history` | Cross-reference: most recent sketch for entity name (no doc_id scope) |
| `sketches` | Sketch name and description for gallery header |
| `frames` | Frame filenames for Swiper gallery |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Alternate frame-to-sketch join |
| `generator_config` | Showcase Architect and Target Generator selectors |
| `documentation_categories` | Scripts Library modal category selector |

#### Tables Written

| Table | Action | Triggered By |
|---|---|---|
| `rapid_showcase` | `INSERT` per parsed prompt block | Publish action |
| `documentations` | `INSERT` (via `api_md.php`) | Save to Scripts Library |

---

### API / Backend Integration

#### `AIProvider::sendPrompt()`
Called for showcase generation. Config model falls back to `AIProvider::getDefaultModel()` if absent or `''openai''`. Temperature fixed at `0.7`.

#### `api_md.php`
Same two endpoints as the Lore variant: `create_category` and `save`.

#### No PyAPI / Vector calls
Context assembly is entirely relational (MariaDB). No ChromaDB queries are made by this module''s AJAX handlers.

---

### UI & Interaction

Identical layout to the Lore API Processor: fixed flyout sidebar (40% width), main workspace with centre context column and right output column, sidebar-open hides the right column. The Swiper gallery is constrained to a `max-width: 320px; aspect-ratio: 1/1` square rather than a free-scroll multi-image strip. The `initial-scale=0.7` viewport override is present here as well.

---

