## 3. Companion Module: KG API (`kg_api.php`)

### Introduction

`kg_api.php` is the central REST API backing SAGE''s Knowledge Graph system. It handles all CRUD operations for the KG''s categories and nodes, manages the relationship edge system (`kg_node_items`), provides tree export for jsTree rendering, supports full-text and semantic vector search, and produces both full and focused columnar snapshots of the graph for AI context assembly. It is the data layer consumed by the KG editor UI, the KG Rapid Processor, the mini-graph viewer, and any other module that needs programmatic access to graph data.

### Actions Reference

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `fetch_visuals` | POST | Fetch sketch history, frames, KG node ID, and AG node ID for a named entity. Includes `sketch_analysis` curation data if present. Uses lore-history heuristic to detect associated `doc_id` for AG lookup. |
| `fetch_tree` | POST | Returns full jsTree-compatible array of all categories and active nodes with type icons |
| `move_node` | POST | Drag-and-drop: update `category_id` on a node or `parent_id` on a category |
| `create_category` | POST | Insert new `kg_categories` row |
| `rename_category` | POST | Update category name |
| `delete_category` | POST | Soft-delete: orphaned nodes set to `category_id=NULL`, orphaned subcategories set to `parent_id=NULL` |
| `create_node` | POST | Insert new `kg_nodes` row |
| `get_node` | GET | Fetch full node with outgoing AND incoming `kg_node_items` edges; incoming edges joined to source node name/type |
| `save_node` | POST | Upsert node (UPDATE if `id` provided, INSERT otherwise) |
| `delete_node` | POST | Soft-delete: sets `status=''archived''` |
| `rename_node` | POST | Quick rename from tree without full save |
| `add_item` | POST | Insert a `kg_node_items` edge with auto-incremented `sort_order` |
| `update_item` | POST | Update an existing `kg_node_items` edge |
| `remove_item` | POST | Hard-delete a `kg_node_items` edge |
| `search` | GET | Full-text `LIKE` search across `name`, `content`, `keywords`; returns up to 50 active nodes |
| `export_snapshot` | GET | Full columnar graph export (no content text); `with_edges=0` to strip edges. Includes `content_status` classification per node. |
| `semantic_query` | POST | Two-collection ChromaDB query (`sage_kg_nodes_content` weight 1.0, `sage_kg_nodes_meta` weight 0.6); merges scores, joins DB metadata, returns ranked hits with `content_status` |
| `focused_snapshot` | POST | Columnar export for a specific array of `node_ids`; optional `with_content=1` to include full markdown text; optional `with_edges` (default true) |
| `get_fuzz_candidate_for_node` | POST/GET | Returns the most recent `fuzz_candidates` row with `status=''promoted''` for a given `kg_node_id` |

### Input Handling
Accepts both JSON body (decoded from `php://input`) and POST form data; POST wins on key conflicts. GET params used only for `fetch_tree`, `search`, `export_snapshot`, and `get_node`.

### Columnar Export Format
Both `export_snapshot` and `focused_snapshot` use a columnar structure — `fields` array declared once, `rows` as positional value arrays — to minimise token usage when passing snapshots to AI context windows. `export_meta` includes `content_status_summary` (`empty` / `stub` / `partial` / `filled` based on `CHAR_LENGTH(content)`) and a note that content is excluded in the standard export to avoid displacement.

### Semantic Query Architecture (`semantic_query`)
Queries two ChromaDB collections in sequence:
- `sage_kg_nodes_content` — full markdown content vectors, weight `1.0`
- `sage_kg_nodes_meta` — metadata/keyword vectors, weight `0.6`

Distance is converted to similarity via `max(0, 1 - distance/2)`, then weighted. Best score per node across both collections is kept. Results are joined back to `kg_nodes` for metadata enrichment before returning. Max `n_results` capped at 60.

### Node Icons
`kg_node_icon()` maps `node_type` strings to Bootstrap Icons classes: `character` → `bi-person-fill`, `location` → `bi-geo-alt-fill`, `event` → `bi-calendar-event`, `concept` → `bi-lightbulb-fill`, `arc` → `bi-bezier2`, `episode` → `bi-camera-reels`, `relationship` → `bi-arrow-left-right`, default → `bi-journal-text`.

### Data Model

#### Tables Read/Written

| Table | Operations |
|---|---|
| `kg_categories` | SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE |
| `kg_nodes` | SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE (status archive) |
| `kg_node_items` | SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE |
| `sketch_lore_history` | SELECT (fetch_visuals) |
| `sketches` | SELECT (fetch_visuals) |
| `frames` | SELECT (fetch_visuals) |
| `frames_2_sketches` | SELECT (fetch_visuals) |
| `sketch_analysis` | SELECT LEFT JOIN (fetch_visuals — curation data) |
| `ag_nodes` | SELECT (fetch_visuals — AG node cross-reference) |
| `documentations` | SELECT (fetch_visuals — validates lore doc_id is active) |
| `fuzz_candidates` | SELECT (get_fuzz_candidate_for_node) |

#### `kg_nodes` — Key Columns

| Column | Usage |
|---|---|
| `id` | Primary key; used in all node operations |
| `name` | Display name; unique; used in semantic lookups |
| `node_type` | Type classification; drives icon, grouping, filtering |
| `category_id` | FK to `kg_categories`; nullable (uncategorised) |
| `content` | Freetext markdown body; excluded from standard snapshot |
| `description` | Short description; included in identity context |
| `keywords` | Comma/space-separated keywords; included in identity context and search |
| `status` | `''active''` or `''archived''`; all reads filter `status=''active''` |
| `sort_order` | Display ordering within category |

#### `kg_node_items` — Key Columns

| Column | Usage |
|---|---|
| `node_id` | Owner node FK |
| `item_type` | Type of linked item (e.g. `''kg_node''`, `''character''`, etc.) |
| `item_id` | Optional DB ID of linked entity |
| `item_label` | Display label for the linked item |
| `relationship` | Relationship descriptor (e.g. "allied with", "opposes") |
| `note` | Extended note on the relationship |
| `sort_order` | Display ordering |

#### `get_node` Bidirectional Edge Logic
`get_node` merges outgoing edges (rows owned by this node) with incoming edges (rows from other nodes where `item_type=''kg_node''` and `item_id` matches this node''s ID). Incoming edges are joined to the source node''s name and type for display. Both sets carry a `direction` field (`''outgoing''` / `''incoming''`).

