## 5. Shared Data Model: Sketch / Frame Tables

These four tables are shared across all three rapid processors and `kg_api.php`.

### `sketch_lore_history`

Audit log of AI sketch generations, linking a generated sketch back to the lore document and entity that prompted it. Used by the KG Rapid Processor and Sketches Processor for cross-referencing existing visuals.

| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| `sketch_id` | FK to `sketches.id` |
| `doc_id` | FK to `documentations.id` |
| `entity_type` | Plural type string (e.g. `''characters''`, `''locations''`) used for AG/KG detection heuristic |
| `entity_name` | Name string used for name-based lookups |
| `generator_config_id` | Which config was used to generate |
| `prompt_used` | Context/prompt sent to AI at generation time |

The AG detection heuristic across all modules checks `entity_type` for a trailing `''s''` to distinguish lore-derived entries (plural category types) from KG-derived entries.

### `sketches`

The core image generation entity. Key fields used by the rapid processors:

| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| `name` | Unique; used as showcase category name on publish |
| `description` | Scene prompt / beat notes; editable in workspace |
| `description_raw` | Original pre-continuity-modification prompt |
| `mood` | Mood label; displayed in sidebar and included in AI prompts |
| `seed` | Generation seed; displayed in gallery |
| `img2img` / `cnmap` flags | Image-to-image and ControlNet map generation toggles; not directly used by rapid processors |

### `frames`

Generated images. `entity_type=''sketches''` + `entity_id` is the primary join path; `frames_2_sketches` is the secondary join for frames linked via the many-to-many table rather than the direct entity columns.

### `frames_2_sketches`

Many-to-many join between frames and sketches. `to_id` has a CASCADE DELETE constraint on `sketches.id`. Used as a fallback in all frame fetch queries:
```sql
WHERE (f.entity_type = ''sketches'' AND f.entity_id = ?)
   OR f.id IN (SELECT from_id FROM frames_2_sketches WHERE to_id = ?)
```

