### Known State / Notes

- **`muvitriccs_transition_demos` table** is not included in the `db:` dump snapshot supplied. It is auto-created at runtime by `ensureMuviTriccsTable()`. Schema is inferred from the API logic: `(id, transition_name, video_id, job_id, label, is_primary, created_at, updated_at)`. `[VERIFY]` exact column set if the table was added after the dump was taken.

- **`idx_trans` index** on `muvitriccs_render_jobs.transition_name` appears in the PHP `ensureMuviTriccsTable` DDL but is absent from the live `db:muvitriccs_render_jobs` dump, indicating the table was created before that index was added. `[VERIFY]` whether the index has since been applied manually.

- **`tilt_shift_cut`, `cinematic_bars`, `whip_zoom`** appear in `TRANSITION_REGISTRY` and `_MOVIE_NAMES` dispatcher but are present in `transitions_movie.py`. They are not listed in the `/transitions` endpoint''s `families` dict in `muvitriccs_service.py` — the `families` dict for `movie` only lists `iris_wipe`, `venetian_blind`, `cross_zoom`. `[VERIFY]` whether the families dict in `list_transitions` has been updated to include the three missing movie transitions; they will render correctly but may appear under `"other"` family in the UI grid.

