INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('526', 'mod_boards_view', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: Production Boards

**File:** `boards_view.php` + `boards_api.php`
**Module ID:** `boards`
**Doc Version:** 1.0 — SAGE 2.0

---

## 1. Introduction

The Production Boards module is SAGE''s visual curation and cross-reference workspace, allowing Sebastian to assemble production artefacts from across the entire pipeline onto named boards organised into a hierarchical folder tree. Rather than navigating individual modules to track the state of a scene, sequence, or character, boards act as a single pinboard where Map Runs, Storyboards, Documents, Fuzz Candidates, Narrative Sequences, Knowledge Graph nodes, Auto Graph nodes, and Entity records (characters, locations, backgrounds, etc.) can all be gathered together in one view. Each board sits inside a drag-and-drop folder tree, supports pagination over its pinned items, and renders rich content inline — image Swipers with metadata popups, VideoJS players with playlist strips, and compact reference cards with direct deep-links — making it the primary production review surface within SAGE.

---

## 2. Module Details

---

### Purpose & Scope

Production Boards solves the "scattered context" problem that emerges in a large multi-module pipeline. As SAGE grows to cover image generation, video production, narrative sequencing, lore, and documentation, individual artefacts live in their home modules but have no natural review surface that cuts across all of them. Boards provides that surface.

**Pipeline position:** Post-generation review and production tracking layer. It does not create or mutate primary production data (with the single exception of the `regenerate_run` action, which flags sketches for re-generation). Its role is aggregation, reference, and navigation.

**Inputs:**
- Any `map_run`, `storyboard`, `md_doc`, `fuzz_candidate`, `narrative_sequence`, `kg_node`, `ag_node`, or entity record ID from across the SAGE database.

**Outputs:**
- Inline rendered board view (Swiper image carousels, VideoJS player with playlist, slim reference cards).
- Navigation deep-links to the owning module for every pinned item.
- Sketch `regenerate_images` flag write-back (via `regenerate_run` action).

---

### Key Features

#### Board & Folder Tree Navigation
The left-side entry point is a jsTree-powered modal (`#treeModal`) that renders the full folder/board hierarchy. Folders (`boards_categories`) are nestable to arbitrary depth. Boards sit inside folders or at root. Selecting a board node fires `loadBoard()`, closes the tree modal, and renders the board contents via AJAX. The tree supports **drag-and-drop reordering** of both folders and boards, toggled by a persistent checkbox (`boards_tree_dnd_enabled` in `localStorage`). DnD state survives page refresh.

#### Item Type Support
When adding an item to a board, the user selects a type from a dropdown covering 18 item types:

| Category | Types |
|---|---|
| Production runs | `map_run`, `storyboard` |
| References | `md_doc`, `fuzz_candidate`, `narrative_sequence` |
| Graph nodes | `kg_node`, `ag_node` |
| Entities | `characters`, `locations`, `backgrounds`, `animas`, `vehicles`, `artifacts`, `sketches`, `generatives`, `composites` |

Duplicate prevention is enforced server-side: attempting to add an already-pinned item returns a `message: ''Already on board''` response without creating a duplicate row.

#### Rich Content Rendering — Image Runs
Map Runs and Storyboards containing image frames render as a **Swiper carousel** (`frame-chain-swiper`) with `slidesPerView: ''auto''` and free-mode scrolling. Each slide is a `chain-card` containing:
- A square thumbnail (1:1 aspect ratio) with PhotoSwipe lightbox link.
- Frame title and type badge (`Original` / `Edit` / `Img2Img`).
- A **Meta badge** (purple, `badge-meta`) showing the count of sketch ingredients; clicking opens a modal listing each ingredient with icon, label, and prompt fragment.
- A truncated prompt text that opens a full-description modal on click.
- A Gear Menu overlay (top-right of card) for entity-level actions (edit, regenerate, etc.) via the shared `GearMenu` system.
- Arrow connector glyphs between slides (`→` via CSS `::after`).

#### Rich Content Rendering — Video Runs
Map Runs that have associated videos render as a **VideoJS player + playlist strip** rather than a Swiper. The layout is a two-column flex row (65% player / 35% strip) at 450px height, collapsing responsively on mobile. Clicking a playlist thumbnail swaps the active source in the VideoJS player and updates the `vid-details-btn` to point to the newly selected video''s ID. A `🎬 Video Details` button opens the video details view in the shared `frameDetailsModal` iframe overlay.

#### Rich Content Rendering — Reference Cards
Documents, Fuzz Candidates, Narrative Sequences, KG Nodes, and AG Nodes render as compact **ref-cards** in a horizontal wrapping scroll row. Each card shows an ID badge, optional name, and an external-link icon. KG and AG node cards also include an `⤢ mini graph` button that opens `mini_graph.php` in a fullscreen iframe modal (`viewModal`), allowing graph context to be reviewed without leaving the board.

#### Pagination
Board item sets are paginated server-side at **5 items per page** (`$limit = 5`), ordered by `created_at DESC`. A pagination bar (Previous / page number input / "of N" / Next) appears at the bottom when `total_pages > 1`. The current page is reflected in the URL via `pushState` for bookmarkability.

#### Regenerate Run
Image map runs display a `↻` icon in the run header. Clicking it calls `boards_api.php?action=regenerate_run`, which sets `regenerate_images = 1` on all `sketches` records linked to the run''s frames. This queues them for the next background image generation cycle.

#### Theme Toggle
A `🌙/☀️` toggle in the sticky header switches `data-theme` between `dark` and `light` on `<html>`, persisted via `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` — consistent with the Forge UI system-wide theming standard.

#### URL State
On initial load, `board_id` and `page` are read from query string parameters, enabling direct deep-links to a specific board page. `pushState` keeps the URL in sync as the user navigates.

---

### Data Model

#### Tables Read

| Table | Usage |
|---|---|
| `boards` | Board name, status, category membership |
| `boards_categories` | Folder hierarchy for tree |
| `boards_items` | The pin records linking items to boards |
| `map_runs` | Fetched by ID for image/video run data |
| `frames` | Frame images, prompts, entity links |
| `storyboards` | Storyboard metadata |
| `storyboard_frames` | Frame list for a storyboard |
| `videos` | Video URL, thumbnail, duration for video runs |
| `documentations` | Doc name and content preview |
| `fuzz_candidates` | Label, concept type, notes preview |
| `narrative_sequences` | Sequence name |
| `kg_nodes` | KG node name |
| `ag_nodes` | AG node name and `doc_id` |
| `generatives` | Generative name for frame enrichment |
| `image_edits` | Edit tool and note for badge classification |
| `sketches` | Sketch description for frame prompt |
| `meta_sketches` | Meta associations for ingredient lookup |
| `sketch_ingredients` | Full ingredient list per sketch |
| `generator_config` | Generator title for ingredient labels |
| `sketch_templates` | Template name/core idea for ingredient labels |
| `interactions` | Interaction name for ingredient labels |
| `frames_2_{entity}` | Dynamic link tables (e.g. `frames_2_characters`) for entity frame lookups |
| Individual entity tables | `characters`, `locations`, `backgrounds`, `animas`, `vehicles`, `artifacts`, `sketches`, `generatives`, `composites` |

#### Tables Written

| Table | Action | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `boards` | INSERT | `create_board` action |
| `boards_categories` | INSERT / UPDATE `parent_id` | `create_category`, `move_node` |
| `boards_items` | INSERT / DELETE | `add_item`, `remove_item` |
| `sketches` | UPDATE `regenerate_images = 1` | `regenerate_run` |

#### Key Schema Notes

```sql
-- boards_items: the core pin record
`item_type` varchar(50)   -- e.g. ''map_run'', ''storyboard'', ''md_doc'', ''kg_node'', ''characters'' ...
`item_id`   int(11)       -- FK into the type''s own table
`note`      text          -- production note (stored but not currently displayed in UI) [VERIFY]
`sort_order` int(11)      -- append-only increment on add; not yet reorderable via UI [VERIFY]

-- boards_categories: self-referential folder tree
`parent_id` int(11)       -- NULL = root folder
`sort_order` int(11)      -- used for tree ORDER BY
```

---

### API / Backend Integration

All board operations are handled by `boards_api.php`, which accepts `action` via `$_POST` or `$_GET`.

#### API Endpoints (boards_api.php)

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `list_boards` | GET/POST | Returns all active boards with category name |
| `fetch_tree` | GET | Returns jsTree-compatible node array for folders + boards |
| `move_node` | POST | Updates `parent_id` / `category_id` after DnD reorder |
| `create_category` | POST | Inserts a new folder; optionally nested under `parent_id` |
| `create_board` | POST | Inserts a new board; optionally inside `category_id` |
| `add_item` | POST | Pins an item to a board (deduplication enforced) |
| `remove_item` | POST | Deletes a `boards_items` row by `id` (`link_id`) |
| `regenerate_run` | POST | Sets `regenerate_images=1` on sketches linked to a map run |
| `fetch_board_content` | POST | Main content loader — returns paginated item data with full frame/video enrichment |

#### External / Internal Service Calls
- No PyAPI (FastAPI) calls.
- No external AI provider calls.
- No scheduler job triggers.
- Uses `KitchenChef` class (`App\SceneKitchen\KitchenChef`) — instantiated in `boards_api.php` but `[VERIFY]` whether it is actively invoked in current board content fetching (the `getRichContentForItem` helper appears to use direct PDO queries rather than Chef methods in the provided source).

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout
The page uses a **sticky header** containing: the 🌳 tree-open button, board title + subtitle, theme toggle, and a contextual `+ Add Item` button (hidden until a board is loaded). Below the header, `#board-content` is a fluid max-1600px container that renders the board''s item sections stacked vertically.

#### Interaction Patterns

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Board navigation | jsTree modal, node-click fires `loadBoard()` |
| Add item | Modal with type-select + ID input |
| Remove item | Inline `✕` on ref-cards; `Remove` button on run headers; `confirm()` dialog |
| Create folder/board | Separate modals triggered from tree modal toolbar |
| Image lightbox | PhotoSwipe 5 (ESM module), initialized per board load |
| Video player | VideoJS 8.5; player instances checked before re-init |
| Ingredient meta | Click `.meta-pill-trigger` → JSON parsed from `data-ingredients` → rendered in `#meta-modal` |
| Full prompt | Click `.full-desc-trigger` → `data-full-desc` → `#desc-modal` |
| Mini graph | Click `⤢ mini graph` → `openIframeModal()` → fullscreen iframe modal |
| Video details | `openVideoDetails(id)` → `view_video_details.php` in `frameDetailsModal` iframe |
| Gear Menu | `GearMenu.attach()` called after each board render; entity/frame actions (edit, regenerate, etc.) via `gear_menu_globals.js` |
| URL sync | `pushState` on `loadBoard()`; `popstate` not wired [VERIFY] |

#### Mobile Behaviour
- `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=0.8">` — slight zoom-out on mobile.
- Video grid collapses: player `flex: 0 0 60%`, thumbnails shrink to `110px` width, container height reduces to `280px`.
- Swiper uses `freeMode` and `slidesPerView: ''auto''` — touch-scrollable on Android Chrome.
- Ref-card rows use `flex-wrap: wrap` — stack naturally on narrow screens.
- Tree modal is fixed-width `400px` — may overflow on very small screens [VERIFY].

#### Toast Notifications
All async operations use the shared `Toast.show(message, type)` system (`/js/toast.js`, `/css/toast.css`) with `''success''`, `''error''`, and `''info''` variants.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

#### Modules This Board Viewer Depends On

| Dependency | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Core | PDO, SpwBase, AccessManager |
| `ModuleRegistry` (`gear_menu`, `image_editor`) | UI Component | Gear Menu overlay + image editor modal on frames |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | UI Component | Shared iframe overlay for video details and doc preview |
| `gear_menu_globals.js` | JS | Shared gear menu logic for entity actions |
| `KitchenChef` | PHP Class | Instantiated in API [VERIFY active usage] |
| jsTree 3.3.12 | JS Library | Folder/board tree |
