**Files:** `public/entity_form.php` · `public/view_frame.php` · `src/Gallery/FrameDetails.php`  
**Dump command:** `./bash/dumpcode.sh temp/enfofradet101.txt public/entity_form.php public/view_frame.php src/Gallery/FrameDetails.php db:frames db:videos db:sketches db:animatics db:frames_2_sketches db:videos_2_animatics db:sketch_analysis db:map_runs public/entity_icons.php`

---

## 1. Introduction Paragraph

The Entity Form is SAGE''s universal record editor — a single PHP view that dynamically adapts to any entity type in the production database, from `sketches` and `characters` to `animatics`, `composites`, and audio entities. It presents the entity''s editable fields alongside all contextually relevant media: generated frames, depth maps, composite images, rendered videos, and audio tracks, each surfaced in its own collapsible section. Deeply integrated with the Knowledge Graph, Fuzz Graph, and Story Bible systems, the Entity Form also surfaces cross-system lore and node references directly on the sketch record, making it a unified inspection and editing hub for any pipeline entity. The companion Frame Viewer (`view_frame.php`) provides a dedicated full-detail page for any individual frame, including AI computer vision analysis, depth map preview, prompt metadata, and live graph links — accessible as a standalone page or embedded as a modal iframe within the Entity Form.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Entity Form (`entity_form.php`) solves the problem of needing a single, universal editing interface for every entity type in SAGE''s relational database without hand-coding a form per entity. It:

- Accepts any `entity_type` and `entity_id` via GET parameters.
- Introspects the target table''s column metadata via `SHOW FULL COLUMNS` to derive field types, nullability, and labels dynamically.
- Renders a structured edit form with core fields always visible and advanced/system fields collapsed behind a toggle.
- Aggregates all media attached to the entity — frames, depth maps, composite images, source (img2img/cnmap) frames, videos, and audios — into collapsible sections below the form.
- For `sketches` entities, surfaces AI narrative analysis (curation), Fuzz Graph links, KG node links, and Automatic Graph (AG) node links.

`view_frame.php` is the standalone Frame Viewer, providing deep detail on a single `frames` record, including image display, depth map side-by-side, prompt/seed/filename metadata, lore/KG/graph cross-links, and an AI Vision analysis modal powered by `PyApiCVService`.

`src/Gallery/FrameDetails.php` is the PHP class responsible for loading a frame record, resolving its parent entity, and traversing the `sketch_lore_history` → `documentations` → `kg_nodes` → `ag_nodes` chain to produce lore and KG reference data for rendering.

**Pipeline position:** Post-generation inspection and metadata editing layer. Sits downstream of image/video generation (map runs) and upstream of any manual curation or narrative assembly steps.

**Inputs:** `entity_type` (GET), `entity_id` (GET), optional `redirect_url` (GET). POST with `action=update` for saves.

**Outputs:** Rendered HTML view for editing. On POST: SQL `UPDATE` to the entity''s table.

---

### Key Features

#### Dynamic Field Rendering

The form calls `SHOW FULL COLUMNS FROM \`{entity_type}\`` and derives input types automatically:

| Column pattern | Rendered as |
|---|---|
| `tinyint(1)` / boolean flag names | Checkbox |
| `(tiny\|small\|medium\|big)?int` | Number input |
| `float` / `double` / `decimal` | Number input (float) |
| `text` / `longtext` | Textarea (auto-expand on focus) |
| `varchar(>200)` | Textarea |
| `date` / timestamp fields | `datetime-local` input |
| `created_at`, `updated_at` | Read-only system fields |
| `id` / `AUTO_INCREMENT` | Read-only number |

Field names in `$alwaysNames` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `prompt`, `prompt_negative`, `seed`, regenerate flags) are pinned to the "always visible" section. All other columns are placed under the **Advanced & System Fields** collapsible toggle, with state persisted to `localStorage`.

#### Textarea Auto-Expand

Textareas use a CSS-only collapsed state (2 lines) and expand to up to 320px on focus, then collapse cleanly on blur. This preserves vertical space on mobile without sacrificing usability for long prompt fields.

#### Frame Sections

For non-audio entities, the form collects and displays up to four distinct frame categories:

- **Source Images** — the `img2img_frame_id` and `cnmap_frame_id` reference frames for the entity, shown in a fixed 3-column grid with `IMG2IMG` / `CNMAP` badge overlays.
- **Frames** — all `frames` records with `entity_type`/`entity_id` matching the entity, plus any frames linked via `frames_2_{entity_type}` mapping tables.
- **Composite Frames** — for `composites` entities: frames joined via `composite_frames`.
- **Depth Maps** — any frame whose `depth_map_filename` is non-null, collected from all of the above sources.

All image grids use PhotoSwipe 5 for lightbox zoom.

#### GearMenu Integration

A `GearMenu` module instance is initialised with standard actions (delete, view_frame) and attached to all frame grids via `window.GearMenu.attach()`. Actions are configurable per entity type and include delete-with-fade and navigation to `view_frame.php`.

#### Video Section

For `animatics` entities, videos are fetched via `videos_2_animatics`. For all other entities with a `frames_2_{entity_type}` map, a three-way join resolves videos through the animatic''s `img2img_frame_id`. The video section renders a VideoJS player with a horizontal playlist strip. Clicking a thumbnail swaps the player source; the 🎬 button triggers the `showVideoDetailsModal` from `modal_frame_details.php`.

#### Audio Section

Detected when `entity_type` starts with `audio_` (excluding `audio_voice_identity`). The source audio file (`wav2wav_audio_filename`) is displayed as an HTML5 `<audio>` element. Result audios are resolved from `audios_2_{entity_type}` mapping tables and rendered as an AmplitudeJS playlist with play/pause controls and a progress slider. For `composites`, audios are resolved via `composite_audios`.

#### Sketch Curation Badge

If the entity is a `sketch` with a row in `sketch_analysis`, a green **🕵️ {score}** badge appears in the masthead. Clicking it opens a full **Narrative Analysis modal** showing:

- Overall quality score
- Narrative function and emotional tone
- Theme pills and character entity pills
- Score breakdown grid (narrative completeness, visual impact, production readiness, visual distinctiveness)
- Potential use recommendation

#### Knowledge Graph & Lore Links (Sketches)

For `sketches` entities, the form traverses `sketch_lore_history` (ordered by `id DESC`) to resolve:

- **Fuzz Graph** — available for all entities in `$fuzzSafeEntities`; renders a `🕸️ Fuzz` link and an `⤢ modal` button that opens `fuzzgraph.php` in an iframe modal.
- **KG Node** — resolved by name match against `kg_nodes` (status=active); renders `🔮 KG` link + modal trigger.
- **AG Node** — resolved by name + `doc_id` match against `ag_nodes`; renders `📜 AG` link + modal trigger.

These links appear in the core fields section header. The iframe modal (`#viewModal`) loads the target URL in a full-screen iframe with a close button and ESC key handler.

#### AI Vision Analysis (Frame Viewer)

`view_frame.php` exposes a POST handler (`action=analyze_frame`) that accepts an optional custom prompt, loads the frame''s image file from disk, and calls `PyApiCVService::analyze()` to return a computer vision description. The result is displayed in a modal with a copy-to-clipboard button. The default prompt targets Stable Diffusion-compatible comma-separated descriptions.

---

### Data Model

| Table | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `frames` | R | Primary frame records; `entity_type` + `entity_id` ownership; optional `depth_map_filename`, `img2img_frame_id`, `cnmap_frame_id` |
| `videos` | R | Video records linked to animatics |
| `sketches` | R/W | Sketch entity records; img2img + cnmap fields |
| `animatics` | R/W | Animatic records |
| `frames_2_sketches` | R | Maps `frames.id` → `sketches.id` |
| `videos_2_animatics` | R | Maps `videos.id` → `animatics.id` |
| `sketch_analysis` | R | JSON analysis columns: `classification`, `scoring`, `entities`, `thematics`, `recommendations`, `overall_quality` |
| `map_runs` | R (via frame) | `entity_type`, timestamps, `parent_map_run_id`; linked from frame display |
| `kg_nodes` | R | Knowledge Graph nodes; resolved by name match |
| `ag_nodes` | R | Auto Graph nodes; resolved by `doc_id` + name match |
| `sketch_lore_history` | R | Audit trail linking sketches → lore doc entities; used to resolve KG/AG/lore references |
| `documentations` | R | Validates that a lore `doc_id` is still active (`is_active=1`) |
| `composite_frames` | R | For `composites` entities: maps composite → frame |
| `composite_audios` | R | For `composites` entities: maps composite → audio |
| `audios_2_{entity_type}` | R | Dynamic mapping table for audio entities |
| `{entity_type}` (dynamic) | R/W | Any SAGE entity table; column-inspected at runtime |

**Dynamic mapping tables** — the form checks for the existence of `frames_2_{entityType}` and `audios_2_{entityType}` tables via `SHOW TABLES LIKE ''...''` before querying them.

---

### API / Backend Integration

| Service | Usage |
|---|---|
| `PyApiCVService` | Computer vision analysis in `view_frame.php` (`analyze_frame` POST action); calls FastAPI CV endpoint with image path and prompt |
| `ModuleRegistry` | Instantiates `GearMenuModule`, `ImageEditorModule`, `VideoFrameExtractorModule` |
| `SpwBase` | Provides `getMysqli()`, `getPDO()`, `getProjectPath()` |

No direct external AI provider calls are made from these files. The CV analysis is proxied through `PyApiCVService` which delegates to the Python FastAPI microservice layer.

**Scheduler:** No scheduler job triggers in this module. Regeneration flags (`regenerate_images`, `regenerate_videos`, `regenerate_audios`) are written to the entity record and consumed by the scheduler on its next run.

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout

- **Masthead** — sticky top bar with entity type badge, graph/fuzz/KG/AG links (sketches only), curation score badge, and Back button.
- **Core Fields section** — always-open card containing the primary editable fields. Advanced & System fields hidden behind a `›  Advanced & System Fields` toggle button; state persisted to `localStorage` per entity.
- **Save bar** — fixed at the bottom of the form section with Back and Save Changes buttons.
- **Media sections** — collapsible cards stacked below the form. Section open/collapsed state persisted to `localStorage` per section ID.

#### Frame Viewer Layout (`view_frame.php`)

- Full-width main image at top.
- If depth map present: 50/50 split row — depth map left, Frame Information panel right.
- If no depth map: full-width Frame Information panel.
- Full-width Details section below (prompt, negative prompt, filename).

#### Mobile / Responsive

- `max-width: 0.85` viewport meta scale for compact mobile rendering.
- Frame grid uses `auto-fill minmax(120px, 1fr)` — collapses gracefully.
- Video section: desktop = side-by-side player + playlist strip; mobile = stacked player + horizontal-scroll strip.
- All tap targets ≥ 44px.

#### Modals & Overlays

| Modal | Trigger | Contents |
|---|---|---|
| `#curationModal` | Curation score badge click | Narrative analysis JSON rendered as structured cards |
| `#viewModal` | `⤢ modal` buttons | Full-screen iframe for Fuzz/KG/AG graph pages |
| `#visionModal` | 👁 eye button in Frame Viewer | AI Vision prompt input → loading spinner → result textarea + copy |
| PhotoSwipe lightbox | Frame image click | Full-res image zoom |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | `openVidDetail()` / 🎬 button | Video detail view (included via PHP `require`) |

#### Toast Notifications

`/js/toast.js` is loaded for save confirmation and copy feedback. PHP-side save result is rendered as an inline `.notif` div (success/error) at the top of the page on POST redirect.

