**File group:** `rapid_forge.php` · `rapid_import_forge.php` · `rapid_config_forge.php` · `api/generate.php` · `cli_rapid_gen.php`
**Database table:** `rapid_showcase` · `generator_config` · `sketches`

---

## Introduction

The Rapid Forge is SAGE''s automated batch generation system for producing AI-authored Sketch entities at scale from a structured scenario library. It solves the cold-start problem in pre-production by allowing Sebastian to define hundreds of narrative, visual, or lore scenarios in advance — imported from structured Markdown files — and then process each one sequentially through the configured AI generator pipeline, automatically producing a named Sketch record per scenario. The system is split across three browser-based Forge UI views (generator, importer, config) and a companion CLI runner, all backed by a shared `rapid_showcase` queue table and the central `generator_config` system. Rapid Forge sits between the lore/narrative authoring phase and the Sketch/Storyboard pipeline, acting as the factory floor that turns pre-written scenario briefs into seeded SAGE content.

---

## Purpose & Scope

**What it does:** Rapid Forge processes a queue of "scenarios" (`rapid_showcase` rows) through a two-pass AI generation pipeline — first generating a long-form description, then generating a short name — and saves the result as a new `sketches` record. Each scenario is then marked as completed with a reference to the created sketch.

**Pipeline position:** Post-lore authoring → pre-Sketch curation. Rapid Forge feeds the `sketches` table, which is downstream consumed by storyboard tools (e.g. VidBat, Showrunner).

**Inputs:**
- `rapid_showcase` queue rows (reference code, title, category, scenario prompt, assigned generator config ID)
- `generator_config` records (AI provider configuration, system role, output schema, oracle config)

**Outputs:**
- New rows in `sketches` (name, description)
- `rapid_showcase` rows updated with `is_generated = 1` and `created_sketch_id`

---

## Key Features

### rapid_forge.php — Generator View

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Pending job queue sidebar | Scrollable list of all `rapid_showcase` entries, filterable by search term. Shows reference code, category badge, and DONE/PENDING status. |
| Sequence loop (Start/Stop) | Runs `processNextJob()` continuously until the queue is empty, with a 2-second cooldown between jobs. Controlled via header button or main CTA. |
| Active job workspace | Displays current scenario context (title, category, prompt) as a read-only textarea; populates generated Name and Description fields as each pass completes. |
| Generator auto-select | The generator assigned to the scenario''s `generator_config_id` is selected automatically; falls back to the first available option if not found. |
| Generation log panel | Green-on-black terminal log panel appended in real-time during sequence processing; timestamped entries for each step. |
| Manual job preview | Clicking a sidebar card loads the scenario into the workspace form without triggering generation. |
| Sketch save + mark complete | On successful generation, POSTs the form to create a `sketches` row, then calls `?action=mark_complete` to update `rapid_showcase`. |
| Pending count header stat | Live counter showing remaining ungenerated active jobs, refreshed after each job completes. |

### rapid_import_forge.php — Importer View

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Markdown file importer | Drag-and-drop or file-browse upload of `.md` / `.txt` files. Parses the file server-side and inserts new `rapid_showcase` rows. Always inserts; never overwrites. |
| Category + generator parsing | Parses `## Category Name` headings and optional `**Generator**: \`name\`` metadata to assign `generator_config_id` per category. Falls back to a hardcoded default if no match found. |
| Fuzzy generator name matching | Generator lookup normalises names (strips non-alphanumeric, lowercases) and tries substring matching if exact match fails. |
| Scenario block parsing | Each scenario is expected to follow: `### REFCODE: Title`, followed by a fenced code block containing the prompt text. |
| Import stats display | After upload, shows count of new rows inserted and errors encountered. |
| AI Instruction modal | Modal displaying the contents of `public/rapid.json` — a JSON instruction file to be copied to an LLM to generate correctly formatted import Markdown. |

### rapid_config_forge.php — Config View

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Category sidebar with progress bars | Lists all distinct categories from `rapid_showcase`, each showing a progress bar (% generated), total/generated counts, and current generator assignment. |
| Archived / Hide Done toggles | Header toggle pills persist to `localStorage`. "Show Archived" flips to show only archived categories; "Hide Done" suppresses fully-completed categories. |
| Category editor panel | Selecting a category loads an editor showing stats, a sample prompt preview, a generator select dropdown, and checkboxes for Reset Progress and Archive Category. |
| Bulk generator reassignment | Saving applies the selected `generator_config_id` to all `rapid_showcase` rows in the category via `UPDATE ... WHERE category = ?`. |
| Progress reset | Optional "Reset Progress" checkbox sets `is_generated = 0` for all rows in the category; triggers a page reload after save to refresh counts. |
| Archive toggle | Sets `is_archived = 1` on all rows in the category; archived rows are skipped by the generator sequence. |
| Items modal | "Items" button fetches all scenario rows for the selected category and renders them as a scrollable list with reference codes, titles, prompts, and generated status. |
| Context preview | Expand icon on the sample prompt block opens a full-screen modal for reading the complete prompt text. |

### api/generate.php — AI Generation Endpoint

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Authenticated JSON API | Accepts POST with JSON body or form data. Requires active session. |
| Config-driven generation | Loads the `GeneratorConfig` entity by `config_id`, then delegates to `GeneratorService` with caller-supplied parameters. |
| Info mode | `_info=1` query param returns the config''s structure (model, parameters, output schema, oracle flag) without running generation. |
| Pass-through AI options | `temperature` and `max_tokens` in the request body are extracted and forwarded to the AI provider separately from the entity parameters. |
| Schema validation + normalisation | Uses `SchemaValidator` and `ResponseNormalizer` service classes; result returned via `$result->toArray()`. |

### cli_rapid_gen.php — CLI Runner

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Headless batch processor | PHP CLI script that replicates the browser loop exactly — fetches next job, generates description, generates name, saves sketch, marks complete — without requiring a browser session. |
| ANSI terminal output | Colour-coded progress output (cyan headers, yellow job info, green OK, red errors). |
| Configurable delays | `$delaySeconds` constant controls cooldown between jobs. Sleeps 5 seconds on error to prevent API hammer loops. |
| Fallback handling | If the assigned `generator_config_id` is not found, falls back to `$fallbackDescGenId`. If the name generator config is missing, uses the scenario title as the name. |

---

## Data Model

### `rapid_showcase`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | int PK | Auto-increment |
| `reference_code` | varchar | Short code, e.g. `VX-001` |
| `title` | varchar | Human-readable scenario title |
| `category` | varchar | Group label for config assignment |
| `description_prompt` | text | Scenario brief fed to the AI as context |
| `generator_config_id` | varchar | FK → `generator_config.config_id` |
| `is_generated` | tinyint | `0` = pending, `1` = complete |
| `is_archived` | tinyint | `1` = excluded from generation queue |
| `created_sketch_id` | int | FK → `sketches.id`, set on completion |
| `created_at` | datetime | Import timestamp |

### `generator_config`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `config_id` | varchar UNIQUE | UUID-style string key |
| `user_id` | int nullable | NULL = public/system generator |
| `title` | varchar | Display name |
| `model` | varchar | AI provider/model string |
| `system_role` | text | System prompt |
| `instructions` | JSON | Generation instruction set |
| `parameters` | JSON | Input parameter schema |
| `output_schema` | JSON | Expected output structure |
| `examples` | JSON nullable | Few-shot examples |
| `oracle_config` | JSON nullable | Bloom Oracle creative seeding config |
| `active` | tinyint | `1` = available for use |
| `is_public` | tinyint | `1` = accessible to all users |
| `list_order` | int | Drag-and-drop order |

### `sketches`

Output table. Rapid Forge writes `name`, `description`, `order`, `created_at`, `updated_at`. The `sketches` table is shared with other SAGE modules (Showrunner, VidBat, PLUSH) — Rapid Forge is one of several entry paths that creates rows here.

---

## API / Backend Integration

### Internal API calls

| Endpoint | Method | Called by | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `rapid_forge.php?action=get_next_job` | GET | `rapid_forge.php` JS, `cli_rapid_gen.php` | Returns the next ungenerated, unarchived scenario |
| `rapid_forge.php?action=get_queue_list` | GET | `rapid_forge.php` JS | Loads sidebar job list with pending count |
| `rapid_forge.php?action=mark_complete` | POST | `rapid_forge.php` JS | Sets `is_generated=1`, stores `created_sketch_id` |
| `rapid_forge.php` (POST, `action=save`) | POST | `rapid_forge.php` JS | Creates new `sketches` row |
| `rapid_config_forge.php` (POST, `action=update_category`) | POST | Config view JS | Bulk-updates generator and archive status for a category |
| `rapid_config_forge.php` (POST, `action=get_category_items`) | POST | Config view JS | Returns item list for a category |
| `/api/generate.php` | POST JSON | `rapid_forge.php` JS | Runs AI generation via `GeneratorService` |

### AI Provider

Generation is routed through `GeneratorService` → `$spw->getAIProvider()`. The specific AI provider (OpenAI, Groq, Pollinations, etc.) is determined by the `model` field in the `generator_config` row — Rapid Forge itself is provider-agnostic. Two generator configs are hardcoded by UUID in the JS and CLI:

- `446437576e785bbf3d188624dd9794eb` — fallback description generator ("NuSketch Desc Gen") [VERIFY name]
- `9bf6de291765e2ced28589de857a9f0b` — name generator ("NuEntity Name Gen") [VERIFY name]

These UUIDs are referenced directly in `rapid_forge.php` as JS constants `ID_NAME_GEN` / `ID_DESC_GEN` and mirrored in `cli_rapid_gen.php` as `$nameGenId` / `$fallbackDescGenId`.

### rapid.json

`rapid_import_forge.php` reads `public/rapid.json` at page load and surfaces its contents in the AI Instruction modal. This file contains the structured prompt/protocol to be given to an external LLM to produce correctly formatted import Markdown. The file is not generated by SAGE — it is a manually maintained instruction document. [VERIFY: whether this file ships with the repo or must be created by the operator]

---

## UI & Interaction

All three views use the standard SAGE Forge UI design system: Space Mono + Syne fonts, amber accent colour, CSS custom properties with dark/light theming via `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and `data-theme` attribute. Theme detection runs inline before page paint to prevent flash.

### Layout pattern (rapid_forge.php, rapid_config_forge.php)

Both use the same three-area CSS Grid: `52px header | 280–300px sidebar | 1fr main panel`. The sidebar lists jobs/categories; the main panel shows workspace or empty state. On screens ≤ 900px, the layout collapses to a stacked single-column view with the sidebar shrinking to a fixed-height strip above the main area.

### rapid_import_forge.php layout

Uses a two-column workspace: left panel (drop zone + stats) and right panel (import log). Sidebar is a simple vertical nav linking to the three Rapid Forge sub-views.

### Key interactive patterns

- **Toast notifications** — fixed bottom-right, auto-dismiss at 3–3.5s, manually dismissible on click. Types: `success` (green border), `error` (red), `info` (amber).
- **Log console** — monospace green-on-black `<div>`, auto-scrolls on append. Not a `<textarea>`.
- **Toggle pills** (Config view) — styled `<label>` wrappers over hidden checkboxes. State persisted to `localStorage`.
- **Progress bars** (Config view) — inline CSS width driven by `(generated / total) * 100`. Colour: green = 100%, amber = 50–99%, red = 0–49%.
- **Modals** — overlay with `backdrop-filter: blur`. Closed by clicking the overlay or the ✕ button. Config view has two modals: items list and context preview.

---

## Dependencies & Related Modules

| Module / System | Relationship |
|---|---|
| `generator_config` table + `GeneratorService` | Core dependency. All AI generation routes through these. |
| `sketches` table | Output destination. Rapid Forge is a producer; other modules (Showrunner, VidBat, PLUSH) are consumers. |
| `api/generate.php` | Called by the browser JS in `rapid_forge.php` to execute AI generation. |
| SAGE Dashboard (`dashboard.php`) | Entry point. All three views include a home button back to dashboard. |
| `public/rapid.json` | External instruction file surfaced in the Import Forge AI modal. Must exist on disk. |
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Standard SAGE bootstrap. Provides `$spw`, PDO/MySQLi handles, `$em`, `$framesDir`, etc. |
| Bloom Oracle (`oracle_config` in `generator_config`) | Optional creative seeding layer applied during generation if configured on a generator. |

---

## Known State / Notes

- **Hardcoded generator UUIDs** — The description and name generator config IDs are hardcoded as PHP constants and JS variables in `rapid_forge.php`, and as PHP constants in `cli_rapid_gen.php`. If these generator configs are deleted or reassigned to a new UUID, the fallback behaviour will silently break. [VERIFY: whether a UI-based way to configure these defaults is planned]
- **CLI user ID hardcoded** — `cli_rapid_gen.php` sets `$userId = 1` (admin). This bypasses the normal session auth but means the script must be run by a user with ID 1. [VERIFY: whether this is intentional for single-user Termux deployments]
- **Import is insert-only** — `rapid_import_forge.php` never updates existing rows. Re-importing the same file will create duplicate entries. There is no de-duplication by `reference_code` at import time.
- **Config reset triggers reload** — When "Reset Progress" is saved in the Config view, the page performs a full reload after 1 second to get accurate row counts from the database. This is a known workaround for count accuracy.
- **`rapid.json` not in codebase** — The AI instruction file read by the Import Forge modal is external to the PHP source. Its absence produces a JSON error message in the modal rather than a hard failure.
- **Name extraction heuristic** — `runAiGeneration()` in the browser JS and the CLI both try `data.description`, then `data.name`, then `data.text`, then `JSON.stringify(data)` in order. This makes the function tolerant of varied output schemas but the extraction priority could produce unexpected results if a generator returns both `description` and `name` fields. [VERIFY: whether this ordering is intentional]
- **Generator select in browser is `disabled`** — The generator dropdown in `rapid_forge.php` is rendered as `disabled` (auto-selected label). Generators can only be assigned per category via `rapid_config_forge.php`. Manual override from the generator view is not currently supported.
