**Module files:** `view_storyboards.php`, `view_storyboard.php`, `storyboards_api.php`, `storyboard_import.php`, `storyboards_download.php`, `storyboard_order_save.php`, `view_storyboards_pg.php`, `sbcut.php`, `sbcut_api.php`

---

## 1. Introduction

The Storyboards module is SAGE''s visual frame sequencing and pre-visualization system, providing a structured workspace for assembling generated frames into ordered, categorized boards that serve as the production''s pictorial planning layer. It bridges the raw frame output from AI image generation pipelines with the narrative and editorial structure of the series, allowing frames to be tagged to specific episodes, sequences, and scenes or organized by character, location, and other production contexts. The module supports the full lifecycle of a storyboard — creation, ordering, archiving, exporting, copying, splitting, and migration into the narrative sequencer — making it a central hub for visual continuity work. Within the SAGE pipeline, Storyboards sit downstream of image generation and upstream of the Showrunner narrative sequencer and the ScrollMagic multi-plane viewer.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Storyboards module manages collections of frames ("boards") that serve as visual shot planning tools. Each storyboard is a named, categorized container of ordered frame references, backed by a dedicated directory on the filesystem. The module handles:

- Creating and editing storyboard records with category and editorial linkage
- Displaying boards as paginated or scrollable grids of thumbnails
- Drag-and-drop or persistent sort-order management of frames within a board
- Bulk import of frames from the `frames` table into any storyboard
- Copy, archive, export (ZIP), and delete operations on boards
- Splitting a single storyboard into two at any frame boundary
- Cloning a storyboard''s frame sequence into the Narrative Sequencer (`narrative_sequences` table) with entity migration to the `sketches` pipeline

**Inputs:** Frame records from the `frames` table (referenced by `frame_id`); AI-generated image files on disk; editorial structure from `editorial_episodes`, `editorial_sequences`, `editorial_scenes`.

**Outputs:** Ordered storyboard frame collections; physically copied image files in per-board directories; ZIP archives for download; `narrative_sequences` records for use in the Showrunner module.

---

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Category system** | Boards are tagged as `editorial`, `character`, `location`, or `misc` via `storyboard_categories`. The `editorial` type activates a cascading Episode → Sequence → Scene selector for precise production linkage. |
| **Two list views** | `view_storyboards.php` renders a two-column card grid with live search and filter. `view_storyboards_pg.php` adds server-side pagination (10/page) with AJAX load, suitable for large board counts. |
| **Detail view — sortable** | `view_storyboard.php` renders all frames of a single board into a drag-and-drop SortableJS grid with "Save Order", "Auto-prefix", and "Export ZIP" toolbar actions. |
| **Detail view — paginated** | `view_storyboards_pg.php` (detail mode) renders 50 frames per page with bulk checkbox selection, bulk delete, and "Copy to Storyboard" cross-board import via modal. |
| **Frame lazy-copy** | On first render of a detail view, frames with `is_copied = 0` are physically copied from the main frames directory into the storyboard''s own subdirectory under `/storyboards/`, and `is_copied` is set to `1`. This ensures each board owns its own file references. |
| **PhotoSwipe lightbox** | Frame thumbnails open in a PhotoSwipe v5 fullscreen lightbox in both detail views. Natural image dimensions are captured via `onload` for correct cropping. |
| **Archive toggle** | Boards can be archived (soft-delete) and restored without losing frames. The list view has an "Archived" checkbox to switch the view between active and archived boards. |
| **Storyboard copy** | Duplicates a board with all frames (DB-level); the physical copy is deferred to first view. |
| **Clone to Narrative** | The `clone_to_narrative` API action migrates storyboard frames into the `sketches`/`frames`/`narrative_sequences` pipeline. Non-sketch entity frames are migrated to new sketch records via `sketch_migration_entities` and `sketch_migration_frames` mapping tables, with de-duplication logic. |
| **SbCut — Splitter Tool** | `sbcut.php` / `sbcut_api.php` provide a dedicated visual tool for splitting, reordering, and copying storyboards. Frames are shown as a drag-and-drop list (mouse and touch/pointer events). "Split Here" dividers appear between every frame. Splitting creates a new board from the trailing frames and physically removes their copied files from the original board directory. |
| **Export ZIP** | Assembles all `is_copied = 1` frames for a board into a ZIP file (via PHP''s `ZipArchive`), stored in the system temp directory, then served as a download via `storyboards_download.php`. A `metadata.json` is included in the archive. |
| **Auto-prefix rename** | Renames physical files on disk with zero-padded numeric prefixes matching their current sort order (e.g. `001_filename.png`). Strips any existing numeric prefix before applying the new one. |
| **GearMenu integration** | Both detail views attach the SAGE `GearMenu` UI module to the frame grid, enabling standard entity actions (including "Delete Original Frame") for all supported entity types. |
| **Image editor** | Both detail views mount the SAGE `ImageEditor` module (mask, crop, transform, filters) via the `ModuleRegistry`. |
| **Cross-board import** | In the paginated detail view, selected frames (by original `frame_id`) can be copied into any other storyboard via a searchable modal picker backed by `storyboard_import.php` and the `StoryboardHelper` class. |

---

### Data Model

#### Primary Tables

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `storyboards` | One record per board. Holds name, description, filesystem `directory`, `category_id` (FK to `storyboard_categories`), `editorial_scene_id` (optional FK), `custom_tag`, `is_archived`. Note: the table also has a legacy `category` enum column alongside the newer `category_id` FK — [VERIFY whether these are kept in sync]. |
| `storyboard_frames` | Join table between a storyboard and its frames. Each row holds `storyboard_id`, optional `frame_id` (FK to `frames`), `filename` (copied path), `is_copied`, `original_filename`, `sort_order`. Standalone frames (not linked to a `frames` record) have `frame_id = NULL`. |
| `storyboard_categories` | Lookup table: `id`, `name`, `code` (slug), `sort_order`. Seeded with at minimum `editorial`, `location`, `character`, `misc`. |

#### Referenced Tables

| Table | Usage |
|---|---|
| `frames` | Source of frame image paths, `entity_type`, `entity_id`, `rating`, `prompt`, generation metadata. |
| `editorial_episodes` | Cascading dropdown source for editorial boards. |
| `editorial_sequences` | Cascading dropdown source (filtered by episode). |
| `editorial_scenes` | Cascading dropdown source (filtered by sequence); stored as `editorial_scene_id` on the storyboard. |
| `sketches` | Target for `clone_to_narrative` migration. |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Link table populated during clone migration. |
| `map_runs` | New `map_run` records created during clone migration (one per migrated entity type, `entity_type = ''sketches''`). |
| `sketch_migration_entities` | De-duplication map: `source_type`, `source_id` → `target_sketch_id`. Prevents duplicate sketch creation across multiple clone operations. |
| `sketch_migration_frames` | De-duplication map: `source_frame_id` → `target_frame_id`. |
| `narrative_sequences` | Target table for the cloned sequence output from `clone_to_narrative`. |

#### Filesystem

Each storyboard has a unique subdirectory under `/storyboards/` (e.g. `/storyboards/storyboard03741/`). Copied frames are written here as `frame<zero-padded-id>.<ext>`. The directory is created on storyboard creation and on first detail-view render if missing.

---

### API / Backend Integration

All primary CRUD and frame operations go through `storyboards_api.php`. No PyAPI (FastAPI) or external AI provider calls are made by this module.

#### `storyboards_api.php` — Actions

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `get_categories` | GET | Returns all `storyboard_categories` ordered by `sort_order`. |
| `list` | GET | Returns all storyboards (with frame counts, category info, episode/sequence/scene joins, and first-frame thumbnail path). Supports `?archived=true`. |
| `get_episodes` | GET | Returns `editorial_episodes` for cascading selectors. |
| `get_sequences` | GET | Returns `editorial_sequences` filtered by `?episode_id=`. |
| `get_scenes` | GET | Returns `editorial_scenes` filtered by `?sequence_id=`. |
| `create` | POST | Creates new storyboard record and filesystem directory. |
| `update` | POST | Updates name, description, category, editorial scene, custom tag. |
| `toggle_archive` | POST | Sets `is_archived` to 0 or 1. |
| `copy` | POST | Duplicates board and all frame records (deferred physical copy). |
| `clone_to_narrative` | POST | Full migration: creates sketches, frames, links, and a `narrative_sequence` record. Transactional with rollback. |
| `delete` | POST | Hard-deletes board record and all its `storyboard_frames`. Does not currently delete physical files. [VERIFY] |
| `get_frames` | GET | Returns all frames for a board ordered by `sort_order`, joined with `frames` metadata. |
| `save_order` | POST | Bulk-updates `sort_order` for a given ordered array of frame IDs. |
| `delete_frame` | POST | Deletes a single `storyboard_frames` record; unlinks the physical file if `is_copied = 1`. |
| `delete_storyboard_frame` | POST | Alias for single-frame delete (used by paginated view); does not unlink file. [VERIFY distinction] |
| `bulk_delete_storyboard_frames` | POST | Batch deletes `storyboard_frames` records by array of IDs for a given storyboard. Does not unlink files. |
| `rename_in_order` | POST | Renames physical files on disk with numeric prefixes matching current sort order; updates `filename` and `sort_order` in DB. |
| `export_zip` | POST | Creates a ZIP of all `is_copied = 1` frames plus `metadata.json`; returns a `download_url` pointing to `storyboards_download.php`. |

#### `storyboard_import.php`

Accepts `storyboard_id` and a JSON array of `frame_ids` (original `frames.id` values). Delegates to `\App\Helper\StoryboardHelper::importFramesToStoryboard()`. Returns counts of imported and errored frames.

#### `storyboards_download.php`

Validates filename against pattern `storyboard_[a-zA-Z0-9_\-]+\.zip`, streams the ZIP from `sys_get_temp_dir()`, then deletes it. No authentication beyond bootstrap is applied to this endpoint — [VERIFY if download tokens or time-limits are needed].

#### `storyboard_order_save.php`

A legacy filesystem-based order persistence endpoint (writes `storyboard_order.json` files to disk). Supports `save`, `delete`, and `prefix` actions on web-relative directories. Includes hardcoded write-access guards blocking the main project frames directory and `frames_starlightguardians`. This file appears to pre-date the database-driven order system in `storyboards_api.php` and may be used by other views. [VERIFY current usage context]

#### `sbcut_api.php` — Actions

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `copy_storyboard` | POST | Duplicates a board with a new name (DB + deferred physical copy). |
| `split_storyboard` | POST | Splits board at a given frame index into two boards; moves trailing frames to a new board; deletes physical files of moved frames from the original directory. Transactional. |
| `reorder_storyboard` | POST | Bulk-updates `sort_order` from a comma-separated frame ID list. |
| `remove_storyboard_item` | POST | Deletes a single `storyboard_frames` record and unlinks its physical file if copied. Transactional with `FOR UPDATE` lock. |
| `export_storyboard` | POST | Returns full storyboard metadata and all frame rows as a JSON object for client-side download. |
| `delete_storyboard` | POST | Hard-deletes a board, all its frames (DB), all copied physical files, and attempts `rmdir` on the directory. |

---

### UI & Interaction

#### `view_storyboards.php` — Board List

- **Layout:** Forge header bar + filter strip + two-column card grid.
- **Filter strip:** Live search input (180ms debounce on name, `custom_tag`, scene/sequence/episode name), category `<select>`, archive checkbox, and a conditional "editorial" row (episode → sequence → scene cascading selects, revealed when an `editorial` category is selected).
- **Card:** Thumbnail (first copied frame), context badge (colored by category code), storyboard name, contextual detail line, frame count, and action buttons: View, ScrollMagic, Archive/Restore, Edit, Clone to Narrative, Duplicate, Delete.
- **Create/Edit modal:** Forge-styled modal with name, category select, conditional custom tag field (relabeled "Location Name" / "Character Name" / "Tag / Context" depending on category), and conditional editorial cascading selects. Slides down the editorial panel on `editorial` category selection.
- **Clicking a card** (outside buttons) navigates to `view_storyboard.php?id=`.
- **ScrollMagic button** navigates to `/view_scrollmagic_multi_prm.php?storyboard_ids=<id>&refresh=true`.
- **Clone to Narrative** navigates to `narratives_v11.php?sequence_id=<new_id>` on success.

#### `view_storyboard.php` — Board Detail (Sortable)

- **Layout:** Forge header + optional description block + toolbar + `auto-fill minmax(110px, 1fr)` grid.
- **Drag-and-drop:** SortableJS with `.handle` (☰ icon) per frame card; ghost and drag CSS classes applied.
- **PhotoSwipe:** Initialized after every `renderFrames()` call; lightbox covers the full gallery.
- **GearMenu:** Attached to the grid element after render.
- **Toolbar:** Save Order (POST `save_order`), Auto-prefix (POST `rename_in_order` + reload), Export ZIP (POST `export_zip` + redirect to download URL).
- **Frame card:** Thumbnail, name, drag handle, delete button (✕). No pagination — all frames loaded at once via `get_frames`.

#### `view_storyboards_pg.php` — Board List + Paginated Detail

- **List mode** (no `?id`): AJAX-driven board browser, 10 per page, search input with 400ms debounce. Page navigation via prev/next buttons or direct page number input. Cards show preview thumbnail, name, description snippet, frame count, archive badge, category, and timestamps.
- **Detail mode** (`?id=<n>`): 50 frames per page, server-side pagination via prev/next `<a>` links and a number `<input>`. Toolbar has Auto-prefix and Export ZIP. Pagination bar has bulk checkbox "Select all", "Delete selected" (calls `bulk_delete_storyboard_frames`), and "Copy to Storyboard" (opens paginated modal picker calling `storyboard_import.php`).
- **Cross-board import modal:** Searchable paginated list of all storyboards (10/page via `ajax_storyboard_json=1`). Selecting a target board POSTs to `storyboard_import.php`. Only frames with a valid `frame_id` (linked to `frames` table) can be copied; standalone frames are excluded with a warning.

#### `sbcut.php` — Splitter Tool

- **List view:** Shows all non-archived boards with frame counts, a copy icon, and a delete icon per row.
- **Editor view:** Full vertical list of frame cards with drag-and-drop (HTML5 drag API + pointer events for mobile). Each card shows thumbnail (PhotoSwipe ESM module), frame number, entity type badge, frame name, description. A "Split Here" divider appears after each card (except the last).
- **Modals:** Split modal (prompts for new board name, two buttons: "Save & Load Part 1" / "Save & Load Part 2"), Copy modal (prompts for new name), Entity Details modal (iFrame pointing to `entity_form.php`).
- **JSON Export:** Client-side download of storyboard metadata as `.json`.

#### Responsive / Mobile

All views use Forge design tokens with `data-theme` light/dark support. The main grid uses `grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr` (two columns, forced) in `view_storyboards.php`, switching thumbnail height at 480px breakpoint. The paginated view uses `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr))` for the board browser. The SbCut tool uses pointer events for mobile drag-and-drop support.

#### Toast / Status Feedback

- `view_storyboard.php` uses an inline `#save-status` text element.
- `view_storyboards_pg.php` uses both `#save-status` elements and the global `Toast` module (`/js/toast.js`) for import/copy results.
- `sbcut.php` uses the `Toast` module for all async feedback.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

