**Files:** `import_character_poses.php` · `import_character_anima_poses.php` · `import_character_expressions.php`

---

## Introduction

The Character Pose Import System is SAGE''s bulk combinatorial generation tool for seeding the three core visual entity libraries — character poses, Anima poses, and facial expressions — that feed the AI image generation pipeline. Rather than requiring manual entry of every character-angle-perspective permutation, the system computes the full Cartesian product of selected characters, motion types, camera angles, and camera perspectives, previews the resulting combinations against the existing database, and writes only the net-new or force-updated records in a single transactional INSERT. It sits at the top of the visual production pipeline: populated pose records become the prompt sources consumed by the map run image generator. A companion tab within each tool allows operators to manually assign generated frames back to pose records, closing the loop between generation and review.

---

## Purpose & Scope

**What it does:**
These three tools each manage a distinct visual entity type within SAGE:

| Tool | Entity Type | Target Table |
|---|---|---|
| `import_character_poses.php` | Standard body poses | `character_poses` |
| `import_character_anima_poses.php` | Anima-specific motion poses | `character_anima_poses` |
| `import_character_expressions.php` | Facial expressions | `character_expressions` |

The workflow is identical across all three; only the source combination view, target table, and some UI accent colours differ.

**Pipeline position:** Pre-generation. Pose records must exist before a map run can be triggered against them.

**Inputs:**
- Character ID range
- Pose/expression ID range
- Camera angle selection (multi-select checkboxes)
- Camera perspective selection (multi-select checkboxes)
- Optional: reference frame ID for img2img seeding
- Optional: exclusion list of specific combinations (toggled in-UI)

**Outputs:**
- New rows inserted into the target entity table with `regenerate_images = 1` set
- Updated rows (force-update mode) with descriptions refreshed and `regenerate_images` reset to 1
- Frame-to-entity mappings written to the relevant junction table

---

## Key Features

**Combination preview with diff display**
Before committing, the operator clicks "Refresh Preview." The system queries `v_character_pose_angle_combinations` (or the equivalent Anima/expression view) and compares results against existing records, splitting output into two tables: NEW ENTRIES (insertable) and EXISTING ENTRIES (would update). Counts are shown as stats chips in the mid-panel toolbar.

**In-UI exclusion toggling**
Pose/expression name chips in the preview table are clickable. Clicking a chip marks that specific combination as excluded (visually struck through), and it is omitted from the next import run. Exclusions are tracked client-side as a `Set` of composite keys (`character_id_pose_id_angle_id_perspective_id`) and sent with each API call as JSON.

**Force update mode**
A sidebar checkbox enables `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE` behaviour, refreshing the `description` and `regenerate_images` fields on existing records rather than skipping them.

**img2img reference frame**
An optional frame ID can be entered in the sidebar. When provided, the frame''s filename is previewed inline (PhotoSwipe lightbox), and the `img2img_frame_id` and `img2img = 1` columns are populated on all inserted/updated records, directing the generation queue to use that frame as the img2img source.

**Prompt composition options**
Two checkboxes modify the generated `description` field:
- *Exclude Character Prompt* — uses `v.base_prompt` (pose + perspective + angle only) instead of the full `v.description` which appends the character''s own description
- *Use Neutral BG Prefix* — prepends a greenscreen background directive (`((neutral greenscreen background - Pantone: 354 C, Hex: #00FB00))`) to the prompt. For expressions specifically, this also prepends a facing-left directive.

**Paginated preview**
Preview results are paginated at 100 rows per page for both the NEW and EXISTING tables, with independent page controls for each. Pagination state is tracked in hidden form fields.

**Tab 2: Frame Mapping**
The second tab loads all imported poses/expressions for the filtered range into a scrollable left-panel list. The operator enters a map run ID to load its frames into a responsive grid on the right. Clicking a frame in the grid assigns it to the currently selected pose via `frames_2_character_poses` (or equivalent junction table) using a toggle — clicking the same frame again removes the link. On successful assignment, the pose list item updates its thumbnail in real time and auto-advances to the next pose in the list.

---

## Data Model

### Primary Tables Read/Written

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `character_poses` | Standard pose records (target for `import_character_poses.php`) |
| `character_anima_poses` | Anima pose records [VERIFY — table name inferred from code pattern] |
| `character_expressions` | Expression records |
| `frames` | Source of reference frames (img2img lookup; map run frame loading) |
| `frames_2_character_poses` | Junction: frame → pose mapping |
| `frames_2_character_anima_poses` | Junction: frame → Anima pose mapping |
| `frames_2_character_expressions` | Junction: frame → expression mapping |

### Key Views Used

| View | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `v_character_pose_angle_combinations` | Computes all valid character × pose × angle × perspective permutations with pre-assembled prompt strings |
| `v_character_anima_pose_angle_combinations` | Equivalent for Anima poses [VERIFY] |
| `v_character_expression_angle_combinations` | Equivalent for expressions [VERIFY] |
| `v_gallery_character_poses` | Joins frames → poses with style/character metadata for gallery display |
| `v_map_runs_character_poses` | Surfaces map run membership and active-run flag per pose |
| `v_prompts_character_poses` | Flat view of pose ID, prompt, negative prompt, seed, and `regenerate_images` flag — used by the generation queue |

### `character_poses` Schema Summary

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | int | PK, auto-increment |
| `character_id` | int | FK → `characters` |
| `pose_id` | int | FK → `poses` |
| `angle_id` | int | FK → `camera_angles` |
| `perspective_id` | int | FK → `camera_perspectives`, default 1 |
| `description` | text | Assembled AI prompt |
| `prompt_negative` | text | Negative prompt (nullable) |
| `seed` | int | Generation seed (nullable) |
| `regenerate_images` | tinyint(1) | Flag consumed by generation queue; set to 1 on import |
| `active_map_run_id` | int | Which map run is currently "active" for this pose |
| `img2img` | tinyint(1) | Whether to use img2img mode |
| `img2img_frame_id` | int | Source frame for img2img |
| `cnmap` | tinyint(1) | ControlNet map toggle |
| `cnmap_frame_id` | int | Source frame for CN map |

### `v_character_pose_angle_combinations` View Logic

Joins `characters × poses × camera_angles × camera_perspectives` and assembles two prompt fields:
- `base_prompt`: `((pose_description)), ((perspective_description)), ((angle_description))`
- `description`: same as base_prompt + character description appended

---

## API / Backend Integration

All three files are self-contained PHP AJAX handlers — no calls to the PyAPI (FastAPI) are made directly. Importing sets `regenerate_images = 1` on target records; the generation queue polls this flag independently.

### Internal AJAX Actions

| `api_action` | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `preview` | POST | Returns paginated new/existing row counts and data; does not write |
| `import` | POST | Executes INSERT (or INSERT … ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE); wraps in transaction |
| `get_frame_url` | GET | Returns filename for a given frame ID (reference image preview) |
| `get_poses_for_mapping` | POST | Returns imported pose list filtered by sidebar params for Tab 2 |
| `get_run_frames` | POST | Returns all frames belonging to a given map run ID |
| `map_frame` | POST | Toggles a frame↔pose link in the junction table |

No external AI provider calls are made from these modules. The downstream effect of setting `regenerate_images = 1` triggers the generation queue, which handles provider calls elsewhere.

---

## UI & Interaction

**Layout:** Full-viewport flexbox layout with a collapsible left sidebar (340px) and a main content area. On mobile (≤900px) the sidebar slides in as an overlay triggered by a hamburger button; button labels hide and icons-only mode activates.

**Sidebar sections:**
1. Camera Perspectives — checkbox chips (All / None quick-selects)
2. Camera Angles — checkbox chips (All / None quick-selects)
3. Character Range — numeric inputs for From/To ID
4. Import Options / Map Run Source — context-sensitive; shows import options on Tab 1, map run ID input on Tab 2

**Tab 1 — Import Combinations:**
- Mid-panel shows stats chips (Total / New / Existing) and pagination controls
- Grid area renders two `dark-table` panels: NEW ENTRIES (green header) and EXISTING ENTRIES (amber header)
- Description cells are truncated at 150 chars; clicking opens a full-text modal
- Existing entries show a 32×32 thumbnail of the most recently mapped frame
- PhotoSwipe 5.4.2 lightbox is initialised dynamically on each preview load

**Tab 2 — Map Frames:**
- Left panel: scrollable list of pose items with character name, pose/expression name, perspective, angle, and a 44×44 thumbnail
- Right panel: responsive CSS grid of frames (minmax 130px), each showing the frame ID badge overlay
- Clicking a pose selects it (purple/gold highlight + `active` class); clicking a frame assigns/unassigns it
- On successful assignment the pose thumbnail updates immediately; cursor auto-advances to the next pose

**Theming:**
- `import_character_poses.php` and `import_character_expressions.php`: purple (`#8b5cf6`) accent
- `import_character_anima_poses.php`: gold/amber (`#fbbf24`) accent to differentiate Anima content

**Debouncing:** Sidebar numeric inputs debounce at 400ms before triggering a reload. Checkbox changes trigger immediately.

---

## Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bootstrap.php` | PHP | Core SAGE bootstrap, PDO setup |
| `env_locals.php` | PHP | Environment-local config |
| `camera_angles` table | DB | Required for sidebar chip population on page load |
| `camera_perspectives` table | DB | Required for sidebar chip population on page load |
| `v_character_pose_angle_combinations` | DB View | Core combination source for Tab 1 |
| `frames` table | DB | Reference frame lookup; map run frame loading |
| PhotoSwipe 5.4.2 | CDN JS | Lightbox for frame and reference image preview |
| Bootstrap 5.3.0 | CDN CSS | Grid/utility base |
| `/css/base.css` | Local CSS | SAGE base styles |
| `gallery.php` template | PHP | Layout renderer (`$spw->renderLayout`) |

**Modules that feed into this one:**
- Map Run system — frame sets loaded by map run ID in Tab 2 originate from generation runs triggered elsewhere (e.g. the Enhanimaticism generation queue or VidBat pipeline)
- `poses` / `poses_anima` / `anivoc_expressions` tables — populated separately; these are the vocabulary these importers combine

**Modules this feeds into:**
- AI image generation queue — reads `regenerate_images = 1` and `v_prompts_character_poses`
- VidBat / Map Run viewer — consumes `frames_2_character_poses` mappings for run navigation
- Gallery views — `v_gallery_character_poses` joins the output of these importers for display

---

## Known State / Notes

- The three files share an identical UI and logic structure; only the target table, source combination view, junction table names, and accent colour differ. This is intentional parallelism, not duplication — each entity type has a distinct generation pipeline downstream.
- The `import_character_expressions.php` neutral BG prefix additionally includes `((character facing left)), ((looking left))` — a production convention for expression reference sheets that is not present in the pose equivalents.
- PhotoSwipe is re-initialised on every preview load and every map frame assignment. If PhotoSwipe `lightbox.destroy()` is called on a null reference on first load, it is safe (the null check `if (lightbox)` guards it).
- The `eruda` debug variable is appended to the output in `import_character_poses.php` and `import_character_anima_poses.php` (`$content.$eruda`) but **not** in `import_character_expressions.php` (`$content` only). [VERIFY — may be an oversight or intentional for the expressions module]
- `active_map_run_id` on `character_poses` tracks which map run''s frames are the "canonical" generation for that pose; this is set separately from the frame mapping done here.
- No server-side rate limiting or batch-size cap is applied to the import INSERT. Large character × pose × angle × perspective products (e.g. many characters × many poses × all angles × all perspectives) will produce very large single INSERT … SELECT statements. [VERIFY — confirm acceptable scale in production]
- The `force_update` checkbox triggers `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE` but relies on a unique key existing on `(character_id, pose_id, angle_id, perspective_id)`. [VERIFY — confirm unique/composite key constraint is defined on all three target tables]
