### API / Backend Integration

VidBat''s API is entirely **inline** — all `api_action` requests are handled within the same PHP file via an early `isset($_REQUEST[''api_action''])` block. There is no separate controller.

#### Inline API Endpoints (`?api_action=...`)

| Action | Method | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| `get_map_runs` | GET | Paginated map runs (3/page) with video count; filtered to `entity_type = ''animatics''` |
| `get_videos` | GET | All videos for a single `map_run_id` |
| `get_storyboards` | GET | Paginated storyboard list for filter tab |
| `get_videos_for_storyboard` | GET | Resolves videos from a storyboard''s entity chain (used by legacy/external callers) |
| `list_videos` | GET | Paginated 24/page with optional filters: `only_review`, `node_id`, `include_descendants`, `seq_id`, `fuzz_cand_id`, `storyboard_id` |
| `list_narrative_sequences` | GET | Paginated 20/page with search |
| `list_fuzz_candidates` | GET | Paginated 20/page with search; excludes rejected/promoted/canonized |
| `toggle_review_batch` | POST JSON | Sets `review` = 0 or 1 on array of video IDs |
| `tree_assign_batch` | POST JSON | `INSERT IGNORE` into `video_tree_items` for array of video IDs |
| `tree_unassign_batch` | POST JSON | `DELETE FROM video_tree_items` for array of video IDs |
| `tree_fetch` | GET | Full `video_tree_nodes` tree as jsTree-formatted JSON |
| `tree_create_node` | POST JSON | Insert new `video_tree_nodes` row |
| `tree_get_assignment` | GET | Returns `video_tree_items` + node name for a given `video_id` |

#### External API Calls

- **`video_admin_api.php`** — called client-side for `list_categories` and `list_playlists` (used to populate dropdowns in the Video Details modal context, not VidBat itself directly)
- **`view_video_details.php`** — loaded inside `modal_frame_details.php` iframe for rich video editing
- **PyAPI** — not called directly by VidBat; rembg jobs are queued to `video_enhancements` for the scheduler to pick up

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout

Two-column on desktop (≥ 900 px), single-column stacked on mobile:

- **Left column / top (mobile):** Video player (16:9, `aspect-ratio` enforced), info bar (name, ID, duration, size, flagged badge, assigned badge, progress track), action button row, Map Run panel or Filter Mode banner
- **Right column / bottom (mobile):** Batch toolbar (SEL mode, ALL/NONE, selected count, grid pagination, Auto checkbox), scrollable video grid

#### Video Grid

3-column `aspect-ratio: 16/9` thumbnail grid. Cards show the video ID in the bottom-left corner. Active card gets a white border; flagged cards get a green border + ★ star; selected cards (batch mode) get an accent-colour border + ✓ checkmark badge.

#### Map Run Panel

Fixed-height strip (126 px = exactly 3 × 42 px items) with a search input and numeric prev/next pagination. Each row shows run ID, note, and video count.

#### Filter Modal

Bottom sheet on mobile, centred on tablet/desktop. Four-tab layout: Tree (jsTree), Narratives (paginated list), Fuzz (searchable paginated list), Storyboard (searchable paginated list). "Browse All" and "Apply Filter" footer buttons. Filter state is shown in a strip between the header and the tab bar. Filter mode is indicated in the ⚙ button gaining an accent-colour glow, and a dismissible banner replaces the Map Run panel.

#### Assign Modal

Bottom sheet with current assignment strip, inline node creation toolbar (name + type + Add), jsTree, and "Assign to Selected Node" confirm button. Works on single video or batch selection.

#### Rembg / Color Sampler

Two layered modals (z-index 120010 / 120015). The sampler draws the video thumbnail to a `<canvas>` scaled to the modal''s actual pixel dimensions. Tap events average a 10-px radius circle of pixels and render a crosshair indicator. The sampled hex flows back to the rembg modal''s swatch and input.

#### Mobile-First Notes

- `100dvh` with `overflow: hidden` on the layout root
- `touch-action: none` on the sampler canvas, custom `touchend` listener for pixel sampling
- `-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent` on all interactive elements
- `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` padding on the grid section
- Space Mono / DM Mono / Fira Mono font stack (no Syne here — `[VERIFY]` whether intentional deviation from Forge UI spec)

