---

## 1. Introduction

The Documentation & MD Curator System is SAGE''s integrated knowledge-management layer, providing a full lifecycle pipeline for Markdown documents from authoring through AI-powered semantic analysis, lore extraction, and interactive exploration. It solves the challenge of turning raw narrative and worldbuilding text into structured, queryable production data — feeding the Knowledge Graph, Lore Explorer, and Chroma vector store directly from prose documents. Within the pipeline it sits between raw narrative writing and downstream vector search, image generation, and the Story Bible viewer, acting as the primary bridge between human-readable lore and machine-actionable entity data.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The system spans five tightly coupled concerns:

- **Document authoring and organisation** — create, edit, categorise, and import `.md` files via a Toast UI Editor interface.
- **Category management** — folder-style grouping of documents with inline AJAX CRUD.
- **AI extraction pipeline** — two-pass CLI curator that chunks documents and calls AI generators to extract lore entities (Pass 1: `md_curator_v1`) and showrunner/narrative data (Pass 2: `md_curator_showrunner_v1`), storing raw results in `md_doc_chunks`.
- **Aggregation pipeline** — assembles chunk results into the final `md_doc_analysis` row per document, building canonical entity lists, timeline events, episode concepts, narrative engine data, and an Automatic Graph (AG) in `ag_nodes` / `ag_node_items`.
- **Read / explore layer** — `view_md.php` (individual document reader with TOC, audio player, auto-scroll) and `view_curated_docs.php` (Showrunner Story Bible V9.6 viewer), plus `view_lore_explorer.php` (semantic search + focused lore export).

**Inputs:** Markdown text content (typed or uploaded), AI generator configs (`md_curator_v1`, `md_curator_showrunner_v1`), ChromaDB vector collections.

**Outputs:** Structured rows in `md_doc_analysis`, nodes in `ag_nodes`, semantic search results, downloadable JSON/Markdown lore exports, TTS audio via `audios_2_documentations`.

---

### Key Features

**Document Index (`view_md.php` — index mode)**

- Categorised, grouped document list with per-group headers.
- Client-side text filter backed by a debounced server search (`api_md.php?action=search`) across `name` and `content` fields.
- Category filter dropdown and sort selector (Created ↓/↑, Updated, Name A–Z/Z–A). Sort changes trigger a full page reload to re-run the SQL `ORDER BY`; category changes update URL state via `history.replaceState` without reload.
- Per-document audio regeneration checkbox (`regenerate_audios` field toggle via `api_md.php?action=toggle_audio`).
- Curated analysis indicator: documents with an `md_doc_analysis` row show a `📑` link to the Story Bible view instead of the plain `📄` icon.
- Markdown import modal: accepts `.md`, `.markdown`, `.txt` up to 5 MB; derives document name from filename; posts to `api_md.php?action=import_md`.
- TTS scheduler trigger button (fires `scheduler_view.php` for scheduler job ID 40).
- Logs modal (iframe overlay of `view_scheduler_log.php`).

**Document Reader (`view_md.php` — single document mode)**

- Parses Markdown with Parsedown and renders with `github-markdown-css` (light/dark CSS swap driven by `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and `MutationObserver`).
- Floating draggable TOC panel (auto-hidden when no headings detected); TOC filter input; paragraph anchor copy buttons (appended to every `<p>`).
- Floating draggable audio player: loads latest audio from `audios_2_documentations` join; bookmark save/restore via `localStorage`; ±10s transport buttons.
- Auto-scroll control widget (fixed bottom-right): speed slider, Start/Pause/Top buttons, keyboard shortcuts (`S` = start, `Space` = pause).
- Download as `.md` button (`?download=1`).
- All navigation links preserve `category_id` and `sort` query params for correct back-navigation.

**Document Editor (`edit_md.php`)**

- Toast UI Editor (CDN or local vendor; dark theme CSS toggled alongside app theme).
- Title input, category selector with inline "add category" prompt.
- Meta modal (✏️ button): long description textarea (Markdown), short description textarea, keywords input, target Chroma collection selector (collection names loaded from `chroma_collections` table via `api_md.php?action=get_chroma_collections`). Collection value stored as `target_collection` name string, not ID.
- Explicit "Done" confirmation pattern: meta changes are only written to the save payload if the user clicked "Done" in the modal; closing without Done cancels the edit.
- Save via `api_md.php?action=save` (upsert); new documents redirect to edit URL with new ID.
- Paste fix: intercepts `paste` events and calls `editor.insertText()` to strip rich formatting.

**Category Manager (`view_md_categories.php`)**

- Lists all categories with document counts (active docs only) and an "Uncategorized" row.
- Inline AJAX modal for create/edit (GET `?action=get_category`, POST `?action=save_category`).
- Delete with transaction: sets `category_id = NULL` on member documents, then deletes category row (POST `?action=delete_category`).
- Client-side search filter over category names.
- All category CRUD is handled inline in `view_md_categories.php` itself — no separate API file.

**API Layer (`api_md.php`)**

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `save` | POST JSON | Upsert document (content, description, desc\_short, keywords, target\_collection, category\_id) |
| `get` | GET | Fetch single document for editor |
| `delete` | POST JSON | Soft-delete (sets `is_active = 0`) |
| `toggle_audio` | POST JSON | Flip `regenerate_audios` flag |
| `create_category` | POST JSON | Insert new category (duplicate name check) |
| `get_categories` | GET | List all categories |
| `get_chroma_collections` | GET | List from `chroma_collections` table |
| `search` | GET `?q=` | Full-text LIKE search on `name` and `content`, returns matching `id` array |
| `get_tts_text` | GET | Parses Markdown → plain text for TTS consumption |
| `import_md` | POST multipart | Uploads `.md`/`.txt` file; derives name from filename |

**MD Curator Extract CLI (`cli_md_curator_extract_db.php`)**

- Two-pass, chunk-aware AI extraction.
- Chunking: splits content on Markdown headings (`#`) and paragraph boundaries to stay within `$charLimit` (default 4 000 chars).
- Pass 1 (Lore): calls `md_curator_v1` generator on raw chunk text → stores JSON in `md_doc_chunks.lore_raw`.
- Pass 2 (Showrunner): calls `md_curator_showrunner_v1` generator with rolling context (document global description + accumulated prior-chunk summaries) → stores JSON in `md_doc_chunks.show_raw`. The chunk summary is extracted from the raw response using a multi-strategy extractor (JSON parse → `find_summary_in_data` → `find_summary_in_raw` → regex fallback) and accumulated for the next chunk''s context window.
- Cached: chunks that already have both `lore_raw` and `show_raw` are skipped (`"."` progress indicator).
- Queue mode: `--qjobs=N` reads `forge_jobs` rows of type `md_curator_extract`; standalone mode accepts `--cat=`, `--limit=`, `--chars=`, `--model=`, `--config=<json>`, `--config-json=<inline>`.
- Controlled by `ONLY_DOCS_WITH_GLOBAL_SUMMARY` constant (default `true`): skips documents with no `description` field, requiring a pre-filled summary to provide context for chunk analysis.

**MD Curator Aggregate CLI (`cli_md_curator_aggregate_db.php`)**

- Reads all `md_doc_chunks` rows for a document and assembles one `md_doc_analysis` upsert.
- Entity merging: `merge_characters_canonical()` deduplicates characters by normalised name key (ASCII-translit, lowercase, strip titles); accumulates aliases, roles, descriptions, and `raw[]` chunk sources.
- Location, faction, artifact deduplication via `unique_objects_by_key()`.
- Lore point extraction via `get_key_insensitive()` with normalised alias key lookup for timeline events, tech/magic, lore rules, anima types, visual details, trade goods, population data.
- Showrunner aggregation: scene hooks (with `__src_chunk` tags), production notes (joined with `---` separators), narrative engine (`select_best_narrative()` picks highest `readiness_score`), episode concepts (`finalize_episode_concepts()` deduplicates by title, newest-chunk-wins), visual keywords.
- Readable series bible: assembled from narrative engine + plot outline snippets from raw lore + summary + episode concept list.
- Automatic Graph (AG) population: after `md_doc_analysis` upsert, wipes and rebuilds `ag_nodes` and `ag_node_items` for the document. Two passes: (1) build alias resolution map across all entities; (2) insert nodes with deep recursive Markdown content, extract explicit relationship edges, and scan entity description text for implicit alias mentions. Locked documents (`is_locked = 1`) are skipped.
- Queue mode: `--qjobs=N` reads `forge_jobs` rows of type `md_curator_aggregate`.

**Curated Story Bible Viewer (`view_curated_docs.php`)**

- Renders `md_doc_analysis` data as interactive "Showrunner V9.6" lore cards.
- Full JS-side entity aggregation mirroring the PHP `LoreAccessService` logic (Omni-Capture pattern: merges `raw[]` chunks, deduplicates relationships, builds timeline).
- Lore index: normalised key lookup enabling cross-entity deep-linking (`clickLink()`).
- Modal with navigation history (back/forward stack), entity detail renderer (attributes grid, relationship cards, timeline), curator view (bible text, production notes, themes).
- Visual sketch preview gallery (Swiper + PhotoSwipe) fetched via POST `?action=fetch_visuals` — looks up `sketch_lore_history` → `frames`/`frames_2_sketches` for the entity name.
- Sketch curation analysis modal (quality score, classification, themes, characters, score breakdown).
- JSON/Markdown download per entity category; clipboard copy of full card JSON.
- Embed mode (`?embed=1`): hides nav, expands card, adjusts modal to full-viewport — used by Lore Explorer iframe.
- Deep-link auto-open: `?doc_id=N&focus_entity=X&focus_type=Y` triggers `openModalFromGrid()` after 150 ms index build delay, with alias fallback scan.
- TTS integration via `mod_floating_tts.php` (excluded in embed mode).

**Lore Explorer (`view_lore_explorer.php` + `lore_explorer_api.php`)**

- Sticky search bar with collection selector; debounced `POST action=search` calls `PyApiVectorService` across selected (or all text) ChromaDB collections, then enriches hits with DB metadata.
- Result grid: hit cards showing entity name, match type, document reference, semantic snippet, relevance %.
- Click card → opens `view_curated_docs.php` in a full-page iframe modal with deep-link params; parent-side TTS speak-selection button that reads iframe selection or marked text.
- **Lore Export Modal** (📤 Export button):
  - Semantic query field: calls `lore_semantic_query` action (same vector path as main search, with hit deduplication and DB enrichment).
  - Hit list with checkbox selection; auto-selects hits scoring > 0.35; "Toggle all" button.
  - `with_content` toggle: structural export (attribute keys only) vs full entity content.
  - Export fires `lore_focused_export` action → `LoreAccessService::loadDoc()` per document → extracts matched entities by name/alias → returns focused JSON snapshot.
  - Client-side download as `lore_semantic_[suffix]_[date].json`.

**`LoreAccessService` (PHP service)**

- `loadDoc(int $docId)`: decodes all four JSON columns, merges lore points into entity categories, structures `$raw` array, calls `processEntities()`.
- `processEntities()`: iterates world categories, calls `aggregateSingleEntity()` per item, builds `$index` (name + alias keys), builds `$aggregated` (keyed by category).
- `aggregateSingleEntity()`: Omni-Capture — extracts attributes, aliases, roles, relationships, timeline from top-level fields and from every `raw[]` chunk; deduplicates aliases/roles.
- Public: `queryEntities($category, $roleFilter)`, `getEntity($name)` (alias-aware), `buildAgentContext($entityName)`, `getStoryEngine()`, `getCuratorData()`, `getWorldData()`.

**`api_lore.php`**

Lightweight GET API over `LoreAccessService`:

| Mode | Description |
|---|---|
| `entity` | Single entity lookup by `?query=` name |
| `context` | `buildAgentContext()` for AI context injection |
| `category` | `queryEntities()` with optional `?role=` filter |
| `story` | `getStoryEngine()` data |
| `full` | (Warning: large) story + category skeleton |

**CLI Forge Hub (`cli_forge.php`)**

- Unified hub UI that includes Extract and Aggregate as two of its ten sub-views (`view-extract`, `view-aggregate`).
- Each sub-view has Configure / JSON Preview / Queue tabs.
- Queue management: `queue_job`, `queue_list`, `cancel_job`, `delete_job`, `requeue_job`, `set_priority` AJAX actions against `forge_jobs` table.
- `curator_meta` action returns category list and generator config titles for the fixed-config display chips.
- Bottom bar updates per active view/panel: Config → Preview JSON + Refresh + Queue Job; JSON → Copy + Download + Queue Job; Queue → Refresh + Back to Config.

