### Data Model

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `documentations` | Primary document store. Key fields: `name`, `content` (longtext), `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `category_id`, `target_collection` (collection name string), `is_active`, `regenerate_audios`, `type` (default `''md''`) |
| `documentation_categories` | Simple name-only categories |
| `md_doc_chunks` | Raw AI responses per document chunk. `UNIQUE(doc_id, chunk_index)`. Fields: `lore_raw`, `show_raw` |
| `md_doc_analysis` | One row per document. Holds assembled JSON for `entities`, `lore_points`, `thematics`, `showrunner_analysis`, `series_bible`, `summary`, `narrative_utility` (float), `target_collection`, `generator_config_id`, `is_locked` |
| `chroma_collections` | Registry of ChromaDB collection names and types used by the collection selector dropdowns |
| `ag_nodes` | Automatic Graph nodes — one per entity per document. Fields: `name`, `node_type`, `content` (recursive Markdown), `doc_id` |
| `ag_node_items` | Graph edges. Fields: `node_id`, `item_type`, `item_id` (nullable — if target node exists), `item_label`, `relationship`, `note`, `doc_id` |
| `forge_jobs` | Queue table for CLI pipeline jobs. Fields: `job_type` (e.g. `''md_curator_extract''`), `status`, `priority`, `payload` (JSON), `label`, `error_msg`, timestamps |
| `audios_2_documentations` | Join table linking generated audio files to documents (`from_id` = audio, `to_id` = document) |
| `sketch_lore_history` | Links sketch IDs to `(doc_id, entity_type, entity_name)` for visual gallery lookup |
| `frames` / `frames_2_sketches` / `sketches` | Image frame and sketch data used by the visual gallery in the Story Bible viewer |
| `generator_config` | AI generator configs. `md_curator_v1` (ID 77, semantic miner, temp 0.1) and `md_curator_showrunner_v1` (ID 78, showrunner/narrative, temp 0.4) drive the extraction pipeline |

**ChromaDB:** Documents are chunked and their extracted entity text is embedded into the collection named in `documentations.target_collection` (or `md_doc_analysis.target_collection`). The Lore Explorer and `lore_semantic_query` query these collections via `PyApiVectorService`.

---

### API / Backend Integration

**PyAPI (FastAPI) — `PyApiVectorService`**

- Called by `lore_explorer_api.php` (`search`, `lore_semantic_query`) and by the KG/Lore Forge pipelines.
- Endpoint: `query($query, null, $collectionName, ''text'', $nResults)` → Chroma `query` call returning `ids`, `metadatas`, `documents`, `distances`.
- Metadata field `db_id` is used to map Chroma hits back to `documentations.id`.
- Base URL from env: `WORDNET_PYAPI_URL` (default `http://127.0.0.1:8009`).

**AI Providers**

- `md_curator_v1`: model `claude-fast` (mapped by `SpwBase::getAIProvider()`). System role: "Semantic Database Extraction Engine". Generates entity/lore JSON at temperature 0.1, max 10 000 tokens.
- `md_curator_showrunner_v1`: model `claude-fast`. System role: "Showrunner and Lead Writer". Generates narrative/episode/visual JSON at temperature 0.4, max 10 000 tokens; includes `chunk_summary` field used for rolling context injection.

**Scheduler**

- Scheduler job ID `40` is the TTS regeneration job, triggered from the document index view via POST to `scheduler_view.php?action=run_now`.

