### Data Model

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `mail_hub_newsletters` | Campaign records (content, status, send counters) |
| `mail_hub_providers` | Mail provider configurations and daily-limit state |
| `mail_hub_queue` | Active per-recipient send jobs |
| `mail_hub_queue_archive` | Completed/failed jobs moved out of the live queue |
| `mail_hub_events` | Delivery and engagement event log |
| `mail_hub_lists` | Subscriber list groupings (local; used as filter for Brevo queries) |
| `mail_hub_unsubscribe_tokens` | One-click unsubscribe token store |

**Note:** There is no local `mail_hub_subscribers` table. Subscriber data lives entirely in Brevo. The `subscriber_id` columns in queue/event tables hold Brevo contact IDs (integers), not local records. A `mail_hub_list_subscribers` join table is referenced in `getLists()` for subscriber counts but its DDL was not included in this dump — likely a local list membership table. `[VERIFY]`

#### Key table fields

**`mail_hub_newsletters`**

| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| `status` | `enum(''draft'',''scheduled'',''sending'',''sent'',''cancelled'',''failed'')` |
| `template_id` | FK → `mail_hub_templates` (not in schema dump — `[VERIFY]` table exists) |
| `list_id` | FK → `mail_hub_lists`; NULL = all active Brevo subscribers |
| `provider_id` | FK → `mail_hub_providers`; NULL = use default |
| `total_recipients` | Set at enqueue time |
| `total_sent` / `total_failed` | Incremented during batch processing |
| `preview_text` | Rendered as an invisible preheader spacer in the email HTML |

**`mail_hub_providers`**

| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| `driver` | `brevo` or `smtp` |
| `config` | JSON blob (api_key / host+port+username+password) |
| `daily_limit` | NULL = unlimited |
| `sent_today` | Incremented per successful send; reset daily |
| `last_reset` | Date of last `sent_today` zero; triggers reset when != today |

**`mail_hub_queue`**

| Column | Notes |
|---|---|
| `subscriber_id` | Brevo contact ID (not a local FK) |
| `status` | `pending → processing → sent / failed / skipped` |
| `priority` | Higher = processed first |
| `attempts` / `max_attempts` | Retry tracking (default max 3) |
| `provider_msg_id` | Message ID returned by provider on success |

**`mail_hub_events`** — event_type enum: `queued`, `attempt`, `sent`, `failed`, `opened`, `clicked`, `bounced`, `complained`, `unsubscribed`. `opened`/`clicked`/`bounced`/`complained` event types are defined in the schema but no webhook receiver to populate them is evidenced in the dump. `[VERIFY]`

