### API / Backend Integration

All frontend communication goes through `public/mail_hub/api.php` via POST JSON. No PyAPI (FastAPI) integration — the Mail Hub is a pure PHP/MariaDB module.

#### API Actions

| Action | Description |
|---|---|
| `get_stats` | Dashboard summary (newsletter counts, 7-day sent, Brevo subscriber count, pending queue) |
| `list_newsletters` | Paginated newsletter list with status/search filters |
| `get_newsletter` | Single newsletter by ID |
| `save_newsletter` | Create or update newsletter |
| `delete_newsletter` | Delete (draft/cancelled only) |
| `duplicate_newsletter` | Clone to new draft |
| `enqueue_newsletter` | Fetch Brevo subscribers → populate queue → set status to `sending` |
| `list_templates` | All templates (name + timestamps only) |
| `get_template` | Single template with body content |
| `save_template` | Create or update template |
| `delete_template` | Delete and NULL linked newsletters |
| `get_queue` | Paginated queue or archive rows |
| `archive_queue` | Move sent/failed rows to archive for a given newsletter |
| `process_batch` | Trigger a send batch (used by scheduler) |
| `list_subscribers` | Live-fetch paginated contacts from Brevo API |
| `list_lists` | Local list records |
| `list_providers` | All configured providers |
| `save_provider` | Create or update provider |
| `delete_provider` | Remove provider |
| `test_provider` | Save provider config, fire a test email to a given address |

#### External API calls

| Service | Endpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Brevo API v3 | `GET /contacts` | List subscribers (dashboard stats + subscriber view) |
| Brevo API v3 | `GET /contacts/{id}` | JIT contact fetch during batch processing |
| Brevo API v3 | `GET /contacts/lists/{id}/contacts` | Filtered recipient resolution |
| Brevo API v3 | `POST /smtp/email` | Transactional email send (BrevoProvider) |
| Brevo API v3 | `PUT /contacts/{id}` | Set `emailBlacklisted: true` on unsubscribe |

Brevo API key is stored in `mail_hub_providers.config` JSON; retrieved at runtime via `getBrevoKey()` which queries for the first enabled Brevo provider. The SMTP driver uses raw PHP `fsockopen()` socket connections with manual STARTTLS negotiation — no Composer dependency, suitable for the Termux environment.

#### Scheduler integration

`processBatch()` is exposed via `process_batch` API action, designed to be called by a SAGE scheduler job. The scheduler triggers batch processing on a recurring interval; the Mail Hub respects `scheduled_at` on queue items and daily provider limits automatically. No explicit scheduler job wiring is visible in this dump — `[VERIFY]` scheduler configuration.

