### UI & Interaction

**Layout:** Fixed-height viewport with a sticky header containing the SAGE logo, tab navigation, and a refresh button. Scrollable main body below. Full Forge Design System styling (Space Mono + Syne, amber accents, dark/light theme).

**Tab views:** Dashboard, Newsletters, Templates, Subscribers, Providers — single-page app with JavaScript view switching (no page reloads).

**Mobile nav:** On screens ≤ 720px, the desktop tab row is hidden and replaced by a fixed bottom navigation bar with icon+label tabs. The main body adds 80px bottom padding to avoid content hidden behind the nav bar. The Providers tab is absent from the mobile bottom nav (only Dashboard, Newsletters, Templates, Subscribers) — `[VERIFY]` intentional omission.

**Modals:** Newsletter editor, Template editor, Provider editor, and Send confirmation (enqueue). All modals use backdrop-click-to-close and animate in with `fadeUp`. The newsletter and template modals contain dual-tab editors (HTML / Plain Text) with shared `switchBodyTab()` logic.

**Toast notifications:** Fixed bottom-right toast stack with success (green border), error (red border), and info states. Auto-dismiss after 3 seconds; click-to-dismiss.

**Send progress:** Displayed inline in newsletter rows as a text fraction (`sent / total`) plus a CSS fill bar. Shown in both the Dashboard recent campaigns table and the full Newsletters table.

**Loading states:** Spinner placeholders in table bodies while API calls are in flight.

**Responsive columns:** Several table columns use `hide-md` and `hide-sm` CSS classes to collapse gracefully on smaller screens.

