- **`nl-reply-to` field** is referenced in `saveNewsletter()` JS (`el(''nl-reply-to'').value`) but there is no corresponding `<input id="nl-reply-to">` in the modal HTML. The value will always be empty string on save. `[VERIFY]` / likely an oversight in the modal HTML.
- **`process_batch` response** — the `total_recipients` comment in the `getNewsletters()` response refers to `pages` being returned but `getNewsletters()` does not set a `pages` key explicitly (only `total` and `page`). The JS computes `nlTotalPages` from `r.data.pages || 1` which would always fall back to 1 unless `pages` is added. `[VERIFY]` / likely a minor bug.
- **Brevo subscriber count on dashboard** — calls `GET /contacts?limit=1&offset=0` and reads `count` from the response. This is a live API call on every dashboard load with no caching.
- **SMTP driver** — uses a pure PHP socket implementation with no Composer dependency. Tested against port 587 (STARTTLS) and 465 (SSL). Port 25 is listed in the UI but STARTTLS is not attempted for it. For Termux environments where `sendmail` is unavailable, this is the intended approach.
- **No local email address storage** is by design — the zero-PII architecture means subscriber emails are never written to the SAGE database. The `subscriber_id` stored in queue rows is the Brevo numeric contact ID.
