**File:** `sage_module_content_hub.md`
**Source:** `public/content_hub/index.php`, `public/content_hub/api.php`, `src/ContentHub/ContentHubManager.php`

---

## 1. Introduction

The Content Hub is SAGE''s social media command centre — a full-stack post planning, scheduling, and publishing system that manages the outward-facing life of *The Anima Chronicles* content across multiple platforms. It solves the problem of coordinating the release of production assets (frames, videos, storyboards) as polished, platform-ready social posts without leaving the SAGE environment. Posts are authored inside the Hub, enriched with platform metadata and attached media from the existing SAGE asset library, then exported as self-contained static HTML files and rolled out directly to a GitHub Pages repository via an automated git-sync job. The module sits at the downstream end of the production pipeline — after frames are rendered, reviewed, and catalogued — and serves as the public-facing broadcast layer of the SAGE platform.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Content Hub manages the full lifecycle of a content post: creation, metadata authoring, asset attachment, scheduling, static HTML generation, and GitHub rollout. It is the publishing gateway through which production assets produced by other SAGE modules (Enhanimaticism map runs, storyboards, video renders) are packaged into audience-facing pages.

**Pipeline position:** Downstream of asset production modules → upstream of GitHub Pages / social distribution.

**Inputs:**
- Frames sourced from `map_runs` or `storyboards` tables
- Videos sourced from the `videos` table
- Post metadata entered via the Hub UI (title, caption, platforms, schedule date, hashtags, post type)
- HTML post templates from `templates/post_detail_*.html`
- Magazine series data from `cinemagic_series` (for grid landing page)

**Outputs:**
- Rendered static HTML post pages (per post type)
- Sidecar JavaScript data files (`data_{id}.js`) for complex post types
- ZIP export archives (individual post or full batch)
- `index.html` grid landing page
- Git-sync jobs enqueued in `forge_jobs` for GitHub Pages deployment

---

### Key Features

#### Dashboard View
- **Stats cards** — total posts, by-status counts (draft / scheduled / published / archived), and a per-platform distribution bar chart drawn from live DB queries.
- **Mini content calendar** — month-grid view with coloured dots per post derived from `scheduled_at` or `created_at`. Supports month navigation and day-click to open a day view modal listing that day''s posts.
- **Upcoming posts panel** — lists the next 5 scheduled posts with thumbnail, date, platform badges, and per-row action buttons (rollout, HTML download, ZIP export).

#### All Posts View
- Filterable list of all posts by platform and status.
- Per-row actions: edit, delete, rollout to GitHub, download HTML, download ZIP.
- Global topbar search field drives post filtering (debounced, 300 ms).

#### Post Editor Modal
- Fields: title, status, post type, scheduled date, sort order, platform checkboxes (multi-select), preview image URL, asset URL prefix, caption/content, attached assets (ordered), hashtags.
- **Asset picker bottom sheet** — three-tab picker (Map Runs, Storyboards, Videos) with paginated container list and per-container frame/video grid. Supports multi-select for media and single-select for preview image. Assets show preview and selection checkmark overlays.
- **Drag-to-reorder** for attached assets — both desktop DnD and mobile touch drag supported via the `initAttachedAssetsSortable()` function.
- Asset URL prefix field: when set, all asset paths in export/rollout are prefixed with the specified CDN/base URL.

#### Post Types

Ten distinct post type templates are supported:

| Post Type | Template | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `image_grid` | `post_detail_image_grid.html` | PhotoSwipe lightbox grid |
| `image_swiper` | `post_detail_image_swiper.html` | Swiper.js carousel + PhotoSwipe |
| `video_playlist` | `post_detail_video_playlist.html` | Video.js player with playlist |
| `youtube_playlist` | `post_detail_youtube_playlist.html` | Embedded YouTube iframe |
| `url_reference` | `post_detail_url_reference.html` | Meta-redirect pass-through |
| `scrollmagic_gallery` | `post_detail_scrollmagic_gallery.html` | Batched scroll-reveal image feed with IntersectionObserver and lightbox |
| `cinematic_story` | `post_detail_cinematic_story.html` | Fullscreen anime.js storyboard viewer with dual-plane crossfade, per-frame analysis panel, and swipe navigation |
| `anime_gallery` | `post_detail_anime_gallery.html` | Scroll-animated location-grouped gallery with video interspersing |
| `narrative_gallery` | `post_detail_narrative_gallery.html` | Scroll-threaded split-layout sequence viewer with ambient background and per-beat intel cards |
| `spatial_viewer` | `post_detail_spatial_viewer.html` | 3D scroll-driven frame carousel with matrix analysis overlay |

#### Data Enrichment for Complex Post Types

For `cinematic_story`, `anime_gallery`, `narrative_gallery`, and `spatial_viewer`, `ContentHubManager` performs additional database lookups at export/render time to enrich each frame with:
- Entity resolution — joins `frames` → `entity_type` / `entity_id` → entity name/description from the relevant entity table (characters, locations, sketches, etc.).
- Sketch analysis — joins `sketch_analysis` for classification, thematics, entities, recommendations, and scoring data.
- This enriched payload is serialised as a JavaScript data variable and either injected inline (live/preview mode) or written as a sidecar `.js` file (static export/rollout mode).

#### Export Modes

| Action | Output |
|---|---|
| **Preview Grid** (`preview_grid`) | Renders `index.html` inline; no download |
| **Download Grid HTML** (`export_grid`) | Downloads `index.html` |
| **Download HTML Only** (`export_post_html`) | Downloads single `{slug}.html` |
| **Export Post ZIP** (`export_post_zip`) | Downloads ZIP containing HTML + all local asset files |
| **Download All HTML** (`export_all_html`) | Downloads ZIP of full site: grid + all post HTMLs + sidecar JS files |

#### GitHub Rollout

The rollout flow (`rolloutPost`):
1. Writes the grid `index.html` and the post''s `{slug}.html` to the local git repository at `GITPAGES_REPO_PATH`.
2. Writes sidecar data JS for complex post types.
3. Copies post asset files from `public/content_hub/posts/post{id}/` to the repo.
4. Inserts a `github_sync` job into `forge_jobs` with `add_all`, `commit`, and `push` flags — picked up by the Forge scheduler.

#### Asset Copy-on-Save

When a post is saved with local (non-CDN) asset paths, `ContentHubManager::savePost()` copies the referenced files into a per-post subdirectory at `public/content_hub/posts/post{id}/` and rewrites the `media_items` JSON to point to the new paths (preserving `original_src` fields). Video thumbnails are copied into a `thumbnails/` sub-folder within the post directory.

---

### Data Model

**Primary table:** `content_hub_posts`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `int` AUTO_INCREMENT | Primary key |
| `title` | `varchar(255)` | Post title |
| `slug` | `varchar(255)` UNIQUE | URL-safe slug (auto-generated, deduped) |
| `post_type` | `enum` | One of the 10 post types listed above |
| `status` | `enum` | `draft`, `scheduled`, `published`, `archived` |
| `platform` | `varchar(64)` | Legacy single-platform column |
| `platforms_json` | `text` | JSON array of platform names (multi-platform) |
| `preview_image_url` | `varchar(512)` | Path or URL to thumbnail |
| `content` | `text` | Caption / body copy |
| `hashtags` | `text` | Hashtag string |
| `media_items` | `longtext` | JSON array of asset objects (`src`, `alt`, `id`, `thumb`, etc.) — must be valid JSON |
| `sort_order` | `int` | Manual ordering; used in descending sort |
| `scheduled_at` | `datetime` | Scheduled publish time |
| `published_at` | `datetime` | Set when status transitions to `published` |
| `notes` | `text` | Internal notes |
| `asset_url_prefix` | `varchar(512)` | CDN base URL prepended to local asset paths at export |
| `external_post_id` | `varchar(255)` | Reserved for platform post IDs post-publish |
| `created_at` / `updated_at` | `timestamp` | Auto-managed |

**Indexes:** `idx_status`, `idx_platform`, `idx_scheduled`, `idx_sort`, `idx_status_platform`

**Read tables (asset browsing):**
- `map_runs` — container listing for frame picker
- `storyboards`, `storyboard_frames` — storyboard container + frame listing
- `frames` — frame records with `map_run_id`, `filename`, `entity_type`, `entity_id`
- `videos` — video records with `url`, `thumbnail`, `map_run_id`

**Read tables (data enrichment):**
- `frames` — entity type/ID resolution
- `sketches`, `characters`, `locations`, `spawns`, `generatives`, `animas`, `artifacts`, `lotations`, `character_poses`, `character_anima_poses`, `character_expressions` — entity name/description lookup
- `sketch_analysis` — per-sketch AI curation data

**Read tables (grid export):**
- `cinemagic_series` — published magazine series cards on the landing page
- `cinemagic_series_2_cinemagics`, `cinemagics_2_sequences` — season/episode counts
- `system_languages` — multi-language support for the grid landing page

**Write tables:**
- `content_hub_posts` — all CRUD
- `forge_jobs` — rollout job insertion

---

### API / Backend Integration

All API interactions are handled by `public/content_hub/api.php`, which dispatches to `ContentHubManager` methods.

**JSON endpoints (POST):**

| `action` | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `get_stats` | `getDashboardStats()` | Post counts by status, platform distribution, asset counts |
| `get_calendar` | `getCalendarData(year, month)` | Posts grouped by date for calendar rendering |
| `get_posts` | `getPosts(filters)` | Paginated post list with platform/status/search filters |
| `get_post` | `getPostById(id)` | Single post record |
| `save_post` | `savePost(data)` | Create or update post + asset copy-on-save |
| `delete_post` | `deletePost(id)` | Delete record + remove post asset directory |
| `update_status` | `updatePostStatus(id, status)` | Quick status change |
| `get_assets` | `searchAssets(type, q, mapRunId)` | Video or sketch asset search |
| `search_containers` | `searchContainers(type, q, page)` | Paginated map run / storyboard / animatics container list |
| `get_container_frames` | `getContainerFrames(type, id)` | Frames for a selected container |
| `rollout_post` | `rolloutPost(id)` | Write files to git repo + enqueue `forge_jobs` sync job |

**File download endpoints (GET):**

| `action` | Output |
|---|---|
| `preview_grid` | Inline HTML — grid landing page preview |
| `preview_post` | Inline HTML — single post preview |
| `export_grid` | Download `index.html` |
| `export_post_html` | Download `{slug}.html` |
| `export_post_zip` | Download ZIP (HTML + assets) |
| `export_all_html` | Download ZIP (full site) |

**External dependencies (frontend templates only — no server-side calls):**
- `anime.js` v3.2.1 (CDN) — cinematic_story, anime_gallery, narrative_gallery, spatial_viewer templates
- `PhotoSwipe` v5.4.4 (CDN) — image_grid, image_swiper templates
- `Swiper` v9 (CDN) — image_swiper template
- `Video.js` v8.23.3 (CDN) — video_playlist template
- `Tailwind CSS` (CDN) — spatial_viewer template
- `Font Awesome` v6.4 (CDN) — spatial_viewer template
- Google Fonts (Cinzel, Lora, Inter, Playfair Display, Syncopate) — grid and post templates
- Google Analytics (`G-SBSTRVS0NR`) — injected into static export/rollout output only

**Forge integration:**
- Rollout enqueues a `github_sync` job in `forge_jobs`. Git identity (`GIT_BOT_NAME`, `GIT_BOT_EMAIL`) and repo path (`GITPAGES_REPO_PATH`) are read from environment variables.

---

### UI & Interaction

**Layout:** Two-panel desktop layout (220 px sidebar + main content area) with a sticky 52 px topbar. Mobile collapses to a bottom tab bar (Dashboard / Posts) with the sidebar hidden.

**Sidebar navigation:**
- Dashboard and All Posts views
- Platform filter pills (Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, Twitter/X, Facebook, Website) — clicking a pill switches to the Posts view filtered by that platform.

**Dashboard:**
- Four stat cards (total, draft, scheduled, published) with coloured top-accent strips.
- Mini calendar (7-col grid, colour-coded dots per post, month navigation).
- Upcoming posts list (5 items max, with rollout / HTML download / ZIP export actions inline).
- Platform distribution bar (proportional coloured segments with legend).

**All Posts view:**
- Platform and status dropdowns for filtering; global topbar search drives a hidden `_postSearchValue` state variable.
- Post rows show thumbnail, title, status badge, platform badges, post type label, date, sort order, and action button cluster.

**Post editor modal:**
- Standard modal overlay with `open` class toggle and backdrop click to dismiss.
