### UI & Interaction

**Main View (`fuzz_forge.php`)**
Sticky header with candidate count, pending count, extraction job button, stats button, and new candidate button. Three collapsible data panels (Pending, Resolved, Rejected) each containing a sortable paginated table. Filter toolbar with full-text search input and concept-type filter chips (All, Character, Location, Faction, Artifact, Concept, Event). Table columns are click-sortable with tri-state cycling (asc → desc → unsorted). Panel open/close state and left-pane section collapse state are persisted to `localStorage` under key `fuzz_forge_ui_state`.

**Deep Dive Dossier Modal**
Full-viewport overlay with a split workspace. Left pane sections (Identity, Aliases, KG Node Resolution, Notes) are individually collapsible with state saved to `localStorage`. Right pane tab state is not persisted between sessions. The Frames tab shows a selection mode: each frame card has a clickable label bar that toggles selection; "Remove Selected" bulk-deletes all `fuzz_mentions` for the selected frames'' source entities.

**Extraction Job Modal**
Two-phase UI. Phase 1 shows source table checkboxes and configuration sliders. Once submitted, Phase 2 shows a job panel with job ID, progress bar, a streaming log box, and (when clustering completes) an "Apply Clusters" action button. A local ingest progress bar replaces the apply button once ingestion begins. Job state is persisted in `localStorage` (`fuzzforge_ext_job`, `fuzzforge_ingest_job`) so polling resumes automatically on modal re-open.

**Fuzz Graph (`fuzzgraph.php`)**
Full-viewport Sigma.js canvas with two draggable floating panels (Graph Controls, Node Detail). Graph Controls panel contains a ForceAtlas2 toggle, camera reset, node search, hop depth selector (1 or 2), node/edge stats, and a colour legend. Node Detail panel shows node name, type badge, metadata rows (confidence bar, status, source info), and contextual action buttons. Node drag is disambiguated from node tap via a 6px movement threshold. Dark/light theme is applied to label and edge label colours via a `MutationObserver` on `data-theme`.

**Entity Form Integration**
Both the Forge and the Landing page open entity deep-dives in a bottom-sheet modal iframe pointing to `/entity_form.php?entity_type=...&entity_id=...&view=modal`. Sketch-derived tables (`sketch_analysis`, `sketch_ingredients`, `sketch_lore_history`) are automatically remapped to `sketches` as the root entity type.

**Mobile / Responsive**
Viewport scale is set to `0.7` in `fuzz_forge.php` and `0.9` in `fuzz_forge_landing.php`. The dossier workspace switches from side-by-side to stacked layout at 900px. The Fuzz Graph uses `viewport-fit=cover` at `scale=0.85`. The landing page uses `overflow-x: auto` on the mention list header to handle narrow screens.

**Theme**
Follows Forge UI design system: Space Mono / DM Mono + Bebas Neue + Barlow Condensed. CSS custom properties set in `:root` with full `[data-theme="light"]` overrides. Theme is read from `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and applied before first paint via an inline script. Scanline overlay is suppressed in light mode.

---

