**File:** `sage_module_forge_tool.md`
**Source files:** `public/forge_tool.php`, `public/clipboard_manager.php`, `public/scheduler_runner.php`
**Last documented:** 2026-05-26

---

## 1. Introduction

The Forge Tool is SAGE AI''s persistent, platform-wide developer console — an Eruda-inspired floating action button (FAB) that injects a resizable bottom-sheet panel into any view across the entire platform via a single `require ''forge_tool.php''` in the shared layout. From this panel, three utilities are immediately accessible from anywhere in SAGE: a scoped clipboard manager for storing and retrieving production text clips; a configurable shortcuts grid for one-tap navigation to any SAGE module; and a settings panel for customising both. The Clipboard Manager (`clipboard_manager.php`) provides the backend API and standalone page that powers clipboard storage, with full support for per-area scoping, pinning, and drag-to-reorder. The Control Deck (`scheduler_runner.php`) is the task execution hub — a curated grid of pre-configured "wrapper" buttons that trigger backend shell scripts on demand, paired with a live log console for monitoring output in real time. Together these three components form SAGE''s cross-module productivity layer: clips, shortcuts, and task launchers are always one tap away regardless of which module is currently active.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

The Forge Tool solves a recurring friction point in a single-developer, multi-module platform: context-switching overhead. Rather than navigating away to retrieve a stored prompt, open a secondary tool, or fire a generation task, the panel is available from any SAGE view. The Clipboard Manager independently serves as a full standalone page usable directly (e.g. loaded in a browser tab or embedded iframe) as well as a JSON API consumed by the Forge Tool panel and any other SAGE view that needs clipboard access. The Control Deck provides a curated, opinionated surface over the raw `scheduled_tasks` table — wrapping frequently-used task/argument combinations into named, icon-labelled buttons that are faster to use than the full scheduler interface.

**Inputs:** User-typed text clips; settings JSON (shortcuts list, custom tab URLs, panel height, clipboard scope); clipboard CRUD requests; wrapper run/save/delete requests; log file read requests.

**Outputs:** Persisted clipboard items (MariaDB); saved Forge Tool settings (MariaDB); wrapper mutations and task triggers (MariaDB `scheduled_tasks.run_now = 1`); log file content streamed from filesystem; system clipboard write via Web Clipboard API.

---

### Key Features

#### Forge Tool (`forge_tool.php`)

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Floating FAB** | Fixed-position draggable button (`⚗` icon). Position persists across page loads via `localStorage`. Tap to toggle panel; drag to reposition. Amber glow pulse animation when panel is open. |
| **Bottom-sheet panel** | Slides up from the bottom of the viewport. Resizable by dragging the top handle bar. Height range: 25–95 `vh`. Default 72 `vh`. Saved to `localStorage` and MariaDB. |
| **Clipboard tab** | Live clipboard view for the active `view_area`. Supports add, inline edit, pin/unpin, delete, drag-to-reorder, and one-tap copy. FAB badge shows item count. |
| **Shortcuts tab** | 4-column (5-column on ≥480px) icon grid. Clicking navigates to the shortcut URL or opens it in a modal/fullscreen overlay depending on per-shortcut settings. |
| **Fullscreen shortcut modal** | Full-viewport overlay loading a SAGE view in an `<iframe>`. Includes `>>` (open in new tab) and `✕` close buttons. Escape key closes. |
| **Settings tab** | Manage shortcuts (add, edit, reorder, show/hide, delete), manage custom iframe tabs, set panel height slider, set clipboard `view_area` scope. Persists to MariaDB on save. |
| **Custom iframe tabs** | User-defined tabs that load any SAGE URL inside the panel. Lazy-loads iframe `src` on first activation. Tabs appear in the tab bar alongside the three built-in tabs. |
| **SortableJS integration** | Clipboard items and shortcut list rows are drag-to-reorder via SortableJS (lazy-loaded from CDN). |
| **Theme support** | Responds to `[data-theme="light"]` on `<html>` via CSS variable overrides, matching the platform-wide Forge UI theme toggle. |
| **Toast notifications** | Lightweight fixed toast for action confirmations and errors. Auto-dismisses after 2 seconds. |
| **`postMessage` listener** | Listens for `{ type: ''clipboard_updated'' }` messages from child iframes so the clipboard tab reloads when clips are modified in an embedded view. |

**Default shortcuts pre-loaded (if no saved settings exist):**

| Icon | Label | URL | Mode |
