### Data Model

#### Tables

**`clipboard_items`** — canonical clip store

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INT` PK AUTO | |
| `content` | `TEXT` | Required. Max ~4000 chars enforced in UI |
| `label` | `VARCHAR` | Optional display label |
| `created_at` | `DATETIME` | Auto-set |
| `updated_at` | `DATETIME` | Updated on `cb_update` |

**`clipboard_visibility`** — per-area pin and order state

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INT` PK AUTO | |
| `clipboard_item_id` | `INT` FK | → `clipboard_items.id` (CASCADE DELETE) |
| `view_area` | `VARCHAR` | Scoping key, e.g. `global` |
| `pinned` | `TINYINT(1)` | 0 or 1 |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | Position within area |

**`forge_tool_settings`** — single-row JSON blob for panel settings

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INT` PK AUTO | |
| `settings_json` | `TEXT` | JSON: `{ shortcuts, custom_tabs, panel_height, cb_area }` |

The settings table is treated as a single-row store: on save, the most recent `id` row is updated; if no row exists, one is inserted.

**`scheduled_tasks`** — platform-wide task registry (read and triggered by Control Deck)

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INT` PK AUTO | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Display name shown in wrapper modal task dropdown |
| `order` | `INT` | Display order |
| `script_path` | `VARCHAR(512)` | Absolute path to shell script (Termux filesystem) |
| `args` | `TEXT` | Default args; used by "Copy Default" in modal |
| `run_now` | `TINYINT(1)` | Set to `1` by `run_wrapper` action to trigger immediate execution |
| `active` | `TINYINT(1)` | Whether task is active in scheduler |
| `schedule_time` | `TIME` | Scheduled time (if time-based) |
| `schedule_interval` | `INT` | Interval in seconds (if interval-based) |
| `last_run` | `DATETIME` | Updated by scheduler daemon after each run |
| `lock_scope` | `ENUM` | `global`, `entity`, or `none` |
| `require_lock` | `TINYINT(1)` | Whether mutex locking is enforced |

**`task_wrappers`** — Control Deck button definitions

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INT` PK AUTO | |
| `task_id` | `INT` FK | → `scheduled_tasks.id` (CASCADE DELETE) |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(100)` | Button label |
| `summary` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Pill text displayed on the button row |
| `fixed_args` | `TEXT` | Args injected into `scheduled_tasks.args` on run |
| `icon` | `VARCHAR(50)` | Emoji or short icon code |
| `display_order` | `INT` | Sort order in the grid |
| `active` | `TINYINT(1)` | Whether wrapper appears in the list |

As of the documented database snapshot (2026-05-26), 50 wrappers are defined covering generation tasks (frames, videos, audio, sketches, composites), environment switches (API provider selection), CLI tools (autopilot, lore-to-sketch, KG-to-sketch, GitHub sync, sequence curation, translation), and control actions (CANCEL GENFRAMES, STOP GENVIDEOS).

---

### API / Backend Integration

#### Forge Tool inline API

Accessed via `GET ?forge_tool_api=<action>` with a JSON POST body where applicable. Handler runs before any HTML output (uses `ob_end_clean()` to clear parent-page buffering).

| Action | Method | Payload | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| `save_settings` | POST | Full settings JSON object | `{ ok: true }` or `{ ok: false, error }` |
| `get_settings` | GET | — | `{ ok: true, data: {...} }` |

Settings are also PHP-injected directly into the JS `_settings` variable at page load via `json_encode($forgeToolSettings)`, so no async fetch is needed on init.

#### Clipboard Manager API

Accessed via `?api_action=<action>&view_area=<area>`.

| Action | Method | Payload | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| `cb_get` | GET | `view_area` (query param) | `{ status, data: [...items] }` |
| `cb_add` | POST | `{ content, label, view_area }` | `{ status, id }` |
| `cb_update` | POST | `{ id, content, label }` | `{ status }` |
| `cb_delete` | POST | `{ id }` | `{ status }` |
| `cb_pin` | POST | `{ id, view_area }` | `{ status, pinned: 0\|1 }` |
| `cb_reorder` | POST | `{ view_area, orders: [{id, sort_order}] }` | `{ status }` |

`cb_get` orders results: `pinned DESC, sort_order ASC, ci.id DESC`.

#### Control Deck API (`scheduler_runner.php`)

All actions via `POST` with `FormData`. Responds with JSON.

| Action | Payload | Effect | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| `run_wrapper` | `id` (wrapper ID) | Sets `scheduled_tasks.args = fixed_args` and `run_now = 1` for linked task | `{ ok, msg }` |
| `save_wrapper` | `wrapper_id`, `task_id`, `name`, `summary`, `fixed_args`, `icon`, `display_order` | INSERT or UPDATE `task_wrappers` | `{ ok }` |
| `delete_wrapper` | `id` | DELETE from `task_wrappers` | `{ ok }` |
| `get_wrapper` | `id` | SELECT single wrapper | `{ ok, data }` |
| `list_logs` | — | Reads `../logs/*.log`, filters, sorts by mtime desc, returns up to 50 | `{ ok, files: [{name, ts, time}] }` |

Log content itself is fetched from a separate file: `scheduler_log_fetch.php?file=<filename>` (returns raw text). This file is not included in the source provided but is a dependency. [VERIFY: confirm `scheduler_log_fetch.php` exists and validate path/security handling]

No PyAPI (FastAPI) calls in any of these three files. No external AI provider calls. The Control Deck triggers tasks which *in turn* invoke external providers (Pollinations, Freepik, etc.) via shell scripts, but this is outside the scope of this module.

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Forge Tool Panel

The panel is a fixed full-width bottom sheet. Key layout layers:

1. **Resize handle** — `44px` strip at the top with a drag bar and the `FORGE TOOL` title label. Dragging adjusts `--ft-panel-h` CSS variable live.
2. **Tab bar** — Horizontally scrollable, `44px` tall. Built-in tabs: Clipboard, Shortcuts, Settings. Custom tabs appended dynamically.
3. **Tab content area** — Fills remaining height. Each pane is a flex column with internal scroll.

The FAB defaults to `bottom: 80px; right: 16px` and restores saved `localStorage` coordinates on load. Tap-without-drag fires `togglePanel()`; drag-without-tap repositions.

The fullscreen modal overlay uses `position: fixed; inset: 0` — no padding — maximising iframe real estate. Floating close/open-in-new-tab buttons positioned absolutely over the iframe content.

#### Clipboard Manager (standalone)

Full-height `100dvh` flex column: header → add form → scrollable list → footer count bar. Designed for iframe embedding. Uses Bootstrap Icons (`bi-*`) for action buttons.

#### Control Deck

`max-width: 800px` centred layout. Two main sections:

- **Log console** — Always visible at the top. Collapsed by default (log box height `0`, opacity `0`). Click anywhere on the header to expand/collapse. The log box animates to `220px` height. The `<select>` dropdown sits inside the header and uses `event.stopPropagation()` to prevent toggling the console when changing log files.
- **Wrapper grid** — Vertical list of `task-row` cards below the console. Each row: large emoji icon, bold name, summary pill, run `▶` button, edit `✎` button. The `+ Add Preset` row at the bottom opens the CRUD modal.

The edit modal is a centred overlay (`max-width: 450px`). The task dropdown populates with all `scheduled_tasks` rows ordered by name, with `data-def-args` attributes for the "Copy Default" helper link.

#### Mobile-first notes (Forge Tool)

- Touch events on FAB drag, resize handle, and SortableJS handles (`touch-action: none`).
- `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` on panel bottom padding for notched devices.
- Tab bar uses `overflow-x: auto; scrollbar-width: none`.
- Shortcut grid: 4 columns default, 5 columns on `min-width: 480px`.

The Control Deck uses `max-width: 800px` with `padding: 10px` — functional on mobile but not specifically optimised for narrow viewports. It is primarily accessed via the Forge Tool shortcut modal (full-viewport iframe), which gives it adequate space.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bootstrap.php` | Internal | DB connection (`$pdo`), shared config — used by all three files |
| `env_locals.php` | Internal | Environment config, used by `scheduler_runner.php` |
| `App\Core\SpwBase` | Internal | `getJquery()` helper, used by `scheduler_runner.php` |
