### Known State / Notes

- The `ft-panel-close` button (`✕`) in the resize handle is rendered with `display:none`. Closing the panel currently requires tapping the FAB or pressing Escape. [VERIFY: intentional UX decision or deferred feature]
- The `?forge_tool_api=get_settings` endpoint exists but the JS init reads settings from the inline-injected PHP variable directly, not via this endpoint. The endpoint may be a fallback or unused path. [VERIFY]
- `forge_tool_settings` table DDL is not in the provided schema export. The PHP handler catches `\Throwable` silently if the table doesn''t exist, falling back to empty defaults. [VERIFY: DDL location in rollout/migration scripts]
- Custom tab iframes use `data-src` lazy loading — `src` is only set on first tab activation.
- `cb_area` is persisted both to `localStorage` (`ft_cb_area`) and to `forge_tool_settings.settings_json`. These can diverge across devices, but the platform is single-device (Android/Termux). [VERIFY: intended behaviour]
- SortableJS is lazy-loaded from CDN in `forge_tool.php`. Init polls `window.Sortable` every 50ms until available. If CDN is unreachable, drag-to-reorder is silently unavailable; all other features work normally.
- `scheduler_runner.php` uses `run_now = 1` as a trigger flag. The actual task execution is handled by the platform''s scheduler daemon (external to this file). There is no polling of task execution status beyond watching log files appear. A task queued via `run_wrapper` with no corresponding daemon running will sit with `run_now = 1` indefinitely. [VERIFY: confirm daemon watch loop location]
- The log file filter in `list_logs` excludes filenames containing `err` or ending in `_exit.log`. This is a substring match (`stripos`), so any log file with "err" anywhere in its name (e.g. `current_version.log`) would also be excluded. [VERIFY: intentional]
- The `pendingAutoSwitch` mechanism watches for a new `task_run_*_out.log` to appear after a run button is pressed. If the task starts slowly or reuses an existing log filename, the auto-switch may not fire. The 2.5-second delay before the first post-run poll (`setTimeout(..., 2500)`) is the tuning point for this.
- Control Deck version is noted in a source comment as "v5: Auto-expand on manual log selection."
