### API / Backend Integration

#### `lore_explorer_api.php` — Actions

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `search` | POST | Vector search across ChromaDB text collections, or recent-docs overview when query is empty |
| `fetch_doc_json` | POST | Returns the full aggregated payload for a single document (curator + world + story) |
| `lore_semantic_query` | POST | Phase 1 export: semantic ranking of matched entities across collections with DB enrichment |
| `lore_focused_export` | POST (JSON body) | Phase 2 export: extract matched entities only via `LoreAccessService`; returns structured snapshot |

**`fetch_visuals` (inline AJAX on `view_curated_docs.php`):**
- Accepts `doc_id`, `entity_name`, `entity_type` via POST.
- Queries `sketch_lore_history` → `sketches` → `frames`/`frames_2_sketches`/`sketch_analysis`.
- Returns sketch metadata, frame file paths, and optional curation data.

#### `api_lore.php` — REST Endpoint

A lightweight GET-based API for programmatic lore access (AI agent use):

| `mode` param | Returns |
|---|---|
| `full` | Story engine (episodes, narrative, keywords, hooks) |
| `entity` | Single entity lookup by name (alias-aware, via `LoreAccessService::getEntity`) |
| `category` | All entities in a category, optionally filtered by `role` param |
| `context` | AI-optimised context object for a named entity (`LoreAccessService::buildAgentContext`) |
| `story` | Raw story engine data |

#### `LoreAccessService` (`src/Service/LoreAccessService.php`)

The PHP-side equivalent of the JS "Omni-Capture" aggregation engine. Called by `lore_focused_export` and `api_lore.php`.

**Key methods:**

| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `loadDoc(int $docId)` | Loads `md_doc_analysis`, decodes JSON columns, merges lore points into entities, runs `processEntities()` |
| `processEntities()` | Iterates all world categories, calls `aggregateSingleEntity()` per item, builds `$this->aggregated` map and `$this->index` (name + alias → entity) |
| `aggregateSingleEntity($entity)` | Merges raw chunks into final entity: aliases, roles, attributes, relationships, timeline |
| `queryEntities($category, $roleFilter)` | Returns all aggregated entities in a category, optionally filtered by role substring |
| `getEntity($name)` | Case-insensitive alias-aware lookup into `$this->index` |
| `buildAgentContext($entityName)` | Returns `{identity, network, history}` object formatted for AI prompt injection |
| `getCuratorData()` | Returns curator array: bible, production notes, themes, mood, summary, narrative utility |
| `getWorldData()` | Returns the full `$this->aggregated` map |

#### ChromaDB / PyAPI

Vector queries are dispatched via `App\Core\PyApiVectorService::query()` — a PHP wrapper that calls the SAGE Python FastAPI (`$WORDNET_PYAPI_URL`) to perform cosine similarity search against ChromaDB collections registered in `chroma_collections`.

#### External Dependencies (CDN)

- **Swiper.js v11** — sketch preview gallery in entity modals
- **PhotoSwipe v5** — lightbox zoom for frame images
- **Bootstrap Icons 1.10 / 1.11** — icons throughout both views

