### 2.4 API / Backend Integration

#### `DawApi.php` — PHP API (inline, `?api_action=...`)

All API calls go to `daw/index.php?api_action=X` (the PHP page doubles as its own API handler before rendering).

| Action | Method | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| `get_entities` | GET | Paginated entity list with name search; dynamically queries entity table |
| `get_playlist` | GET | Audio files for a selected entity; falls back to `audios WHERE entity_type=X AND entity_id=Y` if `v_player_{entity}` view doesn''t exist |
| `add_entity` | POST | Creates new row in entity table with auto-generated name |
| `delete_entity` | POST | Deletes entity by ID |
| `update_field` | POST | Updates a single column on entity row (column whitelist via `SHOW COLUMNS`) |
| `toggle_regenerate` | POST | Flips any boolean column on entity row |
| `get_projects` | GET | Lists `daw_projects` |
| `create_project` | POST | Inserts `daw_projects` row with slugified `folder_name` |
| `get_project_files` | GET | Lists `daw_project_files` for a project |
| `save_project_file` | POST | Inserts new file row with serialized `state_data` |
| `update_project_file` | POST | Overwrites `state_data` on existing file |
| `load_project_file` | GET | Returns `state_data` for a file |
| `load_shot_audio` | GET | Shot-mode pre-population: resolves all 5 audio entity junctions + dialogue lines → returns `lanes[]` array + `video_url` |
| `get_shot_daw_saves` | GET | Lists `daw_shot_saves` for a shot |
| `save_shot_daw` | POST | Inserts `daw_shot_saves` row |
| `update_shot_daw_save` | POST | Overwrites `state_data` on shot save |
| `load_shot_daw_save` | GET | Returns `state_data` for shot save |
| `delete_shot_daw_save` | POST | Deletes `daw_shot_saves` row |
| `register_bounce` | POST | Moves render from `services_data/daw_renders/`, claims `audio_counter` ID, inserts `audios`, optionally inserts junction |

`DawConfig::$audioEntities` defines the whitelist of six valid entity types. `DawConfig::resolveEntity()` validates the `entity` parameter before any DB operation.

#### PyAPI DAW Service (`pyapi/services/daw_service.py`)

Registered at prefix `/daw` on port `8009` (`serv.conf.json` `"daw"` entry, `active: true`).

| Endpoint | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `POST /daw/bounce-async` | Accepts `multipart/form-data` with audio files + `state_json`; launches `render_bounce()` as `BackgroundTask`; returns `{status:"queued", task_id}` |
| `GET /daw/status/{task_id}` | Returns `{status: "processing"|"completed"|"failed", error}` |
| `GET /daw/download/{task_id}` | Streams completed WAV (used optionally; PHP `register_bounce` handles the DB side) |

#### PyAPI Infrastructure (`pyapi/main.py` + `serv.conf.json`)

The SAGE PyAPI is a FastAPI application on port 8009 (`uvicorn`, reload mode). Services are registered dynamically from `serv.conf.json` via `ServiceRegistry.register_active_services()` which imports each active module and calls `app.include_router()`. The DAW service is one of ~20 registered services; others include `backup`, `bloom`, `wordnet`, `graph`, `fuzz_ingest`, `aiprovider`, `openai_compatible`, etc. Inactive services (e.g. `rembg`, `vidrembg`, `svc`) have `"active": false` and are not loaded.

`db_connector.py` provides `get_db_connection()` — reads `DATABASE_URL` / `DATABASE_SYS_URL` / `DATABASE_WORDNET_URL` from `.env.local` or environment, caches `mysql.connector` connections, reopens on disconnect.

---

### 2.5 UI & Interaction

#### Layout Hierarchy

```
.daw-shell  (flex column, 100dvh)
├── .daw-shot-player-wrap   (shot mode only; aspect-ratio 1:1, max 40dvh)
├── .daw-menubar            (34px, overflow-x scroll, all action buttons)
├── .daw-body               (flex: 1)
│   ├── .daw-ruler-row      (28px; ruler-spacer 150px + ruler canvas)
│   └── .daw-timeline-scroll (flex: 1, overflow auto)
│       └── .daw-timeline-content  (absolute-positioned playhead + track rows)
│           ├── .playhead   (position:absolute, left=150px, transform=translateX)
│           └── .daw-track × N
│               ├── .track-head (sticky left 150px)
│               └── .track-lane (flex:1, clips positioned here)
├── .daw-bottombar          (48px fixed bottom; rewind / play-pause / stop / time display)
├── .bin-overlay + .bin-panel   (right flyout)
└── [Modals: param, file, master, trackFx, bounce, fv-modal]
```

#### Token System

CSS custom properties in `:root`:
- `--track-head-w: 150px` — overrides the default `220px` from base styles; also set as `window.DAW_TRACK_HEAD_W = 150` for JS access.
- `--bottombar-h: 48px` — `.daw-shell` has `padding-bottom` to prevent overlap.
- `--lane-h: 80px` — each `.daw-track` height.
- `--bin-w: 320px` — bin panel width (50vw on landscape).

Dark/light theme via `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and `data-theme` attribute (set in an inline script at page head to prevent flash).

#### Responsive / Mobile

- Pinch-to-zoom on the timeline scroll area.
- Bin panel: `width: min(320px, 92vw)`; landscape narrows entity list to `max-height: 20vh` and expands asset list to fill.
- Param modal: `padding-top: 12px; align-items: center` on landscape; `pm-body` gets `max-height: 60dvh; overflow-y: auto`.
- Track head delete button hidden via `display: none !important` to save space at 150px width.
- Auto-advance scrolling during playback.

#### Keyboard Shortcuts

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `Space` | Play / Pause |
| `Home` | Stop (seek to 0) |
| `F` | Toggle fullscreen |
| `Escape` | Close any open modal or bin |
| `Ctrl+Z` | Undo |
| `Ctrl+Y` / `Ctrl+Shift+Z` | Redo |

