---

## 1. Introduction Paragraph

The Enhanimatics module is SAGE''s primary workstation for reviewing, selecting, and actioning AI-generated image frames tied to any entity type in the production database — from sketch scenes and characters to animatics, locations, factions, and beyond. It solves the frame management problem: with tens of thousands of generated images across thousands of entities and map runs, the module provides a unified, filterable interface for browsing frames, composing enhancement instructions, queueing image-to-image enhancement passes, importing selected frames into the Animatics pipeline, and assigning frames directly to Storyboards. The module operates in three switchable list modes — Map Runs, Entities, and Frames — and is deeply integrated with SAGE''s Forge Filter system, enabling cross-cutting intersections driven by Fuzz candidates, Lore documents, KG nodes, Narrative sequences, Storyboards, and semantic vector search. It sits at the junction of the image generation and editorial pipelines, bridging raw AI output to structured story production.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

Enhanimatics serves as the central frame review and actioning tool for the SAGE production pipeline. Its primary responsibilities are:

- Browsing AI-generated frames grouped by **Map Run**, **Entity**, or as a flat **Frames** list
- Selecting frames for batch operations (enhancement or import)
- Submitting **Frame Enhancement** jobs (img2img / depth2img re-generation with a custom instruction)
- Importing selected frames into the **Animatics** table as video-generation seeds
- Assigning frames or entire map runs to **Storyboards**
- Filtering all of the above via multi-dimensional **Forge Intersection Filters**

It sits downstream of the image generation scheduler and upstream of the Animatics/video pipeline and editorial Storyboard system.

**Inputs:** Generated frames in `frames`, entity records from any allowed entity table, map run records from `map_runs`

**Outputs:** New records in `frame_enhancements`, `animatics`, and `storyboard_frames`; `regenerate_images` flag updates on entity records

---

### Key Features

**Three-mode list panel (Map Runs / Entities / Frames)**
A toggle button cycles through the three list display modes. Map Runs mode shows paginated batches of 4 runs at a time with frame counts and creation dates. Entities mode shows one entity per page with a frame count badge and a regenerate checkbox. Frames mode bypasses the list panel entirely and renders a full paginated frame grid (50 per page) directly, with entity name labels on each card.

**Entity selector**
A header dropdown switches the active entity type across all allowed entity types (driven by `$entityIcons` from `entity_icons.php`). Switching entity reloads the list, persisting navigation state via `localStorage`.

**Forge Intersection Filter**
A slide-up modal sidebar with six filter modes:
- **Fuzz** — filters by `fuzz_candidates` linked via `fuzz_mentions`
- **Lore Doc** — filters by `sketch_lore_history` via `documentations`, with two-step doc→entity scoping (whole doc, whole section, or specific entity name)
- **KG Node** — triple-path lookup: `sketch_lore_history.entity_name`, `kg_node_items`, and `fuzz_candidates` via `kg_node_id`
- **Sequence** — filters by `narrative_sequences.sequence_data` JSON
- **Storyboard** — filters by `storyboard_frames` → `frames.entity_id`
- **Semantic Text** — vector search via `PyApiVectorService` against the `sage_sketches_nu` or `sage_lore_entities_draft` ChromaDB collections

Active filters are displayed as dismissable pills in a filter bar below the header. Multiple filters intersect results (AND logic across filter types).

**Frame grid**
A responsive two-column (mobile) or auto-fill (desktop) image grid. Each card shows the frame image, a fullscreen zoom button (PhotoSwipe lightbox), and a click-selectable label. Cards are visually distinguished for imported frames (greyed + "IMPORTED" stamp) and enhanced frames (sepia + "ENHANCED" stamp). Grid display modifiers: Hide Imported, Hide Enhanced, Raw (removes all status overlays), and 1-Column mode.

**Quick Compose modal**
A slide-up instruction builder with tagged operation selectors (Remove, Change color of, Enhance, etc.), subject chips, colour swatches for colour-change operations, style modifier chips, and intensity selector. Composes a plain-text enhancement instruction that is injected into the prompt field.

**Clipboard chip bar**
A horizontally scrollable row of saved prompt phrases loaded from `clipboard_manager.php` for the `enhanimatics` view area. Clicking a chip fills the prompt field. A Manage button opens the clipboard manager in the frame details modal iframe.

**Add Frames modal (reference frame injection)**
Allows additional reference frames to be attached to an enhancement job beyond the primary selected frames. Two tabs: By Frame ID (manual entry) and Browse Variants (character × pose/expression/anima_poses area with AJAX dropdowns and a mini frame grid).

**Storyboard Picker bottom-sheet**
A full-featured storyboard selector triggered from either the STBA button (selected frames → storyboard) or the per-run ops menu (whole run → storyboard). Filters by category and, for editorial storyboards, by episode and sequence. Executes `import_run_to_storyboard` or `import_frames_to_storyboard` API actions.

**Per-item ops menus**
Map Run items: Regenerate run (sets `regenerate_images = 1` on all linked sketches), ScrollMagic link, Storyboard assignment.
Entity items: Edit (opens `entity_form.php` in the iframe modal), Copy, Prompt Matrix link, Delete.

**Entity sort bar (Entities mode)**
Sort by ID (default) or by Latest Frame (uses `MAX(from_id)` on the mapping table index for performance).

**Navigation persistence**
Current entity, page, and list mode are saved to `localStorage` under `enhanimatics_nav` and restored on next load for the same entity type.

**Deep-link params**
`entity_type`, `map_run_id`, `entity_id`, `search`, and `map_run_dis` (forces Entities mode on load) allow external links to land on a specific context.

