### API / Backend Integration

All API calls are handled by `enhanimaticism_api.php`, included when `api_action` is set in the request. All branches terminate with `json_encode()` + `exit`.

| `api_action` | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `list_forge_items` | GET | Returns items for a given forge `mode` (fuzz / doc / doc_entities / kg / seq / storyboard) |
| `get_map_runs` | GET | Paginated map run list for the active entity, with Forge intersection applied |
| `get_entities` | GET | Paginated entity list (1 per page) with frame count via mapping table |
| `get_frames_direct` | GET | Flat paginated frame list (50/page) for Frames mode |
| `get_frames` | GET | All frames for a given `map_run_id` or `entity_id` |
| `get_single_frame` | GET | Single frame by ID for Add Frames modal |
| `af_search_characters` | GET | AJAX character search for Browse Variants tab |
| `af_search_variants` | GET | AJAX variant search (poses / expressions / anima poses) |
| `af_get_variant_frames` | GET | Frames for a given character + variant area + optional variant ID |
| `get_storyboards` | GET | All non-archived storyboards with category and editorial metadata |
| `add_entity` | POST | Creates a blank entity row in the active entity table |
| `delete_entity` | POST | Deletes an entity by ID |
| `copy_entity` | POST | Duplicates an entity row (appends "(Copy)" to name) |
| `toggle_regenerate` | POST | Sets a boolean column on an entity row |
| `regenerate_run` | POST | Sets `regenerate_images = 1` on all sketches linked to a map run |
| `import_run_to_storyboard` | POST | Imports all frames of a run into a storyboard |
| `import_frames_to_storyboard` | POST | Imports a specific set of frame IDs into a storyboard |
| `submit_import` | POST | Creates `animatics` records from selected frames |
| `submit_enhancement` | POST | Creates `frame_enhancements` records with optional extra reference frames and depth2img flag |

**PyAPI / external calls:**
- `\App\Core\PyApiVectorService` — called in the `vector_text` Forge filter mode to query ChromaDB
- `\App\Service\LoreAccessService` — called in the `doc_entities` Forge mode to load structured lore entities from an analyzed documentation record
- No direct external AI provider calls are made from this module (generation is scheduler-driven)

