INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('485', 'mod_kg_view', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: Knowledge Graph System

**Files:** `kg_view.php`, `kg_api.php`, `kg_graph.php`, `ag_view.php`, `ag_api.php`, `ag_graph.php`, `mini_graph.php`, `kg_filter.php`

---

## Introduction

The Knowledge Graph (KG) system is SAGE''s curated lore intelligence layer — a hand-maintained, Markdown-rich graph of entities, concepts, relationships, and narrative constructs that spans the full universe of *The Anima Chronicles*. It gives the showrunner a persistent, interconnected knowledge base that can be browsed as a hierarchical tree, visualised as an interactive force-directed graph, searched semantically via ChromaDB embeddings, and exported as structured JSON snapshots for downstream AI context assembly. A parallel Automatic Graph (AG) system mirrors the KG''s architecture but operates at the level of individual documentation files: when a lore document is analysed by the Fuzz Forge pipeline, SAGE auto-generates a document-scoped AG — a lightweight, isolated subgraph of entities extracted from that document alone. Both graphs share the same editor UI patterns, visual gallery integration, and mini-graph modal system, making them complementary layers of the same lore intelligence stack.

---

## Purpose & Scope

### KG (Knowledge Graph)
The KG is the **authoritative, hand-curated** lore graph. It is long-lived, cross-document, and maintained directly by the showrunner. Its primary roles are:

- Organise lore entities (characters, locations, concepts, arcs, events, episodes, relationships) into a folder hierarchy
- Store rich Markdown content per node (character bibles, location descriptions, arc overviews, etc.)
- Track semantic relationships between nodes via typed, labelled edges
- Provide a semantic search interface (via ChromaDB) for context assembly before AI generation calls
- Serve as the bridge between raw lore documents (in `documentations`) and the rest of SAGE''s production pipeline

### AG (Automatic Graph)
The AG is a **per-document, AI-generated** subgraph. It is created automatically when a lore document is analysed by `md_doc_analysis`. Its roles are:

- Represent the entity/relationship structure visible within one specific document
- Provide a navigable, editable view of the entities the AI extracted from that doc
- Feed back into the KG via the KG Import Bridge (`view_kg_import.php`) when entities are promoted to the curated graph

### Inputs
- User: creates/edits nodes and edges via `kg_view.php` / `ag_view.php`
- Fuzz Forge pipeline: populates `ag_nodes` / `ag_node_items` automatically
- Semantic search: queries ChromaDB collections (`sage_kg_nodes_content`, `sage_kg_nodes_meta`)

### Outputs
- JSON snapshots (full graph, partial selection, semantic slice) for AI context assembly
- Node Markdown content downloadable as `.md` files
- Visual gallery connections (links to sketch frames via `sketch_lore_history`)
- KG/AG node IDs surfaced in `view_frame.php`, `fuzz_forge_landing.php`, and other modules

---

## Key Features

### KG Editor (`kg_view.php`)

**Flyout Sidebar Tree**
A hamburger-triggered flyout panel renders the full KG node hierarchy using jsTree, with folder (`kg_categories`) and leaf (`kg_nodes`) nodes. The tree supports:
- Real-time search (250 ms debounce)
- Drag-and-drop reordering (toggled via a `kg_dnd_enabled` localStorage flag, persisted across sessions)
- Context menu (rename, archive) on both folders and nodes
- Deep-link support: loading `kg_view.php?node_id=N` auto-selects and opens the target node

**Markdown Editor**
Node content is edited in a Toast UI Editor instance (WYSIWYG markdown, dark/light theme-aware). The editor is re-initialised on each node load. Ctrl+S / Cmd+S triggers save. Content is stored as raw Markdown in `kg_nodes.content`.

**Node Metadata Bar**
Above the editor: node ID display, name input, type selector (note / relationship / character / location / event / concept / arc / episode), comma-separated keywords field, and folder assignment dropdown.

**Linked Entities Drawer**
A bottom slide-up drawer shows all `kg_node_items` edges for the selected node — both outgoing (edges this node owns) and incoming (edges from other nodes pointing here). Each row shows:
- Entity type pill (colour-coded by type)
- Directional badge for incoming links (`← from`)
- Navigable label (KG-to-KG links call `loadNode()` in-place; other types open in their native views)
- Relationship label badge
- Edit and remove actions

Clicking the drawer handle toggles open/collapsed. The drawer becomes visible whenever a node is selected.

**Gallery Pill**
When a sketch is linked to the current node via `sketch_lore_history`, a cyan "Gallery" pill appears in the drawer handle. Clicking it opens a fullscreen Swiper gallery of the sketch''s frames. Each frame has a detail button that opens `view_frame.php` in the Frame Detail modal. Mini-graph pills (KG and AG) are embedded in the gallery header.

**Fuzz Pill**
When a `fuzz_candidates` record with `status = ''promoted''` is linked to the node (`fuzz_candidates.kg_node_id`), a purple "FUZZ" pill appears in the drawer handle, linking directly to `fuzz_forge_landing.php`.

**TTS Widget**
A topbar Text-to-Speech widget reads node Markdown content aloud via `api_tts_inline.php` (en_US-libritts_r-medium model). Play/stop controls and a loading spinner are embedded in the topbar.

**Export Modal**
A two-tab export modal:
- *Full Graph tab*: A picker tree (mirrors the sidebar tree) lets the user select specific folders/nodes or export all. Options for including full lore content (Markdown) and graph edges. Exports a columnar JSON snapshot.
- *Semantic Slice tab*: A plain-language query field runs a semantic search via ChromaDB (through `kg_api.php?action=semantic_query`). Results are ranked by relevance score with content status indicators (empty/stub/partial/filled). Selected nodes are exported as a focused snapshot.

**Curated Docs Inline Viewer**
Linked `md_doc` items with deep-link metadata (JSON-encoded `focus_type` + `focus_entity` in the `note` field) open `view_curated_docs.php` in an in-page modal (iframe) rather than navigating away.

**Mini-Graph Modal**
KG and AG graph pills throughout the UI can open `mini_graph.php` in an iframe modal (`showMiniGraphModal()`), allowing focused neighbourhood traversal without leaving the current view.

**Import Button**
A fixed import button (📥) navigates to `view_kg_import.php` — the KG Import Bridge for promoting AI-generated lore entities from `md_doc_analysis` into the curated KG.

---

### KG API (`kg_api.php`)

All AJAX operations for the KG pass through this single endpoint. Actions:

| Action | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `fetch_tree` | GET | Returns jsTree-formatted nodes and categories |
| `get_node` | GET | Fetches a node with its outgoing + incoming edges |
| `save_node` | POST | Creates or updates a node (name, content, keywords, type, category) |
| `delete_node` | POST | Archives a node (sets `status = ''archived''`) |
| `rename_node` | POST | Quick rename from tree context menu |
| `create_category` | POST | Creates a folder |
| `rename_category` | POST | Renames a folder |
| `delete_category` | POST | Deletes folder, orphans its nodes and subcategories to root |
| `move_node` | POST | Handles DnD reordering (updates `category_id` or `parent_id`) |
| `add_item` | POST | Creates a `kg_node_items` edge |
| `update_item` | POST | Updates an existing edge |
| `remove_item` | POST | Deletes an edge |
| `search` | GET | SQL LIKE search across name/content/keywords |
| `export_snapshot` | GET | Full columnar JSON export of all active nodes and edges |
| `semantic_query` | POST | ChromaDB semantic search across `sage_kg_nodes_content` + `sage_kg_nodes_meta` |
| `focused_snapshot` | POST | Columnar JSON export of a specific node ID list (with optional content) |
| `fetch_visuals` | POST | Looks up linked sketch frames via `sketch_lore_history`, resolves KG and AG node IDs for mini-graph pills |
| `get_fuzz_candidate_for_node` | GET/POST | Returns the promoted `fuzz_candidates` record linked to a KG node |

**Semantic Query internals:** Queries two ChromaDB collections in parallel (`sage_kg_nodes_content` weight 1.0, `sage_kg_nodes_meta` weight 0.6). Distances are converted to similarity scores (1 - d/2), weighted, then merged by taking the best score per node. Results are joined against `kg_nodes` to return type, category, content status, and a 200-character excerpt.

**Columnar snapshot format:** Rather than per-row key repetition, snapshots use a `{ fields: [...], rows: [[...], [...]] }` structure to minimise token cost when pasting into AI context windows. Content status (`empty` / `stub` / `partial` / `filled`) is derived from `CHAR_LENGTH(content)` at export time.

---

### KG Graph Visualiser (`kg_graph.php`)

A full-viewport Sigma.js v2 + Graphology force-directed graph visualiser for the entire active KG.

**Key capabilities:**
- PHP pre-fetches all active `kg_nodes` and `kg_node_items` (KG-node-to-KG-node edges only) and embeds them as JSON
- ForceAtlas2 layout runs client-side via `graphology-library` (auto-stops after 2.5 s, can be toggled)
- Node size scales with degree (`4 + sqrt(degree) * 1.5`)
- Tap/click on a node opens the node side panel; drag repositions nodes
- Side panel shows node name, type, and buttons: Open in Editor, Open in Fuzz (if promoted candidate linked), View Details (opens a full Markdown detail modal with connections), Add Link
- **Details modal** renders node content via `marked.js` with a browser history stack (back/forward navigation between nodes)
- **Visual gallery** in the details modal fetches sketches via `kg_api.php?action=fetch_visuals`
- **Curation analysis modal** renders `sketch_analysis` quality scores, themes, and entity breakdowns
- **Filter modal** (kg_filter.php pattern): a picker tree stored in `localStorage` under `kg_live_graph_filter` hides/shows nodes in the reducers — excluded nodes are set `hidden: true` by the `nodeReducer`
- Node search highlights matches and dims non-matches; matched nodes can be exported as a focused snapshot
- Export: search match exports use `focused_snapshot`; full export uses `export_snapshot`

---

### KG Filter (`kg_filter.php`)

A standalone mobile-friendly page for configuring which nodes appear in the graph visualiser. Designed to be opened before launching `kg_graph.php` or `kg_staging_graph.php`.

**Features:**
- Two-tab interface: "Live Graph" (storage key `kg_live_graph_filter`) and "Staging Graph" (storage key `kg_staging_graph_filter`)
- Same picker tree as the export modal — folder-aware, cascading checkboxes, indeterminate state, open/closed state persisted to localStorage
- Status dot in footer: orange when a filter is active (not all nodes selected), grey when all nodes visible
- "Save" writes to localStorage without navigating; "Open Graph" saves then redirects to the selected graph
- Uncheck-all / check-all shortcuts

---

### AG Editor (`ag_view.php`)

Architecturally mirrors `kg_view.php` but is document-scoped. Key differences:

- A document selector dropdown at the top switches the active document (URL param `doc_id`). Switching reloads via `window.location.href`
- Tree, nodes, categories, and edges are all partitioned by `doc_id` — all API calls include it
- No semantic ChromaDB search (AG search is SQL keyword scoring fallback)
- No Fuzz pill (AG nodes are not directly linked to `fuzz_candidates`)
- Export modal is simplified: full export + a keyword-scored "semantic" search tab (no vector DB needed)
- Gallery pill resolves visuals via an inline POST handler in `ag_view.php` itself (not `ag_api.php`), using `sketch_lore_history` scoped to the entity name and `doc_id`
- Mini-graph pills in the gallery header link to both `mini_graph.php?graph=ag&...` and `mini_graph.php?graph=kg&...` when both IDs resolve

---

### AG API (`ag_api.php`)

Mirrors `kg_api.php` but every action requires a `doc_id` parameter and all queries filter by it. Additional action:

| Action | Description |
|---|---|
| `fetch_docs` | Lists all documents that have an `md_doc_analysis` record (the set of documents available for AG editing) |

Incoming edge detection differs from KG: because AG edges are often label-based (not ID-based), the `get_node` action resolves incoming edges by matching `ag_node_items.item_label` against `ag_nodes.name` within the same `doc_id`.

Semantic query uses SQL keyword scoring (no ChromaDB), summing term-in-name (3 pts) and term-in-content (1 pt) matches.

---

### AG Graph Visualiser (`ag_graph.php`)

Mirrors `kg_graph.php` but scoped to a single document. A document dropdown in the topbar switches documents via redirect. Edge resolution joins `ag_node_items` to `ag_nodes` by label match (since AG edges store target entity name, not ID). Includes a deep-link "Open in Curated Docs" button in the node panel, which constructs a `view_curated_docs.php` URL with `focus_type` and `focus_entity` params derived from the node''s type and name.

---

### Mini-Graph (`mini_graph.php`)

A standalone, iframe-embeddable focused subgraph viewer for either the KG or AG. Designed to be loaded inside `showMiniGraphModal()` from `modal_frame_details.php` or from any graph pill in the system.

**Parameters:**

| Param | Description |
|---|---|
| `graph` | `kg` (default) or `ag` |
| `node_id` | Focal node ID |
| `doc_id` | Required when `graph=ag` |
| `hops` | Neighbourhood depth, 1–4 (default 1) |

**Architecture:**
1. PHP performs a BFS from the focal node up to `$hops` edges deep, collecting neighbour IDs
2. For KG: resolves via `kg_node_items.item_id` (outgoing) and reverse lookup (incoming)
3. For AG: resolves via both `item_id` and `item_label` match (handles label-based edges)
4. PHP calls the PyAPI (`/graph/layout`) with the subgraph to pre-compute ForceAtlas2 positions server-side (5 s timeout; falls back to random placement if PyAPI is unavailable)
5. Pre-computed `x`/`y` coordinates are embedded in the node JSON; the client skips the auto-layout loop when positions are present
6. Sigma.js renders the result with focal node highlighted in amber at larger size
7. Clicking a node opens a side panel with Re-center (reloads mini_graph with new focal node), View Details (in-page modal with Markdown content and connections), and Open in Editor links
8. A hops selector triggers a page reload with the updated `hops` param
9. Memory optimisations: pixel ratio capped at 1.5 (prevents WebGL OOM on high-DPR Android), edge labels disabled above 150 edges, input JSON arrays cleared after graph construction

---

## Data Model

### KG Tables

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `kg_nodes` | Core node records: name, node_type, content (Markdown), keywords, category_id, status (active/archived), sort_order |
| `kg_categories` | Folder hierarchy: parent_id (self-referential), name, sort_order |
| `kg_node_items` | Edge records: node_id (source), item_type, item_id, item_label, relationship, note, sort_order |

`kg_nodes.node_type` values: `note`, `relationship`, `character`, `location`, `event`, `concept`, `arc`, `episode`

`kg_node_items.item_type` values: `kg_node`, `character`, `anima`, `location`, `background`, `artifact`, `vehicle`, `generative`, `sketch`, `frame`, `md_doc`, `episode`, `board`, `other`

A special `md_doc` item type with a JSON-encoded `note` field (`{ "focus_type": "...", "focus_entity": "...", "doc_name": "..." }`) enables deep-link navigation to a specific entity within `view_curated_docs.php`.

### AG Tables

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `ag_nodes` | Per-document node records — same structure as `kg_nodes` plus mandatory `doc_id` |
| `ag_categories` | Per-document folder hierarchy — same as `kg_categories` plus `doc_id` |
| `ag_node_items` | Per-document edge records — same as `kg_node_items` plus `doc_id` |

AG tables have an `AUTO_INCREMENT` reaching ~28,000 nodes and ~62,000 edges, reflecting the volume of AI-extracted entities across all analysed lore documents.

### Supporting Tables (read-only from KG/AG)

| Table | Used for |
|---|---|
| `documentations` | AG document list (`fetch_docs`), lore deep-link validation |
| `md_doc_analysis` | Determines which documents have AG data (join on `doc_id`) |
| `chroma_collections` | Metadata only — ChromaDB collection names referenced by `semantic_query` |
| `sketch_lore_history` | Resolves entity name → sketch → frames for gallery pill and `fetch_visuals` |
| `sketches` | Name and description for the gallery modal title/description |
| `frames` | Individual frame filenames for gallery swiper slides |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Alternative frame→sketch join path |
| `fuzz_candidates` | Resolves promoted Fuzz candidate for the Fuzz pill (`kg_node_id` FK) |

---

## API / Backend Integration

### PyAPI (FastAPI)

| Endpoint | Used by | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `POST /chroma/query_json` | `kg_api.php` → `semantic_query` | Vector search across two ChromaDB collections |
| `POST /graph/layout` | `mini_graph.php` | Server-side ForceAtlas2 pre-computation (150 iterations) |

PyAPI base URL is resolved via `bash/pyapi_echo.sh` in `kg_api.php` and from `$GLOBALS[''WORDNET_PYAPI_URL'']` (default `http://127.0.0.1:8009`) in `mini_graph.php`.

### TTS

`api_tts_inline.php` — called from the KG view topbar widget. Model: `en_US-libritts_r-medium`. Strips Markdown syntax before synthesis.

### No Scheduler Integration

The KG/AG system does not trigger any scheduler jobs directly. AG population is handled upstream by the Fuzz Forge / `md_doc_analysis` pipeline.

---

## UI & Interaction

### Layout Pattern

Both `kg_view.php` and `ag_view.php` use a fixed-height `100vh` flex column layout:
- Fixed topbar (52 px)
- Main content area (flex: 1, overflow hidden)
- Fixed bottom drawer (initially `translateY(100%)`, slides in when a node is loaded)

The sidebar is a CSS `transform`-based flyout (off-screen left, slides to `translateX(0)` when open), overlaid by a dim overlay. This pattern avoids layout reflow and works well on small mobile screens.

### Theme

Dark/light theme is controlled by `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` and `data-theme` on `<html>`. The Toast UI Editor and Sigma.js label colours update reactively via `MutationObserver`. Theme is applied inline before first paint via an immediately-invoked script tag to prevent FOUC.

### Mobile-First

- Sidebar width: `min(320px, 88vw)`
- Gallery modal swiper: square aspect ratio, `max-width: min(100vw, calc(100vh - 140px))`
- All modals: `max-width: 94vw` or `96vw`
- Graph visualisers: full viewport canvas, draggable panels with touch support
- Mini-graph: pixel ratio capped at 1.5 for WebGL memory safety on Android

### Toast Notifications

`toast(msg, type)` — fixed bottom-right, 2.8 s auto-dismiss, green/red left border for success/error.

### Modal Stack

Multiple modal layers are managed manually (no modal framework):
1. Sidebar flyout + overlay
2. Bottom drawer
3. Standard `.kg-modal-bg` modals (new node, new folder, link entity, edit folder)
4. Export modal (`.kge-modal-bg`)
5. Gallery modal (`.kg-gallery-modal-bg`)
6. Frame detail modal (`.kg-frame-view-modal`)
7. Mini-graph modal (`.kg-minigraph-modal-bg`)
8. Curated docs inline viewer (`.kg-curated-modal-bg`)

Escape key closes the topmost active modal (frame → curation → all others).

---

## Dependencies & Related Modules

### Libraries (CDN)

- **jsTree 3.3.12** — folder/node tree in sidebar
- **Toast UI Editor (latest)** — Markdown editor
- **Swiper 11** — gallery image carousel
- **Graphology 0.25.4** + **graphology-library 0.7.1** + **Sigma.js 2.4.0** — graph visualisers
- **marked 12** — client-side Markdown rendering in details modals
- **Bootstrap Icons 1.10** — icon font
- **jQuery 3.6** — AJAX and DOM helpers (graph visualisers and AG editor)
- **PhotoSwipe 5** — lightbox in AG graph visualiser

### Related SAGE Modules

| Module | Relationship |
|---|---|
| `fuzz_forge.php` / `fuzz_forge_landing.php` | Fuzz pill links; `fuzz_candidates.kg_node_id` FK |
| `view_kg_import.php` | KG Import Bridge — promotes AG/lore entities into the KG |
| `view_curated_docs.php` | Deep-linked from `md_doc` edges and Lore ref links in `view_frame.php` |
| `view_frame.php` / `FrameDetails.php` | Renders KG node and AG node links in the frame detail panel; resolves graph links via `sketch_lore_history` |
| `modal_frame_details.php` | Provides `showMiniGraphModal()` used by KG gallery pills and `view_frame.php` |
| `mini_graph.php` | Embedded in iframe by `showMiniGraphModal()` from many modules |
| `md_doc_analysis` pipeline | Populates `ag_nodes` and `ag_node_items` automatically |
| `api_tts_inline.php` | Called by TTS widget in KG editor topbar |
| `kg_staging_graph.php` / `kg_staging_api.php` | Staging-environment mirrors of the live KG graph and API — referenced by `kg_filter.php` [VERIFY: staging files not included in this recipe dump] |

---

## Known State / Notes

- The `kg-hamburger`, `kg-export-btn`, and `kg-import-btn` buttons in `kg_view.php` have `opacity: 0.5` set in CSS with no corresponding interaction to restore them to full opacity — this appears intentional (visual de-emphasis) but may be an oversight. [VERIFY]
- The `#kg-editor` has `max-height: 55vh` applied in CSS — this constrains the editor height and may clip content on very small screens. [VERIFY intended]
- The AG export modal''s semantic search tab uses SQL keyword scoring, not ChromaDB — this means relevance is purely lexical (term frequency), not semantic. This is a deliberate fallback since AG nodes are not embedded in ChromaDB collections. [VERIFY if AG embedding is planned]
- `ag_view.php` includes a hidden `ag-export-btn` (inline `style="display:none;"` on the button element itself, overriding the `display:none` style attribute in the fixed-position inline style block — the button effectively never appears). [VERIFY if intentionally hidden]
- The AG graph visualiser (`ag_graph.php`) has a bug in `detailsBuildConnections()`: both the outgoing and incoming sections call `makeSection` with the `incoming` array rather than one using `outgoing`. [VERIFY / known bug]
- `mini_graph.php` clears the `dbNodes` and `dbEdges` JS arrays after graph construction (`dbNodes.length = 0`) to free memory — this is an intentional Android/Termux memory optimisation.
- The KG filter (`kg_filter.php`) references `kg_staging_api.php` and `kg_staging_graph.php` for the Staging tab — these files are not included in this recipe dump and may be a separate staging module. [VERIFY staging module exists]
- ChromaDB collection names used by `semantic_query`: `sage_kg_nodes_content` and `sage_kg_nodes_meta`. The `chroma_collections` table tracks available collections but is not directly queried by these endpoints.
- Node archival is soft-delete only (`status = ''archived''`). No hard-delete path exists in the current API.
- The `kg_node_items` table has reached AUTO_INCREMENT ~6,278 and `kg_nodes` ~6,075, indicating substantial graph density.
