INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('484', 'mod_chromatool', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: ChromaTool & Vector Layer

`sage_module_chromatool.md` — SAGE 2.0 Module Documentation

---

## 1. Introduction

The ChromaTool is SAGE''s browser-based administration interface for the ChromaDB vector database, providing direct CRUD access to the collections that power semantic search across the entire production pipeline. It solves the operational problem of inspecting, debugging, and manually managing vector data without requiring CLI access to the underlying Chroma server, which runs on a separate tablet device. The tool connects to two distinct backends simultaneously: the Chroma native HTTP API (v2, port 8000) for collection management and item browsing, and the SAGE PyAPI (port 8009) for embedding generation and semantic search queries. Together with the surrounding PHP service classes (`PyApiVectorService`, `PyApiProxy`) and the Python ingestion scripts, ChromaTool sits at the intersection of SAGE''s MariaDB content layer and its vector search layer, providing the tooling needed to keep those two systems in sync.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

ChromaTool (`public/chromatool.php`) is an authenticated PHP view that exposes the ChromaDB vector store to the browser. Its primary jobs are:

- Listing, creating, and deleting Chroma collections.
- Browsing stored vectors (documents, metadata, and a compact embedding visualisation).
- Running semantic search queries against any collection, routed through the PyAPI embedding layer.
- Manually inserting new documents (auto-chunked and embedded by PyAPI).

It is a diagnostic and administrative tool rather than a production pipeline component. The ingestion pipelines (`ingest_sketches.py`, `ingest_docs.py`, `ingest_kg.py`) populate Chroma automatically; ChromaTool lets Sebastian inspect and correct that state interactively.

**Inputs:** HTTP form/GET parameters from the browser; document text for manual insertion.  
**Outputs:** Rendered HTML views of collection state; POST actions that modify Chroma data.

---

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Collection list | Displays all collections sorted alphabetically, with UUID, metadata, and action links. |
| Create collection | Form with alphanumeric/dash/underscore name validation; calls Chroma API v2 directly. |
| Delete collection | Available both from the home table and from the per-collection Manage view; guarded by a JS `confirm()` prompt. |
| Browse view | Paginated table (20 items per page) showing item ID badge, document text preview (3-line clamp), metadata JSON block, and a 10-bar mini embedding visualiser derived from the first 10 dimensions of the stored vector. Supports bulk-delete via checkbox selection. |
| Semantic search | Free-text query form; calls `PyApiVectorService::query()` which routes to `/chroma/query` or `/chroma/query_json` on the PyAPI. Results are displayed as scored cards with cosine-distance colour coding: green < 0.3, yellow < 0.7, red ≥ 0.7. |
| Manual insert | Textarea for document text plus a JSON metadata field; delegates to PyAPI `/chroma/add_text` which handles chunking and embedding automatically. |
| Manage view | Per-collection danger zone providing a second explicit delete path. |
| Connection status | Footer shows resolved IP:port for both Chroma (`:8000`) and PyAPI (`:8009`), resolved at runtime via `bash/pyapi_echo.sh`. |
| Forge UI theming | Reads `localStorage(''spw_theme'')` on load and sets `data-theme` on `<html>` for consistent dark/light rendering with the rest of SAGE. |

---

### Data Model

ChromaTool itself does not read or write MariaDB. It operates entirely against the Chroma HTTP API and the PyAPI. The MariaDB tables below are the *source of truth* that the ingestion scripts transform into Chroma vectors, and ChromaTool lets you inspect the result.

#### MariaDB tables (read by ingestion scripts, not by chromatool.php directly)

| Table | Role |
|---|---|
| `sketches` | Scene/sketch records; primary ingestion target for `sage_sketches_nu` collection. |
| `sketch_analysis` | AI-scored quality, entities, themes, classification per sketch. |
| `sketch_ingredients` | Ingredient fragments that contributed to a sketch prompt. |
| `frames` | Individual AI-generated image frames. |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Many-to-many join between frames and sketches. |
| `tags` | Vocabulary of named tags. |
| `tags_2_frames` | Tag-to-frame associations. |
| `tags_2_sketches` | Tag-to-sketch associations. |
| `chroma_collections` | Registry table mapping collection names to type (`text`/`image`) and embedding dimension. Acts as the source-of-truth catalogue for which Chroma collections exist and what they hold. |

#### Chroma collections (browsed/searched by chromatool.php)

| Collection | Contents | Embedding model |
|---|---|---|
| `sage_sketches_nu` | 3-vector split per sketch: `primary`, `narrative`, `style` | MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dim) |
| `sage_nu_images` | CLIP Vision embeddings per frame image | CLIP-ViT-B-32 vision (512 dim) |
| `sage_nu_lore_draft` / `sage_nu_lore_mature` | Documentation/lore doc vectors | MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dim) |
| `sage_kg_nodes_meta` | KG node identity + keywords | MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dim) |
| `sage_kg_nodes_content` | KG node full markdown content (partial/filled only) | MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dim) |

---

### API / Backend Integration

#### Chroma Native API (v2 — direct HTTP from PHP)

All Chroma calls are made by the `ChromaAdminV2` class defined inline in `chromatool.php`. The host IP is resolved at runtime by executing `bash/pyapi_echo.sh` and parsing the returned URL.

| Operation | Chroma v2 Endpoint |
|---|---|
| Heartbeat | `GET /api/v2/heartbeat` |
| Version | `GET /api/v2/version` |
| List collections | `GET /api/v2/tenants/default_tenant/databases/default_database/collections` |
| Create collection | `POST …/collections` |
| Delete collection | `DELETE …/collections/{name}` |
| Get items (browse) | `POST …/collections/{id}/get` with `include: [embeddings, metadatas, documents]` |
| Delete items | `POST …/collections/{id}/delete` with `ids: [...]` |

Collection UUID resolution is handled by `getCollectionIdByName()`, which walks the list response to find the UUID needed for item-level operations.

#### PyAPI (FastAPI, port 8009 — via `PyApiVectorService`)

| Operation | PyAPI Endpoint | Used by |
|---|---|---|
| Semantic search | `POST /chroma/query` (form) | Browse → Search view |
| JSON-body search with `where` filter | `POST /chroma/query_json` | `PyApiVectorService::queryJson()` |
| Add text with auto-chunking | `POST /chroma/add_text` | Insert view |
| Delete by ID | `POST /chroma/delete` | — |
| Delete by metadata field | `POST /chroma/delete_where` | Ingestion scripts |
| Text embedding (MiniLM) | `POST /embed` | Internal to `chroma_service.py` |
| Image embedding (CLIP Vision) | `POST /embed_image` | Internal to `chroma_service.py` |
| CLIP text-to-image search embedding | `POST /embed_search_query` | Internal to `chroma_service.py` |
| Unload heavy models | `POST /embed/unload` | Ingestion scripts post-run |
| Health check | `GET /ping` | `PyApiVectorService::ping()` |
| Service discovery | `GET /service-discovery/{name}` | `ServiceRegistry` in `main.py` |

---

### Embedding Services (`pyapi/services/embed_service.py`)

Three embedding models are managed with a lazy-load / aggressive-unload memory strategy suited to the Android/Termux environment:

| Model | Endpoint | Dimensions | Load behaviour |
|---|---|---|---|
| `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` | `/embed` | 384 | Always resident (small) |
| `Qdrant/clip-ViT-B-32-vision` | `/embed_image` | 512 | Lazy load, unloaded after use |
| `Qdrant/clip-ViT-B-32-text` | `/embed_search_query` | 512 | Lazy load, unloaded after use |

`POST /embed/unload` frees the CLIP models and calls `gc.collect()`, reducing peak RAM. This is called automatically at the end of each ingestion batch.

---

### Chroma Service (`pyapi/services/chroma_service.py`)

Handles the full document lifecycle inside Chroma. Key design decisions:

**Text chunking:** `recursive_split_text()` splits documents into ~1000-character chunks with 150-character overlap, preferring newline or sentence boundaries. All chunks for a document share the same `parent_id` in metadata and are assigned IDs like `{base_id}_chunk_{i}`.

**`sketch_id` integer enforcement:** When `db_id` is present in metadata but `sketch_id` is not, the service copies `db_id` to `sketch_id` and coerces it to `int`. This is a V2 fix required because Chroma metadata filters use type-exact matching, and the PHP ingestion layer was previously sending string IDs.

**`where` filter normalisation (`_normalize_where_dict`):**

| Input shape | Output (Chroma operator format) |
|---|---|
| `{"field": {"$in": [1,2]}}` | Passed through as-is |
| `{"field": [1, 2]}` | `{"field": {"$in": [1, 2]}}` |
| `{"field": "42"}` | `{"field": {"$eq": 42}}` (numeric string coerced to int) |
| `{"field": "text"}` | `{"field": {"$eq": "text"}}` |

Two query endpoints exist: `/query` (form-encoded, backward-compatible) and `/query_json` (JSON body, preferred for complex `where` filters with nested arrays).

---

### PHP Service Layer

#### `PyApiProxy` (abstract base, `src/Core/PyApiProxy.php`)

Abstract base class providing cURL transport methods for all PyAPI calls. Key methods:

- `executeApiRequest()` — form-encoded POST, no file upload.
- `executeApiRequestWithImage()` / `executeApiRequestWithImages()` — multipart POST with `CURLFile` attachment(s).
- `executeApiRequestWithImageJson()` — multipart POST returning decoded PHP array.
- `executeGetRequest()` — simple GET.
- `executeCurlRequest()` (private) — shared cURL kernel with 60s connect / 300s total timeout.

#### `PyApiVectorService` (`src/Core/PyApiVectorService.php`)

Extends `PyApiProxy`. Resolves the PyAPI host at construction time by executing `bash/pyapi_echo.sh`. Key methods:

| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `ping()` | Fast health check (2s connect / 3s total timeout). Returns `bool`. |
| `query()` | Main search entry point. Automatically routes to `queryJson()` when a `where` filter is supplied with text-only input. |
| `queryJson()` | JSON-body POST to `/chroma/query_json`. Preferred for filtered queries to avoid form-encoding issues with nested arrays. |
| `extractSketchIds()` | Collapses chunked Chroma results to unique sketch IDs by reading `sketch_id` from returned metadata (not from parsing the chunk ID string). Returns array sorted by distance ascending. |
| `cleanIds()` | Legacy ID parser kept for frame/image queries where IDs are not chunked. **Not suitable for sketch queries.** |

#### `AbstractContextEngine` / `VectorContextEngine` (`src/Core`)

`VectorContextEngine` extends `AbstractContextEngine` and provides the ranked-results interface consumed by the Sketch Library and other content viewers.

| Method | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `getRankedItems(?int $contextId, ?string $customQuery)` | Single-query path. If `$contextId` is set, pulls `summary` and `thematics` from `md_doc_analysis` to construct the query text. |
| `getRankedItemsMulti(?int $contextId, array $queries)` | Multi-query union. Runs each query independently against the `sage_sketches_nu` collection, merges results by sketch ID. Applies a +0.05 per-extra-hit bonus (capped at +0.20) to boost sketches relevant to multiple queries. |
| `runVectorQuery()` (private) | Parses Chroma response: extracts sketch ID from `sketch_(\d+)` pattern in raw ID strings, converts cosine distance to score via `1 - dist`. |

#### `SketchLibrary` (`public/SketchLibrary.php`)

Data-hydration class that takes ranked sketch ID arrays and returns fully-populated PHP arrays ready for JSON serialisation.

- `hydratePage()` — paginates a sorted ID list and batch-fetches sketch rows, joining `sketch_analysis` and all associated frames via a subquery that checks both `frames.entity_id` and `frames_2_sketches`.
- `hydrateSpecificIds()` — supports mixed input of plain integers or `[''sketch_id'' => n, ''frame_id'' => m]` objects, allowing callers to request a specific frame thumbnail.
- `formatRow()` — normalises output: parses JSON columns, sorts frames by ID descending (newest first), falls back to `/placeholder.png` if no frames exist. Attaches `isMatch`, `matches`, `curation` data.

---

### Ingestion Scripts

Three Python scripts ingest content from MariaDB into Chroma, all sharing the same structural pattern: **sync → purge outdated → process pending**.

Change tracking uses the `vector_state` table (`entity_type`, `entity_id`, `collection`, `status`, `last_ingested_at`).

#### `pyapi/utils/ingest_sketches.py`

3-vector strategy per sketch. Requires both `sketch_analysis` AND `sketch_sequence_analysis` to be present before a sketch is eligible.

| Vector type | Text fields | ID format |
|---|---|---|
| `primary` | Name, description, narrative role, themes, characters, locations, artifacts | `sketch_{id}_primary` |
| `narrative` | Narrative function, layers, energy, position, intensity, structure type, edit relationship, standalone, connective hint | `sketch_{id}_narrative` |
| `style` | Emotional tone, visual style, symbolic meaning | `sketch_{id}_style` |

Shared metadata stored on all three vectors: `sketch_id` (int), `db_id` (int), `type`, `name`, `quality`, `narrative_mask`, `layer_mask`, `confidence`, `energy`, `position`, `intensity`, `standalone`, `analyzed_at`.

Frame images are ingested separately into `sage_nu_images` using CLIP Vision embeddings, linked via `frames_2_sketches`. Only frames where `entity_type = ''sketches''` on the `frames` row are eligible.

Atomicity: all three text vectors must return HTTP 200 for the state to be marked `indexed`.

#### `pyapi/utils/ingest_docs.py`

Ingests lore documentation from the `documentations` + `md_doc_analysis` tables. Supports dynamic collection routing: documents can move between `sage_nu_lore_draft` and a mature collection based on `md_doc_analysis.target_collection`. Generates multiple sub-vectors per document: one overview, plus individual vectors for each character, faction, location, and episode concept extracted from the structured JSON analysis.

#### `pyapi/utils/ingest_kg.py`

Ingests knowledge graph nodes from `kg_nodes` into two collections:

- `sage_kg_nodes_meta` — always ingested, even for empty/stub nodes. Text is name + type + keywords + category.
- `sage_kg_nodes_content` — only for nodes with `content_status` of `partial` or `filled` (≥200 chars). Text is the full markdown content.

Content status thresholds: empty = 0 chars, stub < 200, partial < 600, filled ≥ 600.

All three scripts resolve the PyAPI URL by first checking the `SAGE_PYAPI_URL` environment variable, then falling back to executing `bash/pyapi_echo.sh`, then defaulting to `http://127.0.0.1:8009`.

#### Bash wrappers

`bash/ingest_docs.sh`, `bash/ingest_kg.sh`, `bash/ingest_sketches.sh` — each activates the PyAPI virtualenv at `pyapi/venv/bin/activate` and delegates to the corresponding Python script. They perform path and venv existence checks before running.

---

### PyAPI Application (`pyapi/main.py`)

FastAPI application running on port 8009. Services are registered dynamically via `serv.conf.json` (`ServiceRegistry`). Active services have their routers imported and included at startup.

`ServiceRegistry` supports two address-resolution strategies per service:
- Static `address` field in config.
- `route_script` pointing to a Python file in `pyapi/routes/` with a `get_address()` function for dynamic IP resolution (e.g. hotspot address lookup).

The `/service-discovery/{service_name}` endpoint exposes resolved addresses to PHP callers, allowing the PHP layer to discover where tablet-side services are running.

Environment setup handled at startup: `HF_HOME` set to `cnmodels/` for Hugging Face model cache; Kaggle credentials directory created at `token/.kaggle/` with `chmod 700`.

---

### UI & Interaction

- **Layout:** Single-page PHP with view routing via `?action=` GET parameter. Navigation bar contains a collection selector `<select>` (navigates immediately on change) plus contextual tab links (Browse / Search / Insert / Manage) that appear once a collection is selected.
- **Connection status badge:** Top-right, shows resolved Chroma and PyAPI host addresses.
- **Browse table:** Zebra-striped with high-contrast alternating rows. Bulk-delete uses a hidden `<input id="deleteIdsInput">` populated by checkbox JS (`toggleAll` + individual `change` listeners) before form submit.
- **Embedding visualiser:** 10 `<div>` bars whose opacity is `min(1, max(0.1, |dim_val| * 5))`. Provides a glanceable sanity check that embeddings are non-zero.
- **Search results:** Colour-coded distance badges. Document text shown inline (not truncated in search results).
- **Forge UI:** Inherits `/css/base.css` and the global dark/light theme toggle. Viewport scale set to `0.65` for tablet-optimised layout.
- **Home button:** Loaded via `/js/sage-home-button.js` pointing back to `/dashboard.php`.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Relationship |
|---|---|
| SAGE PyAPI (`pyapi/main.py`) | Required for embeddings and semantic search. ChromaTool will show a connection error if the tablet PyAPI is offline. |
| `PyApiVectorService` / `PyApiProxy` | PHP service classes consumed by ChromaTool and by other modules that need vector search (e.g. Auto-Narrative Laboratory, Sketch Library views). |
| `VectorContextEngine` | Consumes `PyApiVectorService`; provides ranked sketch results to the Showrunner, PLUSH, and any other narrative sequencing views. |
| `SketchLibrary` | Hydrates ranked sketch IDs from `VectorContextEngine` into full display records. |
| `bash/pyapi_echo.sh` | Runtime IP resolution for the PyAPI host. Generated by `hotspot_echo.sh`; must be regenerated when the tablet''s IP changes. |
| `chroma_collections` (MariaDB) | Catalogue of registered collections. Not queried by `chromatool.php` directly but should stay in sync with what Chroma actually contains. |
| `vector_state` (MariaDB) | Change-tracking table used by all three ingestion scripts. Not displayed in ChromaTool but inspectable via DBTool. [VERIFY: table DDL not included in this dump] |
| Knowledge Graph module | `ingest_kg.py` populates the `sage_kg_nodes_*` collections browsed here. |
| Fuzz Forge / Lore module | `ingest_docs.py` populates the lore collections browsed here. |

