INSERT INTO `documentations` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `desc_short`, `keywords`, `content`, `duration`, `type`, `category_id`, `target_collection`, `sort_order`, `is_active`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `regenerate_audios`, `active_map_run_id`) VALUES ('482', 'mod_narratives_v11', NULL, NULL, NULL, '# SAGE Module: Showrunner — Narrative Sequencer & Auto-Narrative Laboratory

**File:** `sage_module_narratives_v11.md`
**Source files:** `narratives_v11.php`, `narratives_api_v11.php`, `narratives_query_helpers_v11.php`, `auto_narratives_v11.php`, `auto_narratives_api_v11.php`, `filter_forge_api.php`
**Database tables:** `narrative_sequences`, `narrative_sequences_auto`

---

## 1. Introduction

The Showrunner is SAGE''s editorial sequencing studio — a two-part module that lets the producer manually assemble or algorithmically generate visual narrative sequences from the platform''s sketch library. The manual editor (`narratives_v11.php`) provides a film-strip timeline, a paginated card library, and a multi-dimensional filter system for finding contextually relevant sketches and dragging them into an ordered sequence. Alongside it, the Auto-Narrative Laboratory (`auto_narratives_v11.php`) runs an AI-directed pipeline that autonomously selects and chains shots according to a chosen director logic, world lore, and entity context, producing sequences that can be reviewed and promoted into the main editor. Together these views form the primary story-assembly layer in the SAGE production pipeline, connecting the lore knowledge graph, the Chroma vector store, and the sketch library into a single sequencing workflow.

---

## 2. Purpose & Scope

### What it does

- Allows the producer to browse the sketch library filtered by lore document context, Forge entity filters, or direct ChromaDB semantic queries, then drag sketches onto a horizontal film-strip timeline to build an ordered narrative sequence.
- Provides an automated generation mode (Auto-Narrative Lab) where an AI Director reasons about each successive shot using world lore, a rich query engine, and optional KG graph-walking, producing coherent shot chains.
- Saves and loads sequences to the database, with the manual editor writing to `narrative_sequences` and the auto-lab writing pending results to `narrative_sequences_auto` before promotion.

### Pipeline position

Sits downstream of sketch generation and curation (sketches exist and are tagged/analysed), and upstream of storyboard assembly and video sequencing. Sequences produced here feed into `vidbat.php` (VidBat video review), the Timelines module, and storyboard exports.

### Inputs / Outputs

| Direction | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| Input | Sketches from `sketches` + `frames` tables; lore from `documentations` + `md_doc_analysis`; KG from `kg_nodes` / `kg_node_items`; vector embeddings from ChromaDB (`sage_sketches_nu`) |
| Output | Saved rows in `narrative_sequences` (manual) or `narrative_sequences_auto` (generated); hydrated sequence arrays used by downstream modules |

---

## 3. Key Features

### 3.1 Film-Strip Timeline (Manual Editor)

A horizontally scrollable SortableJS list at the top of the screen. Sketches are dragged from the card library below and drop into ordered slots. Each slot shows a thumbnail, an ordinal badge, and a remove button. The timeline supports frame-level granularity — each slot records both `sketch_id` and `frame_id` so a specific frame variant is preserved on save/load.

### 3.2 Card Library (Swiper Gallery)

A paginated, Swiper.js-based grid of sketch cards in the lower half of the screen. Each card shows a 16:9 thumbnail with frame navigation arrows (‹ ›) for cycling between frame variants of the same sketch. Cards have action buttons: description reader, curation analysis modal, and an inline entity edit form loaded in a full-screen iframe. Drag handles allow sketches to be pulled directly into the timeline.

### 3.3 Context Selector

A `<select>` dropdown in the control strip that routes library loading. Options include:

- **⚙️ Forge Filter** — activates the Forge Filter modal; results are driven by the Filter Forge API.
- **🧬 Chroma: Sketches / Images / All** — activates the Chroma query bar; a semantic text query is sent directly to ChromaDB, bypassing the standard context engine.
- **Lore Documents** — any document with a `narrative_utility` score (from `md_doc_analysis`) appears here; selecting one drives the Advanced Filter modal with document-specific entity categories.

### 3.4 Advanced Filter Modal (Standard)

A three-column drag-and-drop interface:

1. **Categories** — fixed list (`episodes`, `scene_hooks`, `characters`, `locations`, `factions`, `artifacts`), fetched from `narratives_api_v11.php?action=get_filter_cats`.
2. **Available Items** — entity names within the selected category and document, fetched via `get_filter_items`. Each item has a drag handle (`::`) and a Peek button (👁) that opens an Entity Preview modal showing full lore data without leaving the filter workflow.
3. **Filter Pot** — the active selection. Items dragged here are serialised on Apply into a `filter_payload` JSON object sent to the API.

**V11 Hybrid Engine Settings** appear below the free-text field:

| Toggle | Behaviour |
|--------|-----------|
| Enable Graph-Walker (KG) | Walks 1-degree outgoing and incoming edges from each entity''s KG node; appends relationship text to the lore query |
| Enable SQL Tag Striker | Runs a LIKE-based strike against `tags_2_sketches` on entity names and (if KG is active) neighbour names; exact matches are priority-inserted at the front of the pool and given a +0.2 score bump |
| Enable Chroma Sweep | Default on; when off, the Chroma vector query is bypassed entirely and the pool is SQL-only |

### 3.5 Forge Filter Modal

A separate amber-themed modal activated when the Context Selector is set to **Forge Filter**. Provides dedicated searchable picker sections for:

- Fuzz Concept (`fuzz_candidates`, promoted only)
- Lore Document (with nested entity-within-doc sub-filter)
- Knowledge Graph Node
- Narrative Sequence
- Storyboard
- Semantic / Vector text input
- Text search (name / frame name)
- Direct Sketch ID or Frame ID lookup

Supports AND (intersection) or OR (union) combine modes. A **Preview Results** section renders a paginated thumbnail grid without leaving the modal. On Apply, parameters are passed to `filter_forge_api.php` and results are loaded via `loadForgeLibraryPage()`.

### 3.6 Chroma Query Bar

Visible only when a Chroma collection option is selected. A single text input + Search button triggers `runChromaQuery()`, which builds Forge params with `vector_text` and `chroma_collection`, then calls `filter_forge_api.php` directly (bypassing the standard context engine).

### 3.7 Player (Sequence Playback)

A full-screen Swiper.js slideshow of the current timeline contents. Each slide shows the sketch image and provides frame-cycling arrows (‹ ›) that write back to the timeline slot. Action buttons for description, analysis, and edit are available per slide.

### 3.8 Debug Modal

When the API returns debug data (i.e., `DEBUG_MODE = true` and a filter was applied), a 🔬 button appears in the control strip. The debug modal renders each filter item''s final enriched Chroma query string, with colour-coded badges for enrichment status (`enriched` / `raw`) and warnings for failures.

### 3.9 Entity Preview (Peek)

Available in both the standard Advanced Filter and the Auto-Narrative Lab filter. Clicking 👁 on any filter item fetches `get_entity_preview` from the API, which reads from `LoreAccessService` and returns structured entity data (attributes, relationships, timeline). Renders above the filter modal at z-index 5000.

### 3.10 Save / Load

- **Save**: serialises the timeline as a JSON array of `{sketch_id, frame_id}` objects; writes to `narrative_sequences` via `SequenceManager`.
- **Load**: presents saved sequences from the DB; on selection, calls `hydrate_sequence` which resolves sketch + frame data and rebuilds the timeline DOM.
- **Deep-link**: `?sequence_id=N` auto-loads a sequence on page load.

---

### 3.11 Auto-Narrative Laboratory

A separate view (`auto_narratives_v11.php`) with a terminal-style monitor, a generated-sequences sidebar, and a visual filmstrip.

**Configuration controls:**

| Control | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Context & Filter | Lore document selector + 🧠 Filter button (same Advanced Filter modal) |
| Shots | Target sequence length (3–20) |
| Director Logic | `associative` (flow), `contrast` (conflict), `chaos` (random walk) |
| Use AI | Enables the `auto_director_v1` GeneratorConfig for per-shot AI reasoning |
| Single Run | Run once and stop (default on) |

The generation pipeline (`AutoDirectorV11` class in `auto_narratives_api_v11.php`) operates in two stages:

**Stage 1 — Hybrid Pool Build:** For each step, builds a sketch candidate pool by optionally running the SQL Tag Striker (exact/LIKE match against `tags_2_sketches`) and/or a Chroma vector sweep across `sage_sketches_nu`. SQL results are priority-inserted at the front of the pool.

**Stage 2 — Scored Selection:** Runs three weighted vector queries against the pool (Primary 40%, Narrative 35%, Style 15%, Novelty 10%), applies structural constraints (position, standalone, energy), uses temperature-controlled weighted-random selection, and optionally asks the AI Director for a next-shot intent string via `askAiForNextShot()`.

The AI Enricher (`filter_query_enricher_v1`) runs independently of the Director toggle — it always enriches lore query strings if the config is present. V11 adds KG graph-walking per entity before enrichment, injecting causal relationship text into both the Chroma query and the AI Director prompt.

**Debug mode** is enabled by `const DEBUG_MODE = true` in both PHP and JS. After a run, a **Download Debug Log (JSON)** button appears, containing full per-cycle logs, AI call inputs/outputs, and vector query details.

Generated sequences are saved to `narrative_sequences_auto` with `status = ''pending''`. The **💾 SAVE** button in the results sidebar promotes a sequence to `narrative_sequences` via `SequenceManager` and sets `status = ''promoted''`.

---

## 4. Data Model

### `narrative_sequences`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | INT AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `name` | VARCHAR(255) | User-assigned sequence name |
| `description` | TEXT | Editorial notes |
| `sequence_data` | LONGTEXT (JSON) | Array of `{sketch_id, frame_id}` objects |
| `linked_doc_id` | INT | FK → `documentations.id`; nullable |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | |
| `updated_at` | TIMESTAMP | ON UPDATE |

### `narrative_sequences_auto`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | INT AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `name` | VARCHAR(255) | Auto-generated title |
| `description` | TEXT | Director logic / mode summary |
| `sequence_data` | LONGTEXT (JSON) | Array of sketch IDs |
| `generation_log` | LONGTEXT (JSON) | Full decision log from `AutoDirectorV11::$logs` |
| `linked_doc_id` | INT | FK → `documentations.id`; nullable |
| `score` | FLOAT | Item count used as proxy score |
| `status` | ENUM | `pending`, `promoted`, `archived` |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | |

### Other tables read

| Table | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `sketches` | Sketch metadata; `searchable = 1` filter applied universally |
| `frames` | Frame records; `filename`, `entity_id`, `entity_type` |
| `sketch_analysis` | Curation data (entities, classification, scoring, thematics) |
| `sketch_sequence_analysis` | Structural metadata (position, energy, standalone, narrative_function) |
| `md_doc_analysis` | Lore document metadata; `series_bible`, `keywords`, `showrunner_analysis` |
| `documentations` | Lore document names and keywords |
| `kg_nodes` / `kg_node_items` | Knowledge graph; used by graph-walker and Forge filter |
| `fuzz_candidates` / `fuzz_mentions` | Fuzz lore concepts; used by Forge filter |
| `tags` / `tags_2_sketches` | Tag associations; used by SQL Tag Striker |
| `sketch_lore_history` | Maps sketches to lore entities and documents |
| `storyboards` / `storyboard_frames` | Used by Forge membership checks |

### ChromaDB

| Collection | Usage |
|-----------|-------|
| `sage_sketches_nu` | Primary sketch embeddings; queried by context engine and AutoDirectorV11 |
| `sage_nu_images` | Image embeddings; available via Chroma: Images selector |
| `__all__` | All collections; available via Chroma: All Collections selector |

