## 6. UI & Interaction

### Manual Editor Layout

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [Seq Name]          [⚡ Lab] [▶ Play] [💾] [📂]    │  ← Timeline header
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [film frame] [film frame] [film frame] …            │  ← Horizontal drag strip (SortableJS)
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [Context Select ▼] [🧠 Advanced Filter] [🔄] [🔬]  │  ← Control strip
│  [Chroma query bar — hidden unless Chroma selected]  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ← Page N of M →                                    │  ← Pagination bar
│  [card] [card] [card] [card] … (Swiper horizontal)  │  ← Library (Swiper.js)
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Mobile-first**: All layout uses `100vw`/`100vh` flex columns; the timeline is fixed-height (30vh), control strip is fixed (60px), library fills remaining space.
- **Drag**: SortableJS with `forceFallback: true` on all instances for reliable Android touch handling.
- **Modals**: Standard overlay pattern (`position:fixed; z-index:4000`); Filter modal uses `z-index:4000`, Entity Preview uses `z-index:5000`.
- **Toasts**: `Toast.show()` for non-blocking user feedback.
- **PhotoSwipe v5**: Tap on a card thumbnail opens a lightbox zoom.

### Auto-Narrative Lab Layout

```
┌────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────┐
│  Config panel                  │                  │
│  [Doc select] [🧠 Filter]      │  Generated       │
│  [Shots] [Logic] [Checkboxes]  │  Sequences       │
│  [START ENGINE]                │  (result cards)  │
├────────────────────────────────│                  │
│  Terminal monitor (green-on-   │                  │
│  black log output)             │                  │
├────────────────────────────────│                  │
│  Visual filmstrip (thumbnails) │                  │
└────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────┘
```

- **Terminal monitor**: Appends colour-coded log lines in real time during generation (cyan = info, green = success, amber = warn, purple = AI, orange = debug, sky = vector).
- **Debug log download**: When `DEBUG_MODE = true`, a JSON download button appears after each run containing full per-cycle structured logs.

---

