## 8. Known State / Notes

- `DEBUG_MODE` is currently hardcoded `true` in both `narratives_api_v11.php` and `auto_narratives_v11.php`. This should be set to `false` for production to avoid returning internal query data in API responses.
- The Auto-Narrative Lab filter modal calls `narratives_api.php` (without the `_v11` suffix) for `get_filter_cats` and `get_filter_items`. This appears to be a V10→V11 transition artifact; `[VERIFY]` whether `narratives_api.php` (non-versioned) still exists and is equivalent to `narratives_api_v11.php` for these actions.
- The Entity Preview (Peek) in the Auto-Narrative Lab also targets `narratives_api.php` (not `_v11`). Same `[VERIFY]` applies.
- The `doc_entity_name` sub-filter within the Forge modal (for filtering by a specific entity within a lore document) requires `sketch_lore_history` rows to be populated; sketches without lore history records will not surface under this filter.
- ChromaDB availability depends on the tablet PyAPI being online. Both the manual library and the auto-lab degrade gracefully when the tablet is unreachable: the manual editor falls back to an unfiltered SQL query (`sketch_analysis.overall_quality > 0`) and the auto-lab falls back to associative SQL tag-walking.
- The `enable_sql_tags` feature in V11 requires entity names to be present in `tags` rows (resolved via LIKE match). Entities with unusual name formats may not match. `[VERIFY]` coverage across the full entity roster.
- `narrative_sequences_auto` has AUTO_INCREMENT at 225 and `narrative_sequences` at 176 as of the schema dump — indicative of active use.
- Sequence data format changed between versions: older `narrative_sequences` rows may store a plain array of integers rather than `{sketch_id, frame_id}` objects. `hydrate_sequence` in `SketchLibrary` handles both formats. `[VERIFY]` backward-compatibility for all existing saved sequences.
