**File:** `sage_module_sketchup.md`
**Source files:** `public/sketchup.php`, `public/sketchup_api.php`, `public/sketchup_graph.php`, `src/SketchUp/SketchUp.php`

---

## 1. Introduction

The SketchUp Export module is SAGE''s primary data packaging tool, designed to extract coherent subsets of production content — sketches, frames, lore entities, and knowledge graph nodes — and bundle them into portable JSON or SQL dumps. It solves the practical problem of preparing context-rich data packages for use in AI inference pipelines, external tooling, or cross-environment migrations, where feeding raw, unfiltered table dumps would be impractical. SketchUp supports three source-selection modes: direct sketch search, narrative sequence resolution, and PLUSH story/collection traversal, giving the showrunner precise control over what production context gets packaged. It sits downstream of sketch generation and annotation, and upstream of any workflow that consumes structured SAGE lore as context — including the Auto-Narrative Laboratory, manual AI prompting, and external analysis pipelines.

---

## 2. Module Details

### Purpose & Scope

SketchUp Export assembles a structured, downloadable snapshot of SAGE production data centred on one or more sketches and their associated metadata. It is intended for:

- Feeding context packages into AI inference workflows (e.g. narrative generation, scene analysis)
- Exporting subsets of the knowledge graph alongside sketch/lore data
- Migrating sketch content between SAGE environments
- Creating reproducible reference snapshots for archival or review

**Inputs:** Sketch IDs (individual or range), narrative sequence ID, PLUSH story/collection ID, optional KG node selection, optional related-table flags.

**Outputs:** Downloadable `.json` or `.sql` file containing sketch rows, optional related table data, frames, and/or KG subpot.

---

### Key Features

#### Three Export Modes

The UI presents a tabbed mode switcher (`su-mode-tabs`). Only one mode is active at a time; the resolved sketch set is drawn from whichever mode is currently selected.

| Mode | Tab ID | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Standard | `su-tab-standard` | Manual sketch search by name/ID, plus optional numeric ID ranges |
| Narrative Sequence | `su-tab-sequence` | Resolves all sketches referenced inside a `narrative_sequences` record |
| PLUSH | `su-tab-plush` | Traverses a PLUSH story or collection and resolves all linked entity references |

#### Standard Mode — Sketch Search & Ranges

- Autocomplete search field queries `sketches` by ID or name (`search_sketches` action), debounced 250ms.
- Selected sketches render as removable chips.
- An optional "Include ID Ranges" panel (toggled by checkbox) accepts start/end numeric sketch IDs. Multiple ranges may be added and are resolved at export time.

#### Narrative Sequence Mode

- Autocomplete search queries `narrative_sequences` by ID or name.
- On selection, calls `resolve_sequence_sketches`, which parses the sequence''s `sequence_data` JSON for sketch references (entity_type=''sketches'', sketch_id fields, or nested sketches arrays) and also queries `frames_2_sketches` for frame-linked sketches associated with the sequence.
- A resolved banner displays the count of sketches found and provides a clear button.

#### PLUSH Mode

- Toggle between `story` and `collection` source types.
- Autocomplete searches `plush_stories` or `plush_collections` depending on type.
- On selection, calls `resolve_plush_entities`, which traverses: collection → story IDs → scene IDs → highlight block IDs (English only) → `plush_highlight_block_entities`.
- Entity references typed as `sketches` are routed to the sketch export pipeline; all other entity types (characters, factions, locations, KG nodes) are bundled as a `plush_entities` reference section in the output.
- A resolved banner shows counts of sketches and entity references found.

#### Additional Sketch Data (all modes)

Optional checkboxes include satellite tables per-sketch in the export:

| Checkbox Label | Table Exported |
|---|---|
| `sketch_analysis` | `sketch_analysis` |
| `sketch_sequence_analysis` | `sketch_sequence_analysis` |
| `sketch_overlay_texts` | `sketch_overlay_texts` |
| `sketch_ingredients` | `sketch_ingredients` |

#### Frames Export

A checkbox toggles inclusion of mapped frames. When enabled:
- Exports all `frames_2_sketches` rows where `to_id` is in the selected sketch set.
- Resolves `frame_id`s from that join plus any frames where `entity_type=''sketches''` AND `entity_id` is in scope.
- Exports those frame rows from `frames`.

#### Knowledge Graph Subpot Export

A collapsible section (toggled by `#chkKg`) adds KG node selection to the export:

- **Tree browser** (`#kgTreeWrap`): Hierarchical view of `kg_categories` (folders) and `kg_nodes` (leaves). Supports text filter, expand/collapse with localStorage-persisted open state, and checkbox selection.
- **Selected nodes chips** (`#kgSubpotChips`): Shows selected KG nodes as removable chips; each has a mini-graph launcher and an entity detail link.
- **Include edges checkbox** (`#kgIncludeEdges`): When checked, exports `kg_node_items` edges between selected nodes.
- **Subpot preview** (`#kgSubpotPreview`): Live text preview of selected nodes'' names, types, descriptions, and relationships (calls `kg_subpot_preview` action).

#### Mini-Graph Viewer (`SuGraph`)

Embedded in the KG section via `sketchup_graph.php`. Opens in a modal (`#skGraphModal`) with a Sigma.js force-directed graph:

- Load trigger: clicking the graph icon on any KG node chip.
- Fetches n-hop neighbourhood via `fetch_mini_graph` (1–3 hops, configurable).
- Node panel on click: re-center, view details (Markdown rendered via `marked.js`), or add to export selection.
- Detail panel: supports back/forward navigation history, connection pills (outgoing/incoming), and an "Add to Export" button synced with the main chip list.
- Layout: ForceAtlas2 via `graphology-library`; auto-stops after ~2.2s on initial load.

#### Entity Detail Modal

Clicking any sketch chip name opens `entity_form.php?entity_type=sketches&entity_id=…&view=modal` in an iframe overlay, allowing quick inspection without leaving the export page. KG node chips open the same modal for `kg_nodes`.

#### Export Execution

Both JSON and SQL exports are triggered from the nav bar buttons (`#btnExportJson`, `#btnExportSql`). The buttons disable during the fetch to prevent double-submission. The file is streamed as an attachment via `Content-Disposition` header.

---

### Data Model

#### Tables Read

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `sketches` | Primary export entity |
| `sketch_analysis` | Optional satellite: AI quality/entity analysis |
| `sketch_sequence_analysis` | Optional satellite: narrative function/shot analysis |
| `sketch_overlay_texts` | Optional satellite: multilingual overlay text |
| `sketch_ingredients` | Optional satellite: prompt construction ingredients |
| `frames` | Frame rows for mapped frames |
| `frames_2_sketches` | Frame-to-sketch join |
| `narrative_sequences` | Sequence search and `sequence_data` JSON parsing |
| `plush_stories` | PLUSH story search |
| `plush_collections` | PLUSH collection search |
| `plush_collections_2_stories` | Collection → story membership |
| `plush_scenes` | Story → scene traversal |
| `plush_highlight_blocks` | Scene → block traversal (filtered to `language_code=''en''`) |
| `plush_highlight_block_entities` | Block → entity references |
| `kg_categories` | KG tree folder structure |
| `kg_nodes` | KG node records |
| `kg_node_items` | KG edges (when `include_edges` is checked) |

#### Tables Written

None. SketchUp Export is strictly read-only.

#### Notable Schema Details

- `sketches.id` is the central key; all satellite tables join on `sketch_id` or `to_id`.
- `narrative_sequences.sequence_data` is a `longtext` JSON column; sketch references may be nested at arbitrary depth and are extracted recursively by `_extractSketchIdsFromSequenceData()`.
- `plush_highlight_block_entities.entity_type` is polymorphic (`characters`, `factions`, `locations`, `sketches`, `kg_nodes`, etc.).
- `kg_node_items.item_type=''kg_node''` with non-null `item_id` defines directed KG edges.

---

### API / Backend Integration

All requests are POSTed to `sketchup_api.php` as JSON with an `action` discriminator.

| Action | Description |
|---|---|
| `search_sketches` | Name/ID autocomplete against `sketches` |
| `search_narrative_sequences` | Name/ID autocomplete against `narrative_sequences` |
| `resolve_sequence_sketches` | Parses sequence JSON + frame joins to produce sketch list |
| `search_plush` | Name/ID autocomplete against `plush_stories` or `plush_collections` |
| `resolve_plush_entities` | Traverses PLUSH hierarchy → returns sketches + other entity refs |
| `export` | Delegates to `SketchUp::generateExportData()` + `generateSql()`; streams file |
| `fetch_tree` | Returns full `kg_categories` + `kg_nodes` tree for the KG browser |
| `kg_subpot_preview` | Returns text preview of selected KG nodes and edges |
| `fetch_mini_graph` | Returns n-hop node+edge neighbourhood for a given `node_id` |
| `get_node` | Returns single `kg_nodes` row (used by detail panel) |

No external AI provider calls are made from this module. No PyAPI (FastAPI) endpoints are involved. No scheduler jobs are triggered.

The core export logic lives in `src/SketchUp/SketchUp.php` (`App\SketchUp\SketchUp` class):

- `generateExportData(array $config): array` — collects sketches, satellite tables, frames, and KG data into a structured array.
- `generateSql(array $exportData): string` — serialises the array to `INSERT IGNORE INTO …` statements.
- `fetchTableInChunks()` — chunks large ID arrays into batches of 500 for safe `IN (…)` queries.

---

### UI & Interaction

#### Layout

```
[Nav bar: title | JSON btn | SQL btn]
[Mode tab switcher: Standard | Narrative Sequence | PLUSH]
[Active mode panel]
[Additional Sketch Data + Frames panel]  ← always visible
[KG Subpot panel (collapsed by default)]
```

The workspace is `max-width: 900px` centred, with `padding: 30px 15px 100px` — the large bottom padding accounts for mobile browser chrome.

#### Responsive / Mobile

- `flex-wrap` throughout nav and row layouts.
- Chip rows and mode tabs are wrappable.
- Autocomplete dropdowns are `position: absolute` within their wrapper, scrollable to `max-height: 200px`.
- The KG tree is `max-height: 280px` scrollable.
- The mini-graph modal is `width: 95%; max-width: 900px; height: 85vh`.

#### Theme Support

The module declares both `[data-theme="dark"]` and `[data-theme="light"]` CSS overrides mapping all Forge UI variables. It also explicitly re-maps standard Forge variable names (`--bg`, `--surface`, `--card`, etc.) to its `--pl-*` equivalents so that the included `sketchup_graph.php` sub-component inherits correct colours without modification.

#### Toast & Feedback

Uses the shared `/js/toast.js` for success/warn/error notifications. Export buttons show an inline "Exporting…" state and are disabled during the fetch.

#### Autocomplete Behaviour

All three autocomplete fields (sketch, sequence, PLUSH) share the same dismiss-on-outside-click handler registered once at `DOMContentLoaded`.

---

### Dependencies & Related Modules

| Dependency | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `sketchup_graph.php` | PHP include | Embedded in the KG panel via `<?php include ?>` |
| `src/SketchUp/SketchUp.php` | PHP class | Core export logic, instantiated in `sketchup_api.php` |
| `entity_form.php` | Linked page | Opened in iframe modal for sketch/KG entity inspection |
| `bootstrap.php` / `env_locals.php` | Bootstrap | Standard SAGE PDO/MySQLi setup |
| `curation.php` (template) | Layout | Rendered via `$spw->renderLayout()` |
| Sigma.js 2.4.0 | CDN JS | Graph renderer for mini-graph modal |
| graphology 0.25.4 | CDN JS | Graph data structure |
| graphology-library 0.7.1 | CDN JS | ForceAtlas2 layout |
| marked.js 12 | CDN JS | Markdown rendering in KG node detail panel |
| jQuery 3.7.1 | CDN JS | DOM utility |
| Bootstrap Icons 1.10.0 | CDN CSS | UI icons |
| `/js/toast.js` | Local JS | Notification toasts |
| `/css/base.css`, `/css/toast.css` | Local CSS | Forge base styles |

**Modules that link into SketchUp:** Dashboard / sidebar nav (standard SAGE navigation). The PLUSH Editor and Narrative Sequencer are the upstream sources whose data this module consumes.

---

### Known State / Notes

- `sequence_data` JSON parsing in `_extractSketchIdsFromSequenceData()` is a recursive scanner that accommodates several historic schema variants (entity_type/entity_id pairs, sketch_id fields, and keyed `sketches` arrays). It does not enforce a single canonical structure. `[VERIFY]` whether all active sequence formats are covered.
- The `plush_highlight_block_entities` query filters blocks to `language_code = ''en''` only, to avoid duplicate entity references from translated blocks. Non-English entity tagging would not be included.
- `cinemagics`, `cinemagics_2_sequences`, `sequence_overlay_texts`, and `system_languages` tables are present in the schema dump included with this module but are **not read or written** by SketchUp Export. They appear to be included as context for related modules.
- `plush_story_dates` and `plush_scene_dates` are also present in the schema but not used by this module.
- The `characters`, `factions`, and `locations` tables appear in the schema dump; they are referenced indirectly as entity types in `plush_highlight_block_entities` but their rows are not fetched into the export — only the entity reference records (type, ID, label) are included under `plush_entities`.
- The KG mini-graph `fetch_mini_graph` action hard-caps hops at `max(1, min(4, hops))` server-side, but the UI hop selector only offers values 1–3.
- `sketchup_graph.php` is described in a comment as "Exact clone of the graph environment from sceki adapted for SketchUp." `[VERIFY]` whether divergences exist between this and the primary KG view graph component that need to be kept in sync.
- No pagination is implemented on export; very large sketch ranges or KG selections will produce single large files. `fetchTableInChunks()` batches DB queries at 500 IDs but returns all results in memory.
